obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (101669)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title, commencement and application.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013&sectionId=101669&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Occupational`
  line `Safety, Health and Working Conditions Code, 2020.`
  line
  line `(2) It shall come into force on such date^1`
  line `as the Central Government may, by notification appoint; and`
  line `different dates may be appointed for different provisions of this Code and any reference in any such`
  line `provision to the commencement of this Code shall be construed as a reference to the coming into force of`
  line `that provision.`
  line
  line `(3) It shall not apply to the offices of the Central Government, offices of the State Government and`
  line `any ship of war of any nationality:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Code shall apply in case of contract labour employed through contractor in the`
  line `offices of the Central Government or in the offices of the State Government, where, the Central`
  line `Government or, as the case may be, the State Government is the principal employer.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. 21st day of November, 2025, vide Notifn. No. S.O. 5321 (E), dated 21st day of November, 2025, see Gazette of India,`
  line `Extraordinary, Part II, sec. 3 (ii).`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (101670)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013&sectionId=101670&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `(1) In this Code, unless the context otherwise requires, ---`
  line
  line `(a) "adolescent" shall have the same meaning as assigned to it in clause (i) of section 2 of the Child`
  line `and Adolescent Labour (Prohibition and Regulation) Act, 1986 (61 of 1986);`
  line
  line `(b) "adult" means a person who has completed his eighteenth year of age;`
  line
  line `(c) "agent" when used in relation to a mine, means every person, whether appointed as such or not,`
  line `who, acting or purporting to act on behalf of the owner, takes part in the management, control,`
  line `supervision or direction of such mine or of any part thereof;`
  line
  line `(d) "appropriate Government" means---`
  line
  line `(i) in relation to, establishments [other than those specified in sub-clause (ii)] carried on by or`
  line `under the authority of the Central Government or concerning any such controlled industry as may`
  line `be specified in this behalf by the Central Government or the establishment of railways including`
  line `metro railways, mines, oil field, major ports, air transport service or telecommunication service,`
  line `banking company or any insurance company (by whatever name called) established by a Central`
  line `Act or a corporation or other authority established by a Central Act or a Central public sector`
  line `undertaking or subsidiary companies set up by the Central public sector undertakings or`
  line `autonomous bodies owned or controlled by the Central Government, including establishment of`
  line `contractors for the purposes of such establishment, corporation or other authority, Central public`
  line `sector undertakings, subsidiary companies or autonomous bodies, as the case may be, the Central`
  line `Government:`
  line
  line `Provided that in the case of Central Public Sector Undertakings the appropriate Government`
  line `shall continue to be the Central Government even if the holding of the Central Government reduces`
  line `to less than fifty per cent. equity of the Central Government in that Public Sector Undertakings`
  line `after the commencement of this Code; and`
  line
  line `(ii) in relation to a factory, motor transport undertaking, plantation, newspaper establishment`
  line `and establishment relating to beedi and cigar including the establishments not specified in`
  line `clause (i), the concerned State Government where it is situated.`
  line
  line `Explanation. --- For the removal of doubts it is hereby clarified that State Government shall be`
  line `the appropriate Government in respect of occupational safety, health and working conditions in a`
  line `factory situated in that State;`
  line
  line `(e) "audio-visual production" means audio-visual produced wholly or partly in India and`
  line `includes ---`
  line
  line `(i) animation, cartoon depiction, audio-visual advertisement;`
  line
  line `(ii) digital production or any of the activities in respect of making thereof; and`
  line
  line `(iii) features films, non-feature films, television, web-based serials, talk shows, reality shows`
  line `and sport shows;`
  line
  line `(f) "audio-visual worker" means a person, who is employed, directly or through any contractor, in`
  line `or in connection with the audio-visual production to work as an artist including actor, musician, singer,`
  line `anchor, news reader, dancer, dubbing artist or stunt person or to do any work, skilled, unskilled,`
  line `manual, supervisory, technical, artistic or otherwise, and his remuneration with respect to such`
  line `employment in or in connection with the production of audio-visual does not exceed, where`
  line `remuneration is by way of monthly wages or where such remuneration is by way of lump sum, in each`
  line `case, such amount as may be notified by the Central Government;`
  line
  line `(g) "banking company" means a banking company as defined in clause (c) of section 5 of the`
  line `Banking Regulation Act, 1949 (10 of 1949) and includes the Export-Import Bank of India, the`
  line `Industrial Reconstruction Bank of India, the Small Industries Development Bank of India established`
  line `under section 3 of the Small Industries Development Bank of India Act, 1989 (39 of 1989), the`
  line `Reserve Bank of India, the State Bank of India, a corresponding new bank constituted under section 3`
  line `of the Banking Companies (Acquisition and Transfer of Undertakings) Act, 1970 (5 of 1970), a`
  line `corresponding new bank constituted under section 3 of the Banking Companies (Acquisition and`
  line `Transfer of Undertakings) Act, 1980 (40 of 1980);`
  line
  line `(h) "building or other construction work" means the construction, alteration, repairs, maintenance`
  line `or demolition in relation to buildings, streets, roads, railways, tramways, airfields, irrigation, drainage,`
  line `embankment and navigation works, flood control works (including storm water drainage works),`
  line `generation, transmission and distribution of power, water works (including channels for distribution of`
  line `water), oil and gas installations, electric lines, internet towers, wireless, radio, television, telephone,`
  line `telegraph and overseas communications, dams, canals, reservoirs, watercourses, tunnels, bridges,`
  line `viaducts, aqua-ducts, pipelines, towers, cooling towers, transmission towers and such other work as`
  line `may be specified in this behalf by the Central Government, by notification, but does not include`
  line `building or other construction work which is related to any factory or mine and the building or other`
  line `construction work where such work is for own residential purposes of an individual or group of`
  line `individuals for their own residence and the total cost of such work does not exceed rupees fifty lakhs`
  line `or such higher amount and employing more than such number of workers as may be notified by the`
  line `appropriate Government;`
  line
  line `(i) "building worker" means a person who is employed to do any highly skilled, skilled, semiskilled or unskilled, manual, technical or clerical work for hire or reward, whether the terms of such`
  line `employment are express or implied, in connection with any building or other construction work, but`
  line `does not include any such person who is employed mainly in a managerial or supervisory or`
  line `administrative capacity;`
  line
  line `(j) "cargo" includes anything carried or to be carried in a ship or other vessel, or vehicle;`
  line
  line `(k) "Chief Inspector-cum-Facilitator" means a Chief Inspector-cum-Facilitator appointed under`
  line `sub-section (5) of section 34;`
  line
  line `(l) "competent person", means a person or an institution recognised as such by the Chief Inspectorcum-Facilitator for the purposes of carrying out tests, examinations and inspections required to be`
  line `done in an establishment having regard to ---`
  line
  line `(i) the qualifications and experience of the person and facilities available at his disposal; or`
  line
  line `(ii) the qualifications and experience of the persons employed in such institution and facilities`
  line `available therein:`
  line
  line `Provided that in case of mines the competent person includes such other person who is`
  line `authorised by the manager referred to in section 67 to supervise or perform any work, or to`
  line `supervise the operation of machinery, plant or equipment and is responsible for such duties`
  line `assigned to him and also includes a shot firer or blaster;`
  line
  line `(m) "contract labour" means a worker who shall be deemed to be employed in or in connection`
  line `with the work of an establishment when he is hired in or in connection with such work by or through a`
  line `contractor, with or without the knowledge of the principal employer and includes inter-State migrant`
  line `worker but does not include a worker (other than part time employee) who is regularly employed by`
  line `the contractor for any activity of his establishment and his employment is governed by mutually`
  line `accepted standards of the conditions of employment (including engagement on permanent basis), and`
  line `gets periodical increment in the pay, social security coverage and other welfare benefits in accordance`
  line `with the law for the time being in force in such employment;`
  line
  line `(n) "contractor", in relation to an establishment, means a person, who---`
  line
  line `(i) undertakes to produce a given result for the establishment, other than a mere supply of goods`
  line `or articles of manufacture to such establishment, through contract labour; or`
  line
  line `(ii) supplies contract labour for any work of the establishment as mere human resource,`
  line
  line `and includes a sub-contractor;`
  line
  line `(o) "controlled industry" means any industry the control of which by the Central Government has`
  line `been declared under any Central Act in the public interest;`
  line
  line `(p) "core activity of an establishment" means any activity for which the establishment is set up and`
  line `includes any activity which is essential or necessary to such activity:`
  line
  line `Provided that the following shall not be considered as essential or necessary activity, if the`
  line `establishment is not set up for such activity, namely:---`
  line
  line `(i) sanitation works, including sweeping, cleaning, dusting and collection and disposal of all`
  line `kinds of waste;`
  line
  line `(ii) watch and ward services including security services;`
  line
  line `(iii) canteen and catering services;`
  line
  line `(iv) loading and unloading operations;`
  line
  line `(v) running of hospitals, educational and training Institutions, guest houses, clubs and the like`
  line `where they are in the nature of support services of an establishment;`
  line
  line `(vi) courier services which are in nature of support services of an establishment;`
  line
  line `(vii) civil and other constructional works, including maintenance;`
  line
  line `(viii) gardening and maintenance of lawns and other like activities;`
  line
  line `(ix) housekeeping and laundry services, and other like activities, where these are in nature of`
  line `support services of an establishment;`
  line
  line `(x) transport services including, ambulance services;`
  line
  line `(xi) any activity of intermittent nature even if that constitutes a core activity of an`
  line establishment;
  line
  line `(q) "day" means a period of twenty-four hours beginning at mid-night;`
  line
  line `(r) "District Magistrate", in relation to any mine, means the District Magistrate or the Deputy`
  line `Commissioner, as the case may be, who is vested with the executive powers of maintaining law and`
  line `order in the revenue district in which the mine is situated:`
  line
  line `Provided that in case of a mine, which is situated partly in one district and partly in another, the`
  line `District Magistrate for the purpose shall be the District Magistrate authorised in this behalf by the`
  line `Central Government;`
  line
  line `(s) "dock work" means any work in or within the vicinity of any port in connection with, or`
  line `required for, or incidental to, the loading, unloading, movement or storage of cargoes into or from`
  line `ship or other vessel, port, dock, storage place or landing place, and includes ---`
  line
  line `(i) work in connection with the preparation of ships or other vessels for receipt or discharge`
  line `of cargoes or leaving port;`
  line
  line `(ii) all repairing and maintenance processes connected with any hold, tank structure or lifting`
  line `machinery or any other storage area on board the ship or in the docks; and`
  line
  line `(iii) chipping, painting or cleaning of any hold, tank, structure or lifting machinery or any`
  line `other storage area on board the ship or in the docks;`
  line
  line `(t) "employee" means,---`
  line
  line `(i) in respect of an establishment, a person (other than an apprentice engaged under the`
  line `Apprentices Act, 1961 (52 of 1961)) employed on wages by an establishment to do any skilled,`
  line `semi-skilled, unskilled, manual, operational, supervisory, managerial, administrative, technical,`
  line `clerical or any other work, whether the terms of employment be express or implied; and`
  line
  line `(ii) a person declared to be an employee by the appropriate Government,`
  line
  line `but does not include any member of the Armed Forces of the Union:`
  line
  line `Provided that notwithstanding anything contained in this clause, in case of a mine a person is`
  line `said to be "employed" in a mine who works as the manager or who works under appointment by`
  line `the owner, agent or manager of the mine or with the knowledge of the manager, whether for`
  line `wages or not ---`
  line
  line `(a) in any mining operation (including the concomitant operations of handling and transport`
  line `of minerals up to the point of dispatch and of gathering sand and transport thereof to the mine);`
  line
  line `(b) in operations or services relating to the development of the mine including construction`
  line `of plant therein but excluding construction of buildings, roads, wells and any building work not`
  line `directly connected with any existing or future mining operations;`
  line
  line `(c) in operating, servicing, maintaining or repairing any part of any machinery used in or`
  line `about the mine;`
  line
  line `(d) in operations, within the premises of the mine, of loading for dispatch of minerals;`
  line
  line `(e) in any office of mine;`
  line
  line `(f) in any welfare, health, sanitary or conservancy services required to be provided under this`
  line `Code relating to mine, or watch and ward, within the premises of the mine excluding residential`
  line `area; or`
  line
  line `(g) in any kind of work, whatsoever, which is preparatory or incidental to, or connected with,`
  line `mining operations;`
  line
  line `(u) "employer" means a person who employs, whether directly or through any person, or on his`
  line `behalf, or on behalf of any person, one or more employees in his establishment and where the`
  line `establishment is carried on by any Department of the Central Government or the State Government,`
  line `the authority specified, by the head of such Department, in this behalf or where no authority, is so`
  line `specified, the head of the Department and in relation to an establishment carried on by a local`
  line `authority, the Chief Executive of that authority, and includes, ---`
  line
  line `(i) in relation to an establishment which is a factory, the occupier of the factory;`
  line
  line `(ii) in relation to mine, the owner of the mine, agent or manager referred to in section 67;`
  line
  line `(iii) in relation to any other establishment, the person who, or the authority which has`
  line `ultimate control over the affairs of the establishment and where said affairs are entrusted to a`
  line `manager or managing director, such manager or managing director;`
  line
  line `(iv) contractor; and`
  line
  line `(v) legal representative of a deceased employer;`
  line
  line `(v) "establishment" means---`
  line
  line `(i) a place where any industry, trade, business, manufacturing or occupation is carried on in`
  line `which ten or more workers are employed; or`
  line
  line `(ii) motor transport undertaking, newspaper establishment, audio-video production, building`
  line `and other construction work or plantation, in which ten or more workers are employed; or`
  line
  line `(iii) factory, for the purpose of Chapter II, in which ten or more workers are employed,`
  line `notwithstanding the threshold of workers provided in clause (w); or`
  line
  line `(iv) a mine or port or vicinity of port where dock work is carried out:`
  line
  line `Provided that in sub-clauses (i) and (ii), the threshold of worker specified therein shall not be`
  line `applicable in case of such establishment or class of establishments, in which such hazardous or`
  line `life threatening activity is being carried on, as may be notified by the Central Government:`
  line
  line `Provided further that notwithstanding any threshold provided in the definition of factory in`
  line `clause (w), for the purposes of Chapter II, the establishment specified in sub-clause (i) or`
  line `sub-clause (ii) or sub-clause (iii) shall be deemed to be the establishment within the meaning of`
  line `this clause though the number of employees employed are ten or more;`
  line
  line `(w) "factory" means any premises including the precincts thereof---`
  line
  line `(i) whereon twenty or more workers are working, or were working on any day of the preceding`
  line `twelve months, and in any part of which a manufacturing process is being carried on with the aid of`
  line `power, or is ordinarily so carried on; or`
  line
  line `(ii) whereon forty or more workers are working, or were working on any day of the preceding`
  line `twelve months, and in any part of which a manufacturing process is being carried on without the`
  line `aid of power, or is ordinarily so carried on,`
  line
  line `but does not include a mobile unit belonging to the armed forces of the Union, railways running shed or a`
  line `hotel, restaurant or eating place:`
  line
  line `Provided that where under any law for the time being in force in a State immediately before the`
  line `commencement of this Code, the number of workers specified is more or less than the number specified`
  line `in clause (i) or clause (ii), then, the number specified under the law of the State shall prevail in that State`
  line `till it is amended by the competent Legislature.`
  line
  line `Explanation I.--- For computing the number of workers for the purposes of this clause all the workers`
  line `(in different groups and relays) in a day shall be taken into account.`
  line
  line `Explanation II.--- For the purposes of this clause, the mere fact that an Electronic Data Processing Unit`
  line `or a Computer Unit is installed in any premises or part thereof, shall not be construed as factory if no`
  line `manufacturing process is being carried on in such premises or part thereof;`
  line
  line `(x) "family", when used in relation to a worker, means---`
  line
  line `(i) spouse;`
  line
  line `(ii) children including adopted children of the worker who are dependent upon him and have`
  line `not completed the age of eighteen years; and`
  line
  line `(iii) parents, grand-parents, widowed daughter and widowed sister dependent upon such`
  line worker.
  line
  line `Explanation.--- For the purposes of this clause, such dependents shall not be included who`
  line `are, for the time being, getting such income from such sources, as may be prescribed by the`
  line `appropriate Government;`
  line
  line `(y) "godown" means any warehouse or other place, by whatever name called, used for the storage`
  line `of any article or substance required for any manufacturing process which means any process for, or`
  line `incidental to, making, finishing or packing or otherwise treating any article or substance with a view to`
  line `its use, sale, transport, delivery or disposal as finished products;`
  line
  line `(z) "hazardous" means involving danger or potential danger;`
  line
  line `(za) "hazardous process" means any process or activity in relation to an industry or plantation`
  line `specified in the First Schedule where, unless special care is taken, raw materials used therein or the`
  line `intermediate or finished products, bye-products, hazardous substances, wastes or effluents thereof or`
  line `spraying of any pesticides, insecticides or chemicals used therein, as the case may be, would---`
  line
  line `(i) cause material impairment to the health of the persons engaged in or connected therewith,`
  line or
  line
  line `(ii) result in the pollution of the general environment;`
  line
  line `(zb) "hazardous substance" means any substance or such quantity of the substance as may be`
  line `prescribed by the appropriate Government or preparation of which by reason of its chemical or physiochemical properties or handling is liable to cause physical or health hazards to human being or may`
  line `cause harm to other living creatures, plants, micro-organisms, property or the environment;`
  line
  line `(zc) "industrial premises" means any place or premises (not being a private dwelling house),`
  line `including the precincts thereof, in which or in any part of which any industry, trade, business,`
  line `occupation or manufacturing is being ordinarily carried on with or without the aid of power and`
  line `includes a godown attached thereto;`
  line
  line `(zd) "industry" means any systematic activity carried on by co-operation between an employer and`
  line `worker (whether such worker is employed by such employer directly or by or through any agency,`
  line `including a contractor) for the production, supply or distribution of goods or services with a view to`
  line `satisfy human wants or wishes (not being wants or wishes which are merely spiritual or religious in`
  line `nature), whether or not,---`
  line
  line `(i) any capital has been invested for the purpose of carrying on such activity; or`
  line
  line `(ii) such activity is carried on with a motive to make any gain or profit,`
  line
  line `but does not include---`
  line
  line `(a) institutions owned or managed by organisations wholly or substantially engaged in any`
  line `charitable, social or philanthropic services; or`
  line
  line `(b) any activity of the appropriate Government relatable to the sovereign functions of the`
  line `appropriate Government including all the activities carried on by the Departments of the Central`
  line `Government dealing with defence research, atomic energy and space; or`
  line
  line `(c) any domestic service; or`
  line
  line `(d) any other activity as may be notified by the Central Government;`
  line
  line `(ze) "Inspector-cum-Facilitator" means an Inspector-cum-Facilitator appointed under`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 34;`
  line
  line `(zf) "inter-State migrant worker" means a person who is employed in an establishment and who---`
  line
  line `(i) has been recruited directly by the employer or indirectly through contractor in one State`
  line `for employment in such establishment situated in another State; or`
  line
  line `(ii) has come on his own from one State and obtained employment in an establishment of`
  line `another State (hereinafter called destination State) or has subsequently changed the`
  line `establishment within the destination State,`
  line
  line `under an agreement or other arrangement for such employment and draws wages not exceeding the`
  line `amount of rupees eighteen thousand per month or such higher amount as may be notified by the Central`
  line `Government from time to time;`
  line
  line `(zg) "machinery" means any article or combination of articles assembled, arranged or connected`
  line `and which is used or intended to be used for converting any form of energy to perform work, or which`
  line `is used or intended to be used, whether incidental thereto or not, for developing, receiving, storing,`
  line `containing, confining, transforming, transmitting, transferring or controlling any form of energy;`
  line
  line `(zh) "major port" means a major port as defined in clause (8) of section 3 of the Indian Ports Act,`
  line `1908 (15 of 1908);`
  line
  line `(zi) "manufacturing process" means any process for---`
  line
  line `(i) making, altering, repairing, ornamenting, finishing, packing, oiling, washing, cleaning,`
  line `breaking up, demolishing, or otherwise treating or adapting any article or substance with a view`
  line `to its use, sale, transport, delivery or disposal; or`
  line
  line `(ii) pumping oil, water, sewage or any other substance; or`
  line
  line `(iii) generating, transforming or transmitting power; or`
  line
  line `(iv) composing, printing, printing by letter press, lithography, offset, photogravure screen`
  line `printing, three Dimensional or four Dimensional printing, prototyping, flexography or other`
  line `types of printing process or book binding; or`
  line
  line `(v) constructing, reconstructing, repairing, refitting, finishing or breaking up ships or vessels;`
  line or
  line
  line `(vi) preserving or storing any article in cold storage; or`
  line
  line `(vii) such other processes as the Central Government may notify;`
  line
  line `(zj) "medical officer" means the medical officer appointed under sub-section (1) of section 42;`
  line
  line `(zk) "metro railway" means the metro railway as defined in sub-clause (i) of clause (1) of section 2`
  line `of the Metro Railways (Operation and Maintenance) Act, 2002 (60 of 2002);`
  line
  line `(zl) "mine" means any excavation where any operation for the purpose of searching for or obtaining`
  line `minerals has been or is being carried on and includes---`
  line
  line `(i) all borings, bore holes, oil wells and accessory crude conditioning plants, including the`
  line `pipe conveying mineral oil within the oilfields;`
  line
  line `(ii) all shafts, in or adjacent to and belonging to a mine, whether in the course of being sunk`
  line `or not;`
  line
  line `(iii) all levels and inclined planes in the course of being driven;`
  line
  line `(iv) all open cast workings;`
  line
  line `(v) all conveyors or aerial ropeways provided for bringing into or removal from a mine of`
  line `minerals or other articles or for the removal of refuse therefrom;`
  line
  line `(vi) all adits, levels, planes, machinery, works, railways, tramways and sidings in or adjacent`
  line `to and belonging to a mine;`
  line
  line `(vii) all protective works being carried out in or adjacent to a mine;`
  line
  line `(viii) all workshops and stores situated within the precincts of a mine and under the same`
  line `management and used primarily for the purposes connected with that mine or a number of`
  line `mines under the same management;`
  line
  line `(ix) all power stations, transformer sub-stations, converter stations, rectifier stations and`
  line `accumulator storage stations for supplying electricity solely or mainly for the purpose of`
  line `working the mine or a number of mines under the same management;`
  line
  line `(x) any premises for the time being used for depositing sand or other material for use in a`
  line `mine or for depositing refuse from a mine or in which any operations in connection with such`
  line `sand refuse or other material is being carried on, being premises exclusively occupied by the`
  line `owner of the mine;`
  line
  line `(xi) any premises in or adjacent to and belonging to a mine on which any process ancillary to`
  line `the getting, dressing or preparation for sale of minerals or coke is being carried on;`
  line
  line `(xii) a mine owned by the Government;`
  line
  line `(zm) "minerals" means all substances which can be obtained from the earth by mining, digging,`
  line `drilling, dredging, hydraulicing, quarrying or by any other operation and includes mineral oils (such as`
  line `natural gas and petroleum);`
  line
  line `(zn) "motor transport undertaking" means a motor transport undertaking employing motor transport`
  line `worker and engaged in carrying passengers or goods or both by road for hire or reward, and includes a`
  line `private carrier;`
  line
  line `(zo) "motor transport worker" means a person who is employed in a motor transport undertaking`
  line `directly or through an agency, whether for wages or not, to work in a professional capacity on a`
  line `transport vehicle or to attend the duties in connection with the arrival, departure, loading or unloading`
  line `of such transport vehicle and includes a driver, conductor, cleaner, station staff, line checking staff,`
  line `booking clerk, cash clerk, depot clerk, time-keeper, watchman or attendant, but does not include any`
  line `such person---`
  line
  line `(i) who is employed in a factory;`
  line
  line `(ii) to whom the provisions of any other law for the time being in force regulating the`
  line `conditions of service of persons employed in shops or commercial establishments apply;`
  line
  line `(zp) "newspaper" means any printed periodical work containing public news or comments on`
  line `public news and includes such other class of printed periodical work as may, from time to time, be`
  line `notified in this behalf by the Central Government;`
  line
  line `(zq) "newspaper establishment" means an establishment under the control of any person or body of`
  line `persons, whether incorporated or not, for the production or publication of one or more newspapers or`
  line `for conducting any news agency or syndicate and includes following newspaper establishments which`
  line `shall be deemed to be one establishment, namely:---`
  line
  line `(i) two or more newspaper establishments under common control;`
  line
  line `(ii) two or more newspaper establishments owned by an individual and his or her spouse`
  line `unless it is shown that such spouse is a sole proprietor or partner or a shareholder of a corporate`
  line `body on the basis of his or her own individual funds;`
  line
  line `(iii) two or more newspaper establishments publishing newspapers bearing the same or`
  line `similar title and in the same language in any place in India or bearing the same or similar title`
  line `but in different languages in the same State or Union territory.`
  line
  line `Explanation 1.--- For the purposes of sub-clause (i) two or more establishments shall be`
  line `deemed to be under common control where---`
  line
  line `(a) (i) the newspaper establishments are owned by a common individual or individuals;`
  line
  line `(ii) the newspaper establishments are owned by firms, if such firms have a substantial`
  line `number of common partners;`
  line
  line `(iii) the newspaper establishments are owned by bodies corporate, if one body corporate`
  line `is a subsidiary of the other body corporate, or both are subsidiaries of a common holding`
  line `company or a substantial number of their equity shares are owned by the same person or`
  line `group of persons, whether incorporated or not;`
  line
  line `(iv) one establishment is owned by a body corporate and the other is owned by a firm, if a`
  line `substantial number of partners of the firm together hold a substantial number of equity shares`
  line `of the body corporate;`
  line
  line `(v) one is owned by a body corporate and the other is owned by a firm having bodies`
  line `corporate as its partners if a substantial number of equity shares of such bodies corporate are`
  line `owned, directly or indirectly, by the same person or group of persons, whether incorporated`
  line `or not, or`
  line
  line `(b) there is functional integrality between concerned newspaper establishments.`
  line
  line `Explanation 2.--- For the purposes of this clause,---`
  line
  line `(i) different departments, branches and centres of newspaper establishments shall`
  line `be treated as parts thereof;`
  line
  line `(ii) a printing press shall be deemed to be a newspaper establishment if the`
  line `principal business thereof is to print newspaper;`
  line
  line `(zr) "notification" means a notification published in the Gazette of India or the Official Gazette of a`
  line `State, as the case may be, and the expression "notify" with its grammatical variations and cognate`
  line `expressions shall be construed accordingly;`
  line
  line `(zs) "occupier" of a factory means the person who has ultimate control over the affairs of the`
  line `factory:`
  line
  line `Provided that---`
  line
  line `(i) in the case of a firm or other association of individuals, any one of the individual partners or`
  line `members thereof;`
  line
  line `(ii) in the case of a company, any one of the directors, except any independent director within`
  line `the meaning of sub-section (6) of section 149 of the Companies Act, 2013;`
  line
  line `(iii) in the case of a factory owned or controlled by the Central Government or any State`
  line `Government, or any local authority, the person or persons appointed to manage the affairs of the`
  line `factory by the Central Government, the State Government or the local authority or such other`
  line `authority as may be prescribed by the Central Government,`
  line
  line `shall be deemed to be the occupier:`
  line
  line `Provided further that in the case of a ship which is being repaired, or on which maintenance`
  line `work is being carried out, in a dry dock which is available for hire, the owner of the dock shall be`
  line `deemed to be the occupier for all purposes except the matters as may be prescribed by the Central`
  line `Government which are directly related to the condition of ship for which the owner of ship shall be`
  line `deemed to be the occupier;`
  line
  line `(zt) "office of the mine" means an office at the surface of the mine concerned;`
  line
  line `(zu) "open cast working" means a quarry, that is to say, an excavation where any operation for the`
  line `purpose of searching for or obtaining minerals has been or is being carried on, not being a shaft or an`
  line `excavation which extends below superjacent ground;`
  line
  line `(zv) "ordinarily employed" with reference to any establishment or part thereof, means the average`
  line `number of persons employed per day in the establishment or part thereof during the preceding calendar`
  line `year obtained by dividing the number of man days worked by the number of working days excluding`
  line `rest days and other non-working days;`
  line
  line `(zw) "owner", in relation to a mine, means any person who is the immediate proprietor or lessee or`
  line `occupier of the mine or of any part thereof and in case of a mine the business whereof is being carried`
  line `on by a liquidator or receiver, such liquidator or receiver; but does not include a person who merely`
  line `receives a royalty, rent or fine from the mine, or is merely the proprietor of the mine, subject to any`
  line `lease grant or licence for the working thereof, or is merely the owner of the soil and not interested in`
  line `the minerals of the mine; but any contractor or sub-lessee for the working of a mine or any part thereof`
  line `shall be subject to this Code in like manner as if he were an owner but not so as to exempt the former`
  line `from any liability;`
  line
  line `(zx) "plantation" means---`
  line
  line `(a) any land used or intended to be used for---`
  line
  line `(i) growing tea, coffee, rubber, cinchona or cardamom which admeasures five hectares or`
  line more;
  line
  line `(ii) growing any other plant, which admeasures five hectares or more and in which persons`
  line `are employed or were employed on any day of the preceding twelve months, if, after obtaining`
  line `the approval of the Central Government, the State Government, by notification, so directs.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--- Where any piece of land used for growing any plant referred to in this subclause admeasures less than five hectares and is contiguous to any other piece of land not being`
  line `so used, but capable of being so used, and both such pieces of land are under the management of`
  line `the same employer, then, for the purposes of this sub-clause, the former piece of land shall be`
  line `deemed to be a plantation, if the total area of both such pieces of land admeasures five hectares`
  line `or more; and`
  line
  line `(b) any land which the State Government may, by notification, declare and which is used or`
  line `intended to be used for growing any plant referred to in sub-clause (a), notwithstanding that it`
  line `admeasures less than five hectares:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such declaration shall be made in respect of such land which admeasures`
  line `less than five hectares immediately before the commencement of this Code; and`
  line
  line `(c) offices, hospitals, dispensaries, schools and any other premises used for any purpose`
  line `connected with any plantation within the meaning of sub-clause (a) and sub-clause (b); but does`
  line `not include factory on the premises;`
  line
  line `(zy) "prescribed" means prescribed by rules made by the appropriate Government under this Code;`
  line
  line `(zz) "principal employer", where the contract labour is employed or engaged, means---`
  line
  line `(i) in relation to any office or Department of the Government or a local authority, the head of`
  line `that office or Department or such other officer as the Government or the local authority, may`
  line `specify in this behalf;`
  line
  line `(ii) in a factory, the owner or occupier of the factory and where a person has been named as`
  line `the manager of the factory, the person so named;`
  line
  line `(iii) in a mine, the owner or agent of the mine;`
  line
  line `(iv) in relation to any other establishment, any person responsible for the supervision and`
  line `control of the establishment;`
  line
  line `(zza) "producer", in relation to audio-visual production, means the company, firm or other person`
  line `by whom the arrangements necessary for producing such audio-visual (including the raising of`
  line `finances and engaging audio-visual workers for producing audio-visual) are undertaken.`
  line
  line `Explanation.---For the purposes of this clause, the expressions "company" and "firm" have the`
  line `same meaning as respectively assigned to them in the Companies Act, 2013 (18 of 2013) and the`
  line `Indian Partnership Act, 1932 (9 of 1932);`
  line
  line `(zzb) "qualified medical practitioner" means a medical practitioner who possesses any recognised`
  line `medical qualification as defined in clause (i) of section 2 of the Indian Medical Council Act, 1956`
  line `(102 of 1956) and who is enrolled on a Indian Medical Register as defined in clause (e) and on a State`
  line `Medical Register as defined in clause (l) of the said section;`
  line
  line `(zzc) "railway" means the railway as defined in clause (31) of section 2 of the Railways Act, 1989`
  line `(24 of 1989);`
  line
  line `(zzd) "relay" means a set of two or more persons carrying out the same kind of work during`
  line `different periods of the day and each such period is called a "shift";`
  line
  line `(zze) "sales promotion employees" means any person by whatever name called employed or`
  line `engaged in any establishment for hire or reward to do any work relating to promotion of sales or`
  line `business, or both, but does not include any such person who,---`
  line
  line `(i) being employed or engaged in a supervisory capacity, draws wages exceeding eighteen`
  line `thousand rupees per mensem or an amount as may be notified by the Central Government from`
  line `time to time; or`
  line
  line `(ii) is employed or engaged mainly in a managerial or administrative capacity.`
  line
  line `(zzf) "Schedule" means the Schedule appended to this Code;`
  line
  line `(zzg) "serious bodily injury" means any injury which involves, or in all probability will involve, the`
  line `permanent loss of any part or section of a body or the use of any part or section of a body, or the`
  line `permanent loss of or injury to the sight or hearing or any permanent physical incapacity or the fracture`
  line `of any bone or one or more joints or bones of any phalanges of hand or foot;`
  line
  line `(zzh) "standards", "regulations", "rules", "bye-laws" and "orders" respectively means standards,`
  line `regulations, rules, bye-laws and orders made or declared, as the case may be, under this Code;`
  line
  line `(zzi) "telecommunication service" means the telecommunication service as defined in clause (k) of`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 2 of the Telecom Regulatory Authority of India Act, 1997 (24 of 1997);`
  line
  line `(zzj) "wages" means all remuneration whether by way of salaries, allowances or otherwise,`
  line `expressed in terms of money or capable of being so expressed which would, if the terms of`
  line `employment, express or implied, were fulfilled, be payable to a person employed in respect of his`
  line `employment or of work done in such employment, and includes,---`
  line
  line `(i) basic pay;`
  line
  line `(ii) dearness allowance; and`
  line
  line `(iii) retaining allowance, if any,`
  line
  line `but does not include---`
  line
  line `(a) any bonus payable under any law for the time being in force, which does not form part of`
  line `the remuneration payable under the terms of employment;`
  line
  line `(b) the value of any house-accommodation, or of the supply of light, water, medical`
  line `attendance or other amenity or of any service excluded from the computation of wages by a`
  line `general or special order of the appropriate Government;`
  line
  line `(c) any contribution paid by the employer to any pension or provident fund, and the interest`
  line `which may have accrued thereon;`
  line
  line `(d) any conveyance allowance or the value of any travelling concession;`
  line
  line `(e) any sum paid to the employed person to defray special expenses entailed on him by the`
  line `nature of his employment;`
  line
  line `(f) house rent allowance;`
  line
  line `(g) remuneration payable under any award or settlement between the parties or order of a`
  line `court or Tribunal;`
  line
  line `(h) any overtime allowance;`
  line
  line `(i) any commission payable to the employee;`
  line
  line `(j) any gratuity payable on the termination of employment;`
  line
  line `(k) any retrenchment compensation or other retirement benefit payable to the employee or`
  line `any ex gratia payment made to him on the termination of employment:`
  line
  line `Provided that, for calculating the wages under this clause, if payments made by the employer`
  line `to the employee under sub-clauses (a) to (i) exceeds one-half, or such other per cent. as may be notified by the Central Government, of the all remuneration calculated under this clause, the`
  line `amount which exceeds such one-half, or the per cent. so notified, shall be deemed as`
  line `remuneration and shall be accordingly added in wages under this clause:`
  line
  line `Provided further that for the purpose of equal wages to all genders and for the purpose of`
  line `payment of wages, the emoluments specified in sub-clauses (d), (f), (g) and (h) shall be taken`
  line `for computation of wages.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--- Where an employee is given in lieu of the whole or part of the wages payable`
  line `to him, any remuneration in kind by his employer, the value of such remuneration in kind which`
  line `does not exceed fifteen per cent. of the total wages payable to him, shall be deemed to form part`
  line `of the wages of such employee;`
  line
  line `(zzk) "week" means a period of seven days beginning at midnight on Saturday night or such other`
  line `night as may be approved in writing for a particular area by the Chief Inspector-cum-Facilitator;`
  line
  line `(zzl) "worker" means any person employed in any establishment to do any manual, unskilled,`
  line `skilled, technical, operational, clerical or supervisory work for hire or reward, whether the terms of`
  line `employment be express or implied, and includes working journalists and sales promotion employees,`
  line `but does not include any such person---`
  line
  line `(i) who is subject to the Air Force Act, 1950 (45 of 1950), or the Army Act, 1950 (46 of`
  line `1950), or the Navy Act, 1957 (62 of 1957); or`
  line
  line `(ii) who is employed in the police service or as an officer or other employee of a prison; or`
  line
  line `(iii) who is employed mainly in a managerial or administrative capacity; or`
  line
  line `(iv) who is employed in a supervisory capacity drawing wage exceeding eighteen thousand`
  line `rupees per month or an amount as may be notified by the Central Government from time to`
  line time;
  line
  line `(zzm) "Working Journalist" means a person whose principal avocation is that of a journalist and`
  line `who is employed as such, either whole-time or part-time, in, or in relation to, one or more newspaper`
  line `establishment, or other establishment relating to any electronic media or digital media such as`
  line `newspaper or radio or other likemedia and includes an editor, a leader-writer, news editor, sub-editor,`
  line `feature-writer, copytester, reporter, correspondent, cartoonist, news-photographer and proof-reader,`
  line `but does not include any such person who is employed mainly in a managerial, supervisory or`
  line `administrative capacity;`
  line
  line `(2) For the purposes of this Code, a person working or employed in or in connection with mine is said`
  line `to be working or employed---`
  line
  line `(a) "below ground" if he is working or employed---`
  line
  line `(i) in a shaft which has been or is in the course being sunk; or`
  line
  line `(ii) in any excavation which extends below superjacent ground; and`
  line
  line `(b) "above ground" if he is working in an opencast working or in any other manner not specified`
  line `in clause (a).`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (101671)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Registration of certain establishments.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013&sectionId=101671&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every employer of any establishment,---`
  line
  line `(a) which comes into existence after the commencement of this Code; and`
  line
  line `(b) to which this Code shall apply,`
  line
  line `shall, within sixty days from the date of such applicability of this Code, make an application`
  line `electronically to the registering officer appointed by the appropriate Government (hereinafter referred`
  line `to as the registering officer) for the registration of such establishment:`
  line
  line `Provided that the registering officer may entertain any such application for registration after the`
  line `expiry of such period on payment of such late fees as may be prescribed by the appropriate`
  line Government.
  line
  line `(2) Every application under sub-section (1) shall be submitted to the registering officer in such`
  line `manner, in such form, containing such particulars including the information relating to the`
  line `employment of inter-State migrant workers and shall be accompanied by such fees as may be`
  line `prescribed by the appropriate Government.`
  line
  line `(3) After the receipt of an application under sub-section (1), the registering officer shall register the`
  line `establishment and issue a certificate of registration electronically to the employer thereof in such form`
  line `and within such time and subject to such conditions as may be prescribed by the Central Government:`
  line
  line `Provided that if the registering officer fails to register an establishment under the application so`
  line `made or to entertain the application within the prescribed period, then, such establishment shall be`
  line `deemed to have been registered under this Code immediately on the expiration of such period and the`
  line `electronic certificate of registration shall be auto generated and the responsibility of such failure shall`
  line `be on the registering officer.`
  line
  line `(4) Any change in the ownership or management or in any particulars referred to in sub-section (2)`
  line `which occurs after the registration of an establishment under this Code, shall be intimated by the`
  line `employer electronically to the registering officer within thirty days of such change in such form as`
  line `may be prescribed by the Central Government and thereafter the registering officer shall make`
  line `amendment in the certificate of registration electronically in such manner as may be prescribed by the`
  line `Central Government.`
  line
  line `(5) The employer of an establishment shall, within thirty days of the closing of the establishment---`
  line
  line `(a) inform the closing of such establishment; and`
  line
  line `(b) certify payment of all dues to the workers employed in such establishment,`
  line
  line `to the registering officer in such manner as may be prescribed by the Central Government and the`
  line `registering officer shall, on receiving such information and certificate remove such establishment from the`
  line `register of establishments maintained by him and cancel the registration certificate of the establishment`
  line `within sixty days from the receipt of such information :`
  line
  line `Provided that if the registering officer fails to cancel the registration certification of the`
  line `establishment under this sub-section within such sixty days, then, the registration certificate of such`
  line `establishment shall be deemed to have been cancelled under this Code immediately on the expiration`
  line `of such period of sixty days and the cancellation of registration certificate shall be auto generated and`
  line `the responsibility of such failure shall be on the registering officer.`
  line
  line `(6) If an employer of an establishment---`
  line
  line `(a) has obtained the registration of his establishment by misrepresentation or suppression of any`
  line `material fact, or`
  line
  line `(b) has obtained the registration of his establishment so fraudulently or otherwise that the`
  line `registration has become useless or ineffective to run the establishment,`
  line
  line `then, in case of clause (a) such misrepresentation or suppression of any material fact shall be deemed to`
  line `be the contravention of the provisions of this Code for prosecution of the employer under section 94`
  line `without affecting the registration and running of the establishment and in case of clause (b) the registering`
  line `officer may, after giving an opportunity to the employer of the establishment to be heard, revoke the`
  line `registration by an order and such process for revocation shall be completed by the registering officer`
  line `within sixty days from coming into his notice the facts specified in clause (b).`
  line
  line `(7) No employer of an establishment who---`
  line
  line `(a) has not registered the establishment under this section; or`
  line
  line `(b) has not preferred appeal under section 4 against the cancellation of the registration`
  line `certificate of the establishment under sub-section (5) or revocation of the registration of the`
  line `establishment under sub-section (6) or the appeal so preferred has been dismissed,`
  line
  line `shall employ any employee in the establishment.`
  line
  line `(8) Notwithstanding anything contained in this Code, where any establishment, to which this Code`
  line `applies, has already been registered under any---`
  line
  line `(a) Central Labour law; or`
  line
  line `(b) any other law which may be notified by the Central Government and which applies to the`
  line `establishment which is in existence at the time of the commencement of this Code,`
  line
  line `shall be deemed to have been registered under the provisions of this Code, subject to the condition that`
  line `the registration holder provides the details of registration to the concerned registering officer within such`
  line `time and in such form as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (101672)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title Appeal.
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013&sectionId=101672&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any person aggrieved by an order made under section 3 may, within thirty days`
  line `from the date on which the order is communicated to him, prefer an appeal to an appellate officer who`
  line `shall be a person notified in this behalf by the appropriate Government:`
  line
  line `Provided that the appellate officer may entertain the appeal after the expiry of the said period of thirty`
  line `days, if he is satisfied that the appellant was prevented by sufficient cause from filing the appeal in time.`
  line
  line `(2) On receipt of an appeal under sub-section (1), the appellate officer shall, after giving the appellant`
  line `an opportunity of being heard, dispose of the appeal within a period of thirty days from the date of receipt`
  line `of such appeal.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (101673)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Notice by employer of commencement and cessation of operation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013&sectionId=101673&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `(1) No employer of an`
  line `establishment being factory or mine or relating to contract labour or building or other construction work`
  line `shall use such establishment to commence the operation of any industry, trade, business, manufacturing or`
  line `occupation thereon without sending notice of such purpose in such form and manner and to such authority`
  line `and within such time as may be prescribed and shall also intimate the cessation thereof to the said`
  line `authority in such manner as may be prescribed by the appropriate Government.`
  line
  line `(2) The notice or intimation under sub-section (1) shall be given electronically.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (101674)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Duties of employer.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013&sectionId=101674&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every employer shall,---`
  line
  line `(a) ensure that workplace is free from hazards which cause or are likely to cause injury or`
  line `occupational disease to the employees;`
  line
  line `(b) comply with the occupational safety and health standards declared under section 18 or the`
  line `rules, regulations, bye-laws or orders made under this Code;`
  line
  line `(c) provide such annual health examination or test free of costs to such employees of such age`
  line `or such class of employees of establishments or such class of establishments, as may be prescribed`
  line `by the appropriate Government;`
  line
  line `(d) provide and maintain, as far as is reasonably practicable, a working environment that is safe`
  line `and without risk to the health of the employees;`
  line
  line `(e) ensure the disposal of hazardous and toxic waste including disposal of e-waste;`
  line
  line `(f) issue a letter of appointment to every employee on his appointment in the establishment,`
  line `with such information and in such form as may be prescribed by the appropriate Government and`
  line `where an employee has not been issued such appointment letter on or before the commencement of`
  line `this Code, he shall, within three months of such commencement, be issued such appointment letter;`
  line
  line `(g) ensure that no charge is levied on any employee, in respect of anything done or provided for`
  line `maintenance of safety and health at workplace including conduct of medical examination and`
  line `investigation for the purpose of detecting occupational diseases;`
  line
  line `(h) relating to factory, mine, dock work, building or other construction work or plantation,`
  line `ensure and be responsible for the safety and health of employees, workers and other persons who`
  line `are on the work premises of the employer, with or without his knowledge, as the case may be.`
  line
  line `(2) Without prejudice to the generality of the provisions of sub-section (1), the duties of an employer`
  line `shall particularly in respect of factory, mines, dock, building or other construction work or plantation`
  line include---
  line
  line `(a) the provision and maintenance of plant and systems of work in the workplace that are safe`
  line `and without risk to health;`
  line
  line `(b) the arrangements in the workplace for ensuring safety and absence of risk to health in`
  line `connection with the use, handling, storage and transport of articles and substances;`
  line
  line `(c) the provision of such information, instruction, training and supervision as are necessary to`
  line `ensure the health and safety of all employees at work;`
  line
  line `(d) the maintenance of all places of work in the workplace in a condition that is safe and without`
  line `risk to health and the provision and maintenance of such means of access to, and egress from, such`
  line `places as are safe and without such risk;`
  line
  line `(e) the provision, maintenance or monitoring of such working environment in the workplace for`
  line `the employees that is safe, without risk to health as regards facilities and arrangements for their`
  line `welfare at work.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (101675)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Duties and responsibilities of owner, agent and manager in relation to mine.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013&sectionId=101675&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `(1) The owner`
  line `and agent of every mine shall jointly and severally be responsible for making financial and other`
  line `provisions and for taking such other steps as may be necessary for compliance with the provisions of this`
  line `Code and the rules, regulations, bye-laws and orders made thereunder, relating to mine.`
  line
  line `(2) In the event of any contravention by any person whosoever of any of the provisions of this Code or`
  line `of the rules, regulations, bye-laws or orders made thereunder, relating to mine, except those which`
  line `specifically require any person to do any act or thing or prohibit any person from doing an act or thing,`
  line `besides the person who contravenes, then, each of the following persons shall also be deemed to be guilty`
  line `of such contravention unless he proves that he had used due diligence to secure compliance with the`
  line `provisions and had taken reasonable means to prevent such contravention, namely:---`
  line
  line `(a) the official or officials appointed to perform duties of supervision in respect of the provisions`
  line contravened;
  line
  line `(b) the manager of the mine;`
  line
  line `(c) the owner and agent of the mine;`
  line
  line `(d) the person appointed, if any, to carry out the responsibility under section 24.`
  line
  line `(3) It shall not be a defence in any proceedings brought against the owner or agent of a mine under this`
  line `section that the manager and other officials have been appointed in accordance with the provisions of this`
  line `Code or that a person to carry the responsibility under section 24 has been appointed.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (101676)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Duties of designers, manufacturers, importers or suppliers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013&sectionId=101676&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every person who designs,`
  line `manufactures, imports or supplies any article for use in any establishment shall---`
  line
  line `(a) ensure so far as is reasonably practicable, that the article is so designed and constructed in`
  line `the establishment as to be safe and without risk to the health of the workers when properly used;`
  line
  line `(b) carry out or arrange for the carrying out of such tests and examination in the establishment`
  line `as may be considered necessary for the effective implementation of the provisions of clause (a);`
  line
  line `(c) take steps as may be necessary to ensure that adequate information will be available---`
  line
  line `(i) in connection with the use of the article in any establishment;`
  line
  line `(ii) about the use for which such article is designed and tested; and`
  line
  line `(iii) about any conditions necessary to ensure that the article, when put to such use, shall be`
  line `safe, and without risk to the health of the workers:`
  line
  line `Provided that where an article is designed or manufactured outside India, then it shall be`
  line `obligatory on the part of the importer to see---`
  line
  line `(A) that the article conforms to the same standards of such article manufactured in India;`
  line or
  line
  line `(B) if the standards adopted in the country outside India for the manufacture of such`
  line `article is above the standards adopted in India, that the article conforms to such standards in`
  line `such country;`
  line
  line `(C) if there is no standard of such article in India, then, the article conforms to the`
  line `standard adopted in the country from where it is imported at its national level.`
  line
  line `(2) The designer, manufacturer, importer or supplier shall also comply with such duties as the`
  line `Central Government may, in consultation with the National Occupational Safety and Health Advisory`
  line `Board referred to in sub-section (1) of section 16, by regulations specify.`
  line
  line `(3) Every person, who undertakes to design or manufacture any article and substance for use in any`
  line `factory, may carry out or arrange for the carrying out of necessary research with a view to the`
  line `discovery and, so far as is reasonably, practicable, the elimination or minimisation of any risks to the`
  line `health or safety of the workers to which the design or manufacture of article and substance may give`
  line `rise to such risk.`
  line
  line `(4) Nothing contained in sub-sections (1) and (2) shall be construed to require a person to repeat the`
  line `testing, examination or research which has been carried out otherwise than by him or at his instance in`
  line `so far as it is reasonable for him to rely on the results thereof for the purposes of the said sub-sections.`
  line
  line `(5) Any duty imposed on any person by sub-sections (1) and (2) shall extend only to things done in`
  line `the course of business carried on by him and to matters within his control.`
  line
  line `(6) Every person,---`
  line
  line `(a) who erects or installs any article for use in a factory, shall ensure, so far as practicable, that`
  line `such article so erected or installed does not make it unsafe or a risk to health when that article is`
  line `used by the persons in such factory;`
  line
  line `(b) who manufactures, imports or supplies any substance for use in any factory shall---`
  line
  line `(i) ensure, so far as practicable, that such substance when used in the factory does not make`
  line `it unsafe or a risk to health of persons working in such factory;`
  line
  line `(ii) carry out or arrange for carrying out of such tests and examination in relation to such`
  line `substance as may be necessary;`
  line
  line `(iii) take such steps as are necessary to secure that the information about the results of tests`
  line `carried out in connection with the use of the substance as referred to in sub-clause (ii) is`
  line `available in a factory along with conditions necessary to ensure its safe use and no risks to`
  line health;
  line
  line `(c) who undertakes the manufacture of any substance for use in any factory shall carry out or`
  line `arrange for carrying out of any necessary research with a view to discover and, so far as`
  line `practicable, to ensure the elimination or minimisation of any risks to health or safety to which the`
  line `substance may give rise out of such manufacture or research;`
  line
  line `(7) For the purposes of this section, an article and substance is not to be regarded as properly used,`
  line `if they are used without regard to any information or advice relating to their use which has been made`
  line `available by the person who has designed, manufactured, imported or supplied the article and`
  line substance.
  line
  line `Explanation.--- For the purpose of this section---`
  line
  line `(a) "article" shall include plant and machinery;`
  line
  line `(b) "substance" means any natural or artificial substance whether in a solid or liquid form or`
  line `in the form of a gas or vapour; and`
  line
  line `(c) "substance for use in any factory" means such substance, whether or not intended for use`
  line `by persons working in a factory.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (101677)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Duties of architect, project engineer and designer.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013&sectionId=101677&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `(1) It shall be the duty of the architect,`
  line `project engineer or designer responsible for any building or other construction work or the design of any`
  line `project or part thereof relating to such building or other construction work to ensure that, at the planning`
  line `stage, due consideration is given to the safety and health aspects of the building workers and employees`
  line `who are employed in the erection, operation and execution of such projects and structures as the case may`
  line be.
  line
  line `(2) Adequate care shall be taken by the architect, project engineer and other professionals involved in`
  line `the project referred to in sub-section (1), not to include anything in the design which would involve the`
  line `use of dangerous structures or other processes or materials, hazardous to health or safety of building`
  line `workers and employees during the course of erection, operation and execution as the case may be.`
  line
  line `(3) It shall also be the duty of the professionals, involved in designing the buildings structures or other`
  line `construction projects, to take into account the safety aspects associated with the maintenance and upkeep`
  line `of the structures and buildings where maintenance and upkeep may involve such hazards as may be`
  line `notified by the appropriate Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (101678)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Notice of certain accident.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013&sectionId=101678&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where at any place in an establishment, an accident occurs`
  line `which causes death, or which causes any bodily injury by reason of which the person injured is prevented`
  line `from working for a period of forty-eight hours or more immediately following the accident or which is of`
  line `such nature as may be prescribed by the appropriate Government, then,---`
  line
  line `(a) employer or owner or agent or manager referred to in section 67 of such establishment if it is`
  line `mine; or`
  line
  line `(b) employer or manager in relation to such establishment if it is factory or relates to dock work; or`
  line
  line `(c) the employer of a plantation or an establishment relating to building or other construction or any`
  line `other establishment,`
  line
  line `shall send notice thereof to such authorities, in such manner and within such time, as may be prescribed`
  line `by the appropriate Government.`
  line
  line `(2) Where a notice given under sub-section (1) relates to an accident causing death in a plantation or`
  line `an establishment relating to building or other construction work or any other establishment, the authority`
  line `to whom the notice is sent shall make an inquiry into the occurrence within two months of the receipt of`
  line `the notice or if there is no such authority, the Chief Inspector-cum-Facilitator shall cause the Inspectorcum-Facilitator to make an inquiry within the said period.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (101679)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `Notice of certain dangerous occurrences.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013&sectionId=101679&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `Where in an establishment there is any dangerous`
  line `occurrence of such nature, (whether causing any bodily injury or disability, or not) the employer shall`
  line `send notice thereof to such authorities, and in such form and within such time, as may be prescribed by`
  line `the appropriate Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (101680)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title `Notice of certain diseases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013&sectionId=101680&sectionno=12&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where any worker in an establishment contracts any disease`
  line `specified in the Third Schedule, the employer of the establishment shall send notice thereof to such`
  line `authorities, and in such form and within such time, as may be prescribed by the appropriate Government.`
  line
  line `(2) If any qualified medical practitioner attends on a person, who is or has been employed in an`
  line `establishment, and who is, or is believed by the qualified medical practitioner, to be suffering from any`
  line `disease specified in the Third Schedule, the medical practitioner shall without delay send a report in`
  line `writing to the office of the Chief Inspector-cum-Facilitator in such form and manner and within such time`
  line `as may be prescribed by the appropriate Government.`
  line
  line `(3) If any qualified medical practitioner fails to comply with the provisions of sub-section (2), he shall`
  line `be punishable with penalty which may extend to ten thousand rupees.`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (101681)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 13
  title `Duties of employee.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013&sectionId=101681&sectionno=13&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `Every employee at workplace shall,---`
  line
  line `(a) take reasonable care for the health and safety of himself and of other persons who may be`
  line `affected by his acts or omissions at the workplace;`
  line
  line `(b) comply with the safety and health requirements specified in the standards;`
  line
  line `(c) co-operate with the employer in meeting the statutory obligations of the employer under this`
  line Code;
  line
  line `(d) if any situation which is unsafe or unhealthy comes to his attention, as soon as practicable,`
  line `report such situation to his employer or to the health and safety representative and in case of mine,`
  line `agent or manager referred to in section 67, safety officers or an official for his workplace or section`
  line `thereof, as the case may be, who shall report it to the employer in the manner as may be prescribed by`
  line `the appropriate Government;`
  line
  line `(e) not wilfully interfere with or misuse or neglect any appliance, convenience or other thing`
  line `provided at workplace for the purpose of securing the health, safety and welfare of workers;`
  line
  line `(f) not do, wilfully and without reasonable cause, anything, likely to endanger himself or others;`
  line and
  line
  line `(g) perform such other duties as may be prescribed by the appropriate Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (101682)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 14
  title `Rights of employee.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013&sectionId=101682&sectionno=14&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every employee in an establishment shall have the right to obtain from`
  line `the employer information relating to employee's health and safety at work and represent to the employer`
  line `directly or through a member of the Safety Committee as constituted under section 22, if constituted by`
  line `the employer for such purpose, regarding inadequate provision for protection of his safety or health in`
  line `connection with the work activity in the workplace, and if not satisfied, to the Inspector-cum-Facilitator.`
  line
  line `(2) Where the employee referred to in sub-section (1) in any workplace has reasonable apprehension`
  line `that there is a likelihood of imminent serious personal injury or death or imminent danger to health, he`
  line `may bring the same to the notice of his employer directly or through a member of the Safety Committee`
  line `referred to in sub-section (1) and simultaneously bring the same to the notice of the Inspector-cum-Facilitator.`
  line
  line `(3) The employer or any employee referred to in sub-section (1) shall take immediate remedial action`
  line `if he is satisfied about the existence of such imminent danger and send a report forthwith of the action`
  line `taken to the Inspector-cum-Facilitator in such manner as may be prescribed by the appropriate`
  line Government.
  line
  line `(4) If the employer referred to in sub-section (3) is not satisfied about the existence of any imminent`
  line `danger as apprehended by his employees, he shall, nevertheless, refer the matter forthwith to the`
  line `Inspector-cum-Facilitator whose decision on the question of the existence of such imminent danger shall`
  line `be final.`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (101683)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 15
  title `Duty not to interfere with or misuse things.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013&sectionId=101683&sectionno=15&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `No person shall intentionally or recklessly`
  line `interfere with, damage or misuse anything which is provided in the interest of health, safety or welfare`
  line `under this Code.`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (101684)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 16
  title `National Occupational Safety and Health Advisory Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013&sectionId=101684&sectionno=16&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government shall,`
  line `by notification, constitute the National Occupational Safety and Health Advisory Board (hereinafter in`
  line `this Code referred to as the National Board) to discharge the functions conferred on it by or under this`
  line `Code and to advise the Central Government on the matters relating to---`
  line
  line `(a) standards, rules and regulations to be declared or framed under this Code;`
  line
  line `(b) implementation of the provisions of this Code and the standards, rules and regulations relating`
  line thereto;
  line
  line `(c) the issues of policy and programme relating to occupational safety and health referred to it,`
  line `from time to time, by the Central Government; and`
  line
  line `(d) any other matter in respect of this Code referred to it, from time to time, by the Central`
  line Government.
  line
  line `(2) The National Board shall consist of---`
  line
  line `(a) Secretary, Ministry of Labour and Employment--- Chairperson ex officio;`
  line
  line `(b) Director General, Factory Advice Service and Labour Institutes, Mumbai--- Member ex officio;`
  line
  line `(c) Director General, Mines Safety, Dhanbad--- Member ex officio;`
  line
  line `(d) Chief Controller of Explosives, Nagpur--- Member ex officio;`
  line
  line `(e) Chairman, Central Pollution Control Board, New Delhi--- Member ex officio;`
  line
  line `(f) Chief Labour Commissioner (Central), New Delhi--- Member ex officio;`
  line
  line `(g) Principal Secretaries dealing with labour matters of four States (by rotation as the Central`
  line `Government may deem fit)--- Member ex officio;`
  line
  line `(h) Director General, Employee's State Insurance Corporation, New Delhi--- Member ex officio;`
  line
  line `(i) Director General, Health Services, New Delhi--- Member ex officio;`
  line
  line `(j) five representatives of employers--- Member ex officio;`
  line
  line `(k) five representatives of employees--- Member ex-officio;`
  line
  line `(l) a representative of professional body associated with the matter for which standards, rules,`
  line `policies being framed--- Member;`
  line
  line `(m) five eminent persons connected with the field of Occupational Safety and Health, or`
  line `representatives from reputed research institutions or similar other discipline---Member;`
  line
  line `(n) special invitees from the State Government or the Government of Union territory for seeking`
  line `inputs in specific matters or industry or sector which is predominant in that State or Union territory--- Member;`
  line
  line `(o) Joint Secretary, Ministry of Labour and Employment---Member Secretary ex officio.`
  line
  line `(3) The terms of office of the Members referred to in clauses (g), (j), (k), (l) and (m) of sub-section (2)`
  line `shall be of three years and the procedure for their nomination, and discharge of their functions shall be`
  line `such as may be prescribed by the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(4) The Central Government may, in consultation with the National Board, determine the number,`
  line `nature and categories of other officers and employees required to assist the National Board in the efficient`
  line `discharge of its functions and terms and conditions of service of such officers and employees of the`
  line `National Board shall be such as may be prescribed by the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(5) The Central Government may constitute as many technical committees or advisory committees`
  line `consisting of such number of members having such qualifications as may be prescribed by the Central`
  line `Government, to assist the National Board in discharge of its function specified in sub-section (1).`
  line
  line `(6) The National Board shall consult the State Governments whose Principal Secretaries are the`
  line `Members of the National Board as required under clause (g) of sub-section (2) of section 16 and in case`
  line `of specific issues relating to plantation, factories and like other issues, the State Government concerned`
  line `may be invited by the National Board as special invitee for obtaining their inputs on such issues.`
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (101685)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 17
  title `State Occupational Safety and Health Advisory Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013&sectionId=101685&sectionno=17&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `(1) The State Government shall`
  line `constitute a Board to be called the State Occupational Safety and Health Advisory Board (hereinafter`
  line `referred to as "State Advisory Board") to advise the State Government on such matters arising out of the`
  line `administration of this Code as may be referred to it by the State Government.`
  line
  line `(2) The constitution, procedure and other matters relating to State Advisory Board shall be such as`
  line `may be prescribed by the State Government.`
  line
  line `(3) The State Government may constitute as many technical committees or advisory committees of the`
  line `State Advisory Board including site appraisal committees, consisting of such number of members and`
  line `having such qualifications as may be prescribed, to assist the State Government or State Advisory Board`
  line `in discharge of their functions relating to the area falling within their respective jurisdictions.`
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (101686)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 18
  title `Occupational safety and health standards.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013&sectionId=101686&sectionno=18&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government shall declare, by`
  line `notification, standards on occupational safety and health for workplaces relating to factory, mine, dock`
  line `work, beedi and cigar, building and other construction work and other establishments.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular and without prejudice to the generality of the power to declare standards to be`
  line `followed under sub-section (1), such standards shall relate to---`
  line
  line `(a) physical, chemical, biological and any other hazards to be dealt with for the working life of`
  line `employee to ensure to the extent feasible on the basis of the best available evidence or functional`
  line `capacity, that no employee will suffer material impairment of health or functional capacity even if`
  line `such employee has regular exposure to such hazards;`
  line
  line `(b) the norms---`
  line
  line `(i) appraising the hazards to employees and users to whom such hazards are exposed;`
  line
  line `(ii) relating to relevant symptoms and appropriate energy treatment and proper conditions and`
  line `precautions of safe use or exposure;`
  line
  line `(iii) for monitoring and measuring exposure of employees to hazards;`
  line
  line `(iv) for medical examination and other tests which shall be made available, by the employer or`
  line `at his cost, to the employees exposed to hazards; and`
  line
  line `(v) for hazard evaluation procedures like safety audit, hazard and operability study, fault free`
  line `analysis, event free analysis and such other requirements;`
  line
  line `(c) medical examination including criteria for detection and reporting of occupational diseases to be`
  line `extended to the employees even after he ceases to be in employment, if he is suffering from an`
  line `occupational disease which arises out of or in the course of employment;`
  line
  line `(d) such aspects of occupational safety and health relating to workplaces which the Central`
  line `Government considers necessary on the report of the authority designated by such Government for`
  line `such purpose;`
  line
  line `(e) such safety and health measures as may be required having regard to the specific conditions`
  line `prevailing at the workplaces relating to mine, factory, building and other construction work, beedi and`
  line `cigar, dock work or any other establishments notified; and`
  line
  line `(f) matters specified in the Second Schedule to this Code.`
  line
  line `(3) Notwithstanding anything contained in section 131, the Central Government may, on the basis of`
  line `the recommendation of the National Board and after notifying its intention so to do for not less than fortyfive days, by notification, amend the Second Schedule.`
  line
  line `(4) The State Government may, with the prior approval of the Central Government, by notification`
  line `amend the standards made under sub-section (1) and sub-section (2) for the establishment for which it is`
  line `the appropriate Government situated in the State.`
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (101687)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 19
  title `Research related activities.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013&sectionId=101687&sectionno=19&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `It shall be the duty of such institutions in the field of occupational`
  line `safety and health as the Central or State Government may notify to conduct research, experiments and`
  line `demonstrations relating to occupational safety and health and thereafter submit their recommendations to`
  line `the Central Government or the State Government, as the case may be:`
  line
  line `Provided that the State Government shall consult National Board before notifying conduct of research,`
  line `experiments and demonstration relating to occupational safety and health.`
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (101688)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 20
  title `Safety and occupational health surveys.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013&sectionId=101688&sectionno=20&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `(1) At any time during the normal working hours of an`
  line `establishment or at any other time as he may deem necessary,---`
  line
  line `(a) the Chief Inspector-cum-Facilitator in the case of factory or mine; or`
  line
  line `(b) the Director General of Factory Advice Service and Labour Institute in the case of factory; or`
  line
  line `(c) the Director General of Mines Safety in the case of mine; or`
  line
  line `(d) the Director General of Health Services in the case of factory or mine; or`
  line
  line `(e) such other officer as may be authorised by the appropriate Government in the case of any other`
  line `establishment or class of establishments,`
  line
  line `after giving notice in writing to the employer, conduct survey of the factory or mine or such other`
  line `establishment or class of establishments and such employer shall afford all facilities for such survey,`
  line `including facilities for the examination and testing of plant and machinery and collection of samples and`
  line `other data relevant to the survey.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--- For the purposes of this sub-section, the expression “employer” includes manager for`
  line `the factory or in the case of any other establishment or class of establishments such person who is for the`
  line `time being responsible for the safety and the occupational health of such other establishment or class of`
  line `establishments, as the case may be.`
  line
  line `(2) For the purpose of facilitating surveys under sub-section (1) every worker shall, if so required by`
  line `the person conducting the survey, present himself to undergo such medical examination as may be`
  line `considered necessary by such person and furnish all information in his possession which is relevant to the`
  line survey.
  line
  line `(3) Any time spent by a worker for undergoing medical examination or furnishing information under`
  line `sub-section (2) shall, for the purpose of calculating wages and extra wages for overtime work, be deemed`
  line `to be working hour for him.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--- For the purposes of this section, the report submitted to the appropriate Government by`
  line `the person conducting the survey under sub-section (1) shall be deemed to be a report submitted by an`
  line `Inspector-cum-Facilitator under this Code.`
obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (101689)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 21
  title `Collection of statistics and portal for inter-State migrant workers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013&sectionId=101689&sectionno=21&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `(1) For the purposes of`
  line `this Code, the Central Government and the State Government shall collect compile and analyse occupational safety and health statistics in such form and manner as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) The Central Government and the State Governments shall maintain the database or record, for`
  line `inter-State migrant workers, electronically or otherwise in such portal and in such form and manner as`
  line `may be prescribed by the Central Government:`
  line
  line `Provided that an inter-State migrant worker may register himself as an inter-State migrant worker on`
  line `such portal on the basis of self-declaration and Aadhaar:`
  line
  line `Provided further that the workers who have migrated from one State to any other State and are self-employed in that other State may also register themselves on that portal.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--- For the purposes of this sub-section, the expression "Aadhaar" shall have the same`
  line `meaning as assigned to it in clause (a) of section 2 of the Aadhaar (Targeted Delivery of Financial and`
  line `Other Subsidies, Benefits and Services) Act, 2016 (18 of 2016).`
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (101690)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 22
  title `Safety Committee and safety officers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013&sectionId=101690&sectionno=22&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `(1) The appropriate Government may, by general or`
  line `special order, require any establishment or class of establishments to constitute in the prescribed manner a`
  line `Safety Committee consisting of representatives of employers and workers engaged in such establishment`
  line `in such manner that the number of representatives of workers on the Committee shall not be less than the`
  line `number of representatives of the employer and the representatives of the workers shall be chosen in such`
  line `manner and for such purpose as may be prescribed by the appropriate Government.`
  line
  line `(2) In every establishment which is a---`
  line
  line `(a) factory wherein five hundred workers or more; or`
  line
  line `(b) factory carrying on hazardous process wherein two hundred fifty workers or more; or`
  line
  line `(c) building or other construction work wherein two hundred fifty workers or more; or`
  line
  line `(d) mine wherein one hundred workers or more, are ordinarily employed,`
  line
  line `the employer shall also appoint such number of safety officers, who shall possess such qualifications and`
  line `perform such duties, as may be prescribed by appropriate Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (101691)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 23
  title `Responsibility of employer for maintaining health, safety and working conditions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013&sectionId=101691&sectionno=23&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `(1) The`
  line `employer shall be responsible to maintain in his establishment such health, safety and working conditions`
  line `for the employees as may be prescribed by the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(2) Without prejudice to the generality of the power conferred under sub-section (1), the Central`
  line `Government may prescribe for providing all or any of the following matters in the establishment or class`
  line `of establishments, namely:---`
  line
  line `(i) cleanliness and hygiene;`
  line
  line `(ii) ventilation, temperature and humidity;`
  line
  line `(iii) environment free from dust, noxious gas, fumes and other impurities;`
  line
  line `(iv) adequate standard of humidification, artificially increasing the humidity of the air, ventilation`
  line `and cooling of the air in work rooms;`
  line
  line `(v) potable drinking water;`
  line
  line `(vi) adequate standards to prevent overcrowding and to provide sufficient space to employees or`
  line `other persons, as the case may be, employed therein;`
  line
  line `(vii) adequate lighting;`
  line
  line `(viii) sufficient arrangement for latrine and urinal accommodation to male, female and transgender`
  line `employee separately and maintaining hygiene therein;`
  line
  line `(ix) effective arrangements for treatment of wastes and effluents; and`
  line
  line `(x) any other arrangement which the Central Government considers appropriate.`
obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (101692)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 24
  title `Welfare facilities in the establishment, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013&sectionId=101692&sectionno=24&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `(1) The employer shall be responsible to provide`
  line `and maintain in his establishment such welfare facilities for the employees as may be prescribed by the`
  line `Central Government, including,---`
  line
  line `(i) adequate and suitable facilities for washing to male and female employees separately;`
  line
  line `(ii) bathing places and locker rooms for male, female and transgender employees separately;`
  line
  line `(iii) place of keeping clothing not worn during working hours and for the drying of wet clothing;`
  line
  line `(iv) sitting arrangements for all employees obliged to work in a standing position;`
  line
  line `(v) facilities of canteen in an establishment for employees thereof, wherein one hundred or more`
  line `workers including contract labourers are ordinarily employed;`
  line
  line `(vi) in case of mines, medical examination of the employees employed or to be employed in the`
  line `mines, before their employment and at specific intervals;`
  line
  line `(vii) adequate first-aid boxes or cupboards with contents readily accessible during all working`
  line `hours; and`
  line
  line `(viii) any other welfare measures which the Central Government considers, under the set of`
  line `circumstances, as required for decent standard of life of the employees.`
  line
  line `(2) Without prejudice to the generality of the powers referred to under sub-section (1), the Central`
  line `Government may also prescribe for the following matters, namely:---`
  line
  line `(i) ambulance room in every factory, mine, building or other construction work wherein more than`
  line `five hundred workers are ordinarily employed;`
  line
  line `(ii) medical facilities at the operating centres and halting stations, uniforms, raincoats and other like`
  line `amenities for protection from rain or cold for motor transport workers;`
  line
  line `(iii) adequate, suitable and separate shelters or rest-rooms for male, female and transgender`
  line `employees and lunch-room in every factory and mine wherein more than fifty workers are ordinarily`
  line `employed and in motor transport undertaking wherein employee is required to halt at night;`
  line
  line `(iv) the appointment of welfare officer in every factory, mine or plantation wherein two hundred`
  line `and fifty or more workers are ordinarily employed and the qualification, conditions of service and`
  line `duties of such welfare officer;`
  line
  line `(v) for providing by the employer temporary living accommodation, free of charges and within the`
  line `work site or as near to it as may be possible, to all building workers employed by him and for causing`
  line `removal or demolition of such temporary living accommodation and for returning by the employer the`
  line `possession of any land obtained by him for such purpose from Municipal Board or any other local`
  line authority;
  line
  line `(vi) for payment by the principal employer the expenses incurred on providing the accommodation`
  line `to the contractor, where the building or other construction work is done through the contractor;`
  line
  line `(vii) any other matter which may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) The Central Government may make rules to provide for the facility of creche having suitable room`
  line `or rooms for the use of children under the age of six years of the employees at suitable location and`
  line `distance either separately or along with common facilities in establishments wherein more than fifty`
  line `workers are ordinarily employed:`
  line
  line `Provided that an establishment can avail common crèche facility of the Central Government, State`
  line `Government, municipality or private entity or provided by non-Governmental organisation or by any`
  line `other organisation or group of establishments may pool their resources for setting up of common crèche in`
  line `the manner as they may agree for such purpose.`
obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (101693)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 25
  title `Daily and weekly working hours, leave, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013&sectionId=101693&sectionno=25&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line `(1) No worker shall be required or allowed to`
  line `work, in any establishment or class of establishment for more than---`
  line
  line `(a) eight hours in a day; and`
  line
  line `(b) the period of work in each day under clause (a) shall be so fixed, as not to exceed such hours,`
  line `with such intervals and spread overs , as may be notified by the appropriate Government:`
  line
  line `Provided that subject to clause (a) in the case of mines,---`
  line
  line `(i) the persons employed below ground in a mine shall not be allowed to work for more than`
  line `such hours as may be notified by the Central Government in any day;`
  line
  line `(ii) no work shall be carried on below ground in any mine except by a system of shifts so`
  line `arranged that the period of work for each shift is not spread over more than the daily maximum`
  line `hours as notified under clause (i);`
  line
  line `(iii) no person employed in a mine shall be allowed to be present in any part of a mine below`
  line `ground except during the periods of work shown in respect of him in the register maintained under`
  line `clause (a) of section 33:`
  line
  line `Provided further that subject to clause (a) that the hours of work in case of motor transport worker`
  line `shall include---`
  line
  line `(i) the time spent in work done during the running time of the transport vehicle;`
  line
  line `(ii) the time spent in subsidiary work; and`
  line
  line `(iii) period of mere attendance at terminals of less than fifteen minutes.`
  line
  line `Explanation.---For the purposes of this sub-section---`
  line
  line `(a) "running time" in relation to a working day means the time from the moment a transport`
  line `vehicle starts functioning at the beginning of the working day until the moment when the transport`
  line `vehicle ceases to function at the end of the working day, excluding any time during which the`
  line `running of the transport vehicle is interrupted for a period exceeding such duration as may be`
  line `prescribed by the Central Government during which period the persons who drive, or perform any`
  line `other work in connection with the transport vehicle are free to dispose of their time as they please`
  line `or are engaged in subsidiary work;`
  line
  line `(b) "subsidiary work" means the work in connection with a transport vehicle, its passengers or`
  line `its load which is done outside the running time of the transport vehicle, including in particular---`
  line
  line `(i) the work in connection with accounts, paying of cash, signing of registers, handover of`
  line `service sheets, the checking of tickets and other similar work;`
  line
  line `(ii) taking over and garaging of the transport vehicles;`
  line
  line `(iii) travelling from the place where a person signs on to the place where he takes over the`
  line `transport vehicle and from the place where he leaves the transport vehicle to the place where he`
  line `signs off;`
  line
  line `(iv) work in connection with the upkeep and repair of the transport vehicle; and`
  line
  line `(v) the loading and unloading of the transport vehicle;`
  line
  line `(c) "period of mere attendance" means the period during which a person remains at his post`
  line `solely in order to reply to possible calls or to resume action at the time fixed in the duty schedule.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), the hours of work for working journalist`
  line `shall, subject to a maximum of one hundred and forty-four hours of work during any period of four`
  line `consecutive weeks and a period of not less than twenty-four consecutive hours of rest during any`
  line `period of seven consecutive days, be such as may be prescribed by the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(3) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-sections (1) and (2), a sales promotion employee or`
  line `the working journalist,---`
  line
  line `(i) in addition to such holidays, casual leave or other kinds of leave as may be prescribed by the`
  line `Central Government, shall be granted, if requested for---`
  line
  line `(a) earned leave on full wages for not less than one-eleventh of the period spent on duty;`
  line
  line `(b) leave on medical certificate on one-half of the wages for not less than one-eighteenth of`
  line `the period of service;`
  line
  line `(ii) may accumulate earned leave up to such maximum limit as may be prescribed by the Central`
  line Government;
  line
  line `(iii) shall be entitled for the limit up to which the earned leave may be either encashed or availed`
  line `of at a time by him and the reasons for which such limit may be exceeded shall be such as may be`
  line `prescribed by the Central Government;`
  line
  line `(iv) shall,---`
  line
  line `(a) when he voluntarily relinquishes his post or retires from service; or`
  line
  line `(b) when his services are terminated for any reason whatsoever (not being termination as`
  line `punishment),`
  line
  line `be entitled to cash compensation, subject to such conditions and restrictions as may be prescribed by the`
  line `Central Government (including conditions by way of specifying the maximum period for which such cash`
  line `compensation shall be payable), in respect of the earned leave earned by him and not availed of;`
  line
  line `(v) who dies while in service, his heirs shall be entitled to cash compensation for the earned`
  line `leave earned by him and not availed of his heirs shall be paid the cash compensation in respect of`
  line `any period of earned leave for which he or his heirs, is or are entitled to cash compensation under`
  line `clause (iv) or clause (v), which shall be an amount equal to the wages due to him for such period.`
  line
  line `(4) Notwithstanding anything contained in this section, the working hours of an adolescent worker`
  line `shall be regulated in accordance with the provisions of the Child and Adolescent Labour (Prohibition`
  line `and Regulation) Act, 1986 (61 of 1986).`
obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_26:
  sectionId (101694)
  sectionNo (26)
  orderNo 26
  title `Weekly and compensatory holidays.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013&sectionId=101694&sectionno=26&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013
obj_root_law_sections_26_content:
  string
  line `(1) No worker shall be allowed to work in an`
  line `establishment for more than six days in any one week:`
  line
  line `Provided that in any motor transport undertaking, an employer may, in order to prevent any dislocation`
  line `of a motor transport service, require a worker to work on any day of weekly holiday which is not a`
  line `holiday so arranged that the worker does not work for more than ten days consecutively without a holiday`
  line `for a whole day intervening.`
  line
  line `(2) The appropriate Government may, by notification, exempt such workers as it thinks fit from the`
  line `provisions of sub-section (1), subject to such conditions as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) Where, as a result of the passing of an order or the making of a rule under the provisions of this`
  line `Code exempting an establishment or the workers therein from the provisions of sub-section (1), a worker`
  line `is deprived of any of the weekly holidays, the worker shall be allowed, within the month in which the`
  line `holidays were due or within the two months immediately following that month, compensatory holidays of`
  line `equal number to the holidays, so deprived.`
obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_27:
  sectionId (101695)
  sectionNo (27)
  orderNo 27
  title `Extra wages for overtime.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013&sectionId=101695&sectionno=27&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013
obj_root_law_sections_27_content:
  string
  line `There shall be paid wages at the rate of twice the rate of wages in`
  line `respect of overtime work, where a worker works in an establishment or class of establishment for more`
  line `than such hours of work in any day or in any week as may be prescribed by the appropriate Government`
  line `and the period of overtime work shall be calculated on a daily basis or weekly basis, whichever is more`
  line `favourable to such worker:`
  line
  line `Provided that a worker shall be required to work overtime by the employer subject to the consent of`
  line `such worker for such work:`
  line
  line `Provided further that the appropriate Government may prescribe the total number of hours of overtime.`
obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_28:
  sectionId (101696)
  sectionNo (28)
  orderNo 28
  title `Night shifts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013&sectionId=101696&sectionno=28&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013
obj_root_law_sections_28_content:
  string
  line `Where a worker in an establishment works on a shift which extends beyond`
  line midnight,---
  line
  line `(a) for the purposes of section 26, a weekly holiday for a whole day shall mean in his case a period`
  line `of twenty-four consecutive hours beginning when his shift ends;`
  line
  line `(b) the following day for him shall be deemed to be the period of twenty-four hours beginning`
  line `when such shift ends, and the hours he has worked after midnight shall be counted in the previous day.`
obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_29:
  sectionId (101697)
  sectionNo (29)
  orderNo 29
  title `Prohibition of overlapping shifts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_29_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013&sectionId=101697&sectionno=29&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013
obj_root_law_sections_29_content:
  string
  line `(1) The work shall not be carried on in any establishment by`
  line `means of a system of shifts so arranged that more than one relay of workers is engaged in work of the`
  line `same kind at the same time.`
  line
  line `(2) The appropriate Government or subject to the approval of the appropriate Government, the Chief`
  line `Inspector-cum-Facilitator, may, by written order and for the reasons specified therein, exempt on such`
  line `conditions as may be deemed expedient, any establishment or class of establishments or any department`
  line `or section of an establishment or any category or description of workers therein from the provisions of`
  line `sub-section (1):`
  line
  line `Provided that the provisions of this sub-section shall not apply to mines.`
obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_30:
  sectionId (101698)
  sectionNo (30)
  orderNo 30
  title `Restriction on double employment in factory and mine.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_30_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013&sectionId=101698&sectionno=30&orderno=30&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013
obj_root_law_sections_30_content:
  string
  line `No worker shall be required or`
  line `allowed to work in a mine or factory if he has already been working in any other such similar`
  line `establishment within the preceding twelve hours, save in such circumstances as may be prescribed by the`
  line `appropriate Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_31:
  sectionId (101699)
  sectionNo (31)
  orderNo 31
  title `Notice of periods of work.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_31_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013&sectionId=101699&sectionno=31&orderno=31&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013
obj_root_law_sections_31_content:
  string
  line `(1) There shall be displayed and correctly maintained in every`
  line `establishment a notice of periods of work, showing clearly for every day the periods during which`
  line `workers may be required to work in accordance with the provisions of this Code.`
  line
  line `(2) The form of notice required by sub-section (1), the manner of display of such notice and the`
  line `manner in which such notice shall be sent to the Inspector-cum-Facilitator shall be such as may be`
  line `prescribed by the appropriate Government.`
  line
  line `(3) Any proposed change in the system of work in any establishment which will necessitate a change`
  line `in the notice referred to in sub-section (1) shall be intimated to the Inspector-cum-Facilitator before the`
  line `change is made, and except with the previous sanction of the Inspector-cum-Facilitator, no such change`
  line `shall be made until one week has elapsed since that last change.`
obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_32:
  sectionId (101700)
  sectionNo (32)
  orderNo 32
  title `Annual leave with wages, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_32_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013&sectionId=101700&sectionno=32&orderno=32&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013
obj_root_law_sections_32_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every worker employed in an establishment shall be entitled`
  line `for leave in a calendar year with wages subject to the following conditions, namely:---`
  line
  line `(i) that he has worked one hundred and eighty days or more in such calendar year;`
  line
  line `(ii) that he shall be entitled for one-day leave for every twenty days of his work, in the case of`
  line `adolescent worker for fifteen days of his work, and in case of worker employed below ground mine, at`
  line `the rate of one day for every fifteen days of his work, in such calendar year;`
  line
  line `(iii) any period of layoff, maternity leave or annual leave availed by such worker in such calendar`
  line `year shall be counted for calculating the period of one hundred and eighty days or more under`
  line `clause (i), but he shall not earn leave for the period so counted;`
  line
  line `(iv) any holidays falling between the leave availed by such worker (in a calendar year or prefixed or`
  line `suffixed holiday) shall be excluded from the period of leave so availed;`
  line
  line `(v) in case of such worker whose service commences otherwise than on the first day of January`
  line `shall be entitled to leave with wages at the rate specified in clause (ii), if he has worked for one-fourth`
  line `of the total number of days in the remainder of the calendar year;`
  line
  line `(vi) in case such worker is discharged or dismissed from service or quits employment or is`
  line `superannuated or dies while in service, during the course of the calendar year, such worker or his heir`
  line `or nominee, shall be entitled to wages in lieu of the quantum of leave to which such worker was`
  line `entitled immediately before his discharge, dismissal, quitting of employment, superannuation or death,`
  line `calculated as specified in preceding clauses, even if such worker has not worked for the required`
  line `period under this sub-section making such worker eligible to avail such leave, and such payment shall`
  line `be made---`
  line
  line `(a) where such worker is discharged or dismissed or quits employment before the expiry of the`
  line `second working day from the date of such discharge, dismissal or quitting; and`
  line
  line `(b) where such worker is superannuated or dies while in service, before the expiry of two`
  line `months from the date of such superannuation or death;`
  line
  line `(vii) if such worker does not in any one calendar year take the whole of the leave allowed to him`
  line `under this sub-section and the rules made thereunder, then, any leave not taken by him shall be added`
  line `to the leave to be allowed to him in the succeeding calendar year so that---`
  line
  line `(a) the total number of days of leave that may be carried forward to a succeeding year shall not`
  line `exceed thirty days; and`
  line
  line `(b) such worker, who has applied for leave with wages but has not been given such leave in`
  line `accordance with this sub-section and the rules made thereunder shall be entitled to carry forward`
  line `the leave refused without any limit;`
  line
  line `(viii) without prejudice to clause (vi) such worker shall be entitled on his demand for encashment of`
  line `leave at the end of calendar year;`
  line
  line `(ix) such worker shall be entitled, where his total number of leave exceeds thirty days under`
  line `sub-clause (a) of clause (vii), to encash such exceeded leave.`
  line
  line `(2) The appropriate Government may, by notification, extend the provisions of sub-section (1) to any`
  line `other establishment except railway establishment.`
  line
  line `(3) The provisions of sub-section (1) shall not operate to the prejudice of any right to which a person`
  line `employed in a mine may be entitled under any other law or under the terms of any award, agreement or`
  line `contract of service:`
  line
  line `Provided that if such award, agreement or contract of service, provides for longer annual leave with`
  line `wages than that provided in sub-section (1), the quantum of leave, which the person employed shall be`
  line `entitled to, shall be in accordance with such award, agreement or contract of service but leave shall be`
  line `regulated in accordance with the provisions of sub-section (1) with respect of matters not provided for in`
  line `such award, agreement or contract of service:`
  line
  line `Provided further that where the Central Government is satisfied that the leave rules applicable to`
  line `persons employed in any mine provide benefits which in its opinion are not less favourable than those`
  line `provided for in sub-section (1) it may, by order in writing and subject to such conditions as may be`
  line `specified therein exempt the mine from all or any of the provisions of sub-section (1).`
obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_33:
  sectionId (101701)
  sectionNo (33)
  orderNo 33
  title `Maintenance of registers, records and filing of returns.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_33_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013&sectionId=101701&sectionno=33&orderno=33&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013
obj_root_law_sections_33_content:
  string
  line `An employer of an establishment`
  line shall---
  line
  line `(a) maintain register in prescribed form, electronically or otherwise, containing such particulars`
  line `of workers as may be prescribed by the appropriate Government including,---`
  line
  line `(i) work performed by them;`
  line
  line `(ii) number of hours of work constituting normal working hours in a day;`
  line
  line `(iii) day of rest allowed in every period of seven days;`
  line
  line `(iv) wage paid and receipts given therefor;`
  line
  line `(v) leave, leave wages, overtime work, attendance and dangerous occurrences; and`
  line
  line `(vi) employment of adolescent;`
  line
  line `(b) display notices at the work place of the workers in such manner and form as may be`
  line `prescribed by the appropriate Government;`
  line
  line `(c) issue wage slips to the workers, in electronic forms or otherwise; and`
  line
  line `(d) file such return electronically or otherwise to the Inspector-cum-Facilitator in such manner`
  line `and during such periods as may be prescribed by the appropriate Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_34:
  sectionId (101702)
  sectionNo (34)
  orderNo 34
  title `Appointment of Inspector-cum-Facilitators.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_34_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013&sectionId=101702&sectionno=34&orderno=34&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013
obj_root_law_sections_34_content:
  string
  line `(1) The appropriate Government may, by`
  line `notification, appoint Inspector-cum-Facilitators for the purposes of this Code who shall exercise the`
  line `powers conferred on them under this Code throughout their respective jurisdiction specified in the`
  line notification.
  line
  line `(2) The Inspector-cum-Facilitators appointed under sub-section (1) shall, apart from other duties to be`
  line `discharged by them under this Code, conduct such inspections as specified in sub-section (3).`
  line
  line `(3) The appropriate Government may---`
  line
  line `(i) for the purposes of inspection referred to in sub-section (2), by notification, lay down an`
  line `inspection scheme which may provide for the generation of web-based inspection and calling of`
  line `information under this Code, electronically and such scheme shall, inter alia, have provisions to`
  line `cater to special circumstances for assigning inspection and calling for information from`
  line `establishment or any other person besides web-based inspections; and`
  line
  line `(ii) without prejudice to the provisions of sub-section (2), by notification, under the scheme,`
  line `provide for the randomised selection of establishment and the Inspector-cum-Facilitator for`
  line inspection.
  line
  line `(4) Without prejudice to the powers of the appropriate Government under this section, the inspection`
  line `scheme referred to in sub-section (3) may be designed taking into account, inter alia, the following`
  line `factors, namely:---`
  line
  line `(a) assignment of unique number, to each establishment (which will be same as the registration`
  line `number allotted to the establishment registered under section 3), unique number to each Inspector-cum-Facilitator and to each inspection in such manner as may be notified by the appropriate`
  line Government;
  line
  line `(b) timely uploading of inspection reports in such manner and subject to such conditions as may be`
  line `notified in the scheme;`
  line
  line `(c) provisions for special inspections based on such parameters as may be notified by the`
  line `appropriate Government; and`
  line
  line `(d) the characteristics of employment, the nature of work, and characteristics of the workplaces`
  line `based on such parameters as may be notified by the appropriate Government.`
  line
  line `(5) The appropriate Government may, by notification, appoint any person or persons possessing the`
  line `prescribed qualifications and experience to be Chief Inspector-cum-Facilitator for the purposes of such`
  line `establishments or class of establishments and for such local limits of jurisdiction as may be specified in`
  line `the notification: Provided that a Chief Inspector-cum-Facilitator may be appointed for the purposes of a`
  line `State or more than one States or for the purposes of the whole of the Country.`
  line
  line `(6) The appropriate Government may, by notification, appoint for the purposes of establishments as`
  line `may be notified by that Government, as many Additional Chief Inspector-cum-Facilitators, Joint Chief`
  line `Inspector-cum-Facilitators and Deputy Chief Inspector-cum-Facilitators or any other officer of any`
  line `designation as it thinks appropriate, to exercise such powers of the Chief Inspector-cum-Facilitator within`
  line `his jurisdiction, as may be specified in the notification.`
  line
  line `(7) Every Additional Chief Inspector-cum-Facilitator, Joint Chief Inspector-cum-Facilitator, Deputy`
  line `Chief Inspector-cum-Facilitator and every other officer appointed under sub-section (6) shall, in addition`
  line `to the powers of a Chief Inspector-cum-Facilitator specified in the notification by which the officer is`
  line `appointed, exercise the powers of an Inspector-cum-Facilitator within such local limits as may be`
  line `specified in the notification.`
  line
  line `(8) No person shall be appointed under this section or having been so appointed, shall continue to hold`
  line `office, who is, or who becomes, directly or indirectly interested in a workplace or work activity or in any`
  line `process or business carried on in any workplace or in any plant or machinery connected therewith.`
  line
  line `(9) The appropriate Government may also, by notification, appoint such public officers as it thinks fit`
  line `to be Inspector-cum-Facilitators in addition to existing Inspector-cum-Facilitator for exercising the`
  line `powers and discharging the duties of Inspector-cum-Facilitator for all or any of the purposes of this Code`
  line `within such local limits as may be specified in such notification.`
  line
  line `(10) Without prejudice to the other functions of the Inspector-cum-Facilitator under this Code, an`
  line `Inspector-cum-Facilitator may in respect of any establishment or class of establishments in local area or`
  line `areas of his jurisdiction where the Chief Inspector-cum-Facilitator with the approval of the appropriate`
  line `Government and subject to such restrictions or conditions as he may think fit to impose, by order in`
  line `writing authorise the Inspector-cum-Facilitator to exercise such of the powers of the Chief Inspector-cum-Facilitator as may be specified in such order:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Chief Inspector-cum-Facilitator, with the approval of the appropriate Government,`
  line `may by order in writing, prohibit the exercise, by any Inspector-cum- Facilitator or any class of Inspector-cum-Facilitators specified in such order, of any such power by such Inspector-cum-Facilitator or class of`
  line Inspector-cum-Facilitators.
  line
  line `(11) Every Chief Inspector-cum-Facilitator, Additional Chief Inspector-cum-Facilitator, Joint Chief`
  line `Inspector-cum-Facilitator, Deputy Chief Inspector-cum-Facilitator, Inspector-cum-Facilitator and every`
  line `other officer appointed under this section shall be deemed to be a public servant within the meaning of`
  line `section 21 of the Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860), and shall be officially subordinate to such authority as`
  line `the appropriate Government may specify in this behalf.`
obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_35:
  sectionId (101703)
  sectionNo (35)
  orderNo 35
  title `Powers of Inspector-cum-Facilitators.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_35_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013&sectionId=101703&sectionno=35&orderno=35&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013
obj_root_law_sections_35_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to any rules made in this behalf, an`
  line `Inspector-cum-Facilitator may---`
  line
  line `(i) enter, with such assistance of persons, being persons in the service of the Government, or any`
  line `local or other public authority, or with an expert, as he thinks fit, any place which is used, or which he`
  line `has reason to believe, is used as a work place;`
  line
  line `(ii) inspect and examine the establishment, any premises, plant, machinery, article, or any other`
  line `relevant material;`
  line
  line `(iii) inquire into any accident or dangerous occurrence, whether resulting in bodily injury, disability`
  line `or death or not and take on the spot or otherwise statement of any person which he may consider`
  line `necessary for such inquiry;`
  line
  line `(iv) subject to any rules made by the State Government in this behalf, within his jurisdiction,`
  line `examine the crops grown in any plantation or any worker employed therein or require the production`
  line `of any register or other document maintained in pursuance of this Code, and take on the spot or`
  line `otherwise statement of any person which he may consider necessary for carrying out the purposes of`
  line `this Code relating to plantation;`
  line
  line `(v) supply information and sensitise the employers and workers regarding the provisions of this`
  line `Code and compliance thereof;`
  line
  line `(vi) require the production of any register or any other document relating to the workplace or work`
  line activity;
  line
  line `(vii) search or seize, or take copies of, any register, record or other document or any portion`
  line `thereof, as he may consider necessary in respect of any offence under this Code, which he has reason`
  line `to believe, has been committed;`
  line
  line `(viii) direct the concerned occupier or employer that any premises or any part thereof, or anything`
  line `lying therein, shall be left undisturbed (whether generally or in particular respects) for so long as is`
  line `necessary for the purpose of any inspection or inquiry;`
  line
  line `(ix) take measurements, photographs and videographs and make such recordings as he considers`
  line `necessary for the purpose of any examination or inquiry;`
  line
  line `(x) take samples of any articles or substances found in any establishment or premises into which he`
  line `has power to enter and of the air of the atmosphere in or in the vicinity of any such establishment or`
  line `premises in such manner as may be prescribed by the appropriate Government;`
  line
  line `(xi) in case of any article or substance found in any establishment or premises, being an article or`
  line `substance which appears to him as having caused or is likely to cause danger to the health and safety`
  line `of the employees, direct it to be dismantled or subject it to any process or test (but not so as to damage`
  line `or destroy it unless the same is, in the circumstances necessary, for carrying out the purposes of any`
  line `provision of this Code) and take possession of any such article or substance or a part thereof, and`
  line `detain it for so long as is necessary for such examination;`
  line
  line `(xii) issue show cause notice relating to safety, health and welfare provisions arising under this`
  line `Code, rules, regulations and bye-laws made thereunder;`
  line
  line `(xiii) prosecute, conduct or defend before any court any complaint or other proceeding arising`
  line `under this Code, the rules and regulations made thereunder; and`
  line
  line `(xiv) exercise such other powers and perform such other duties as may be prescribed by the`
  line `appropriate Government.`
  line
  line `(2) Any person required to produce any document or to give any information required by an Inspector-cum-Facilitator under sub-section (1) shall be deemed to be legally bound to do so within the meaning of`
  line `section 175 and section 176 of the Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860).`
  line
  line `(3) The provisions of the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974), shall, so far as may be, apply`
  line `to such search or seizure under sub-section (1) as they apply to any search or seizure made under the`
  line `authority of a warrant issued under section 94 of the said Code.`
obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_36:
  sectionId (101704)
  sectionNo (36)
  orderNo 36
  title `Powers and duties of District Magistrate.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_36_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013&sectionId=101704&sectionno=36&orderno=36&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013
obj_root_law_sections_36_content:
  string
  line `The District Magistrate shall, within the local limits`
  line `of his jurisdiction, exercise such powers and duties of the Inspector-cum-Facilitator in respect of mines as`
  line `may be prescribed by the Central Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_37:
  sectionId (101705)
  sectionNo (37)
  orderNo 37
  title `Third party audit and certification.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_37_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013&sectionId=101705&sectionno=37&orderno=37&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013
obj_root_law_sections_37_content:
  string
  line `(1) The appropriate Government may, by notification,`
  line `formulate a scheme to empanel experts possessing such qualifications and experience as may be`
  line `prescribed for the purpose of such start-up establishments or class of establishments, as may be specified`
  line `in the notification.`
  line
  line `(2) The experts empanelled under sub-section (1), shall,---`
  line
  line `(a) be assigned the third party audit and certification in a randomised manner, by the appropriate`
  line `Government through a web-based scheme;`
  line
  line `(b) carry out the audit and certification in the manner and for the purpose specified in the scheme`
  line `referred to in sub-section (1);`
  line
  line `(c) perform such duties as may be specified in such scheme and submit his report to the concerned`
  line `employer and to the Inspector-cum-Facilitator.`
obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_38:
  sectionId (102027)
  sectionNo (38)
  orderNo 38
  title `Special powers of Inspector-cum-Facilitator in respect of factory, mines, dock work and building or other construction work.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_38_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013&sectionId=102027&sectionno=38&orderno=38&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013
obj_root_law_sections_38_content:
  string
  line `(1) Without prejudice to the other powers of an Inspector-cum-Facilitator in this Code, an Inspector-cum-Facilitator,---`
  line
  line `(A) shall have the following special powers in respect of a factory, namely:---`
  line
  line `(a) where it appears to the Inspector-cum-Facilitator that conditions in a factory or part`
  line `thereof are such that they may cause serious hazard or imminent danger by way of injury or`
  line `death to the persons employed therein or to the general public in the vicinity, he may, by order`
  line `in writing to the occupier of the factory, state the particulars in respect of which he considers the`
  line `factory or part thereof to be the cause of such serious hazard or imminent danger and prohibit`
  line `such occupier from employing any person in the factory or any part thereof other than the`
  line `minimum number of persons necessary to attend to the minimum tasks till the hazard or danger`
  line `is removed;`
  line
  line `(b) any order issued by the Inspector-cum-Facilitator under sub-clause (a) shall have effect`
  line `for a period of three days until extended by the Chief Inspector-cum-Facilitator by a subsequent`
  line order;
  line
  line `(c) any person aggrieved by an order of the Inspector-cum-Facilitator under sub-clause (a),`
  line `and the Chief Inspector-cum-Facilitator under sub-clause (b), shall have the right to appeal to`
  line `the High Court;`
  line
  line `(d) any person whose employment has been affected by an order issued under sub-clause (a),`
  line `shall, without prejudice to the rights of the parties under the Industrial Disputes Act, 1947 (14 of`
  line `1947), be entitled to wages and other benefits and it shall be the duty of the occupier to provide`
  line `alternative employment to him wherever possible in such manner as may be prescribed by the`
  line `appropriate Government;`
  line
  line `(B) shall have the following special powers in respect of mines, namely:---`
  line
  line `(a) if, in respect of any matter for which no express provision is made by or under this`
  line `Code, it appears to the Chief Inspector-cum-Facilitator or an Inspector-cum-Facilitator that`
  line `any mine or part thereof or any matter, thing or practice in or connected with the mine, or`
  line `with the control, supervision, management or direction thereof, is dangerous to human life or`
  line `safety or is defective so as to threaten or tend to cause, the bodily injury of any person, he`
  line `may give notice in writing thereof to the employer of the mine stating therein the particulars`
  line `in respect of which he considers the mine or part thereof or the matter, thing or practice to be`
  line `dangerous or defective and require the same to be remedied within such time and in such`
  line `manner as he may specify in the notice;`
  line
  line `(b) where the employer of a mine fails to comply with the terms of a notice given under`
  line `sub-clause (a) within the period specified therein, the Chief Inspector-cum-Facilitator or the`
  line 38
  line `Inspector-cum-Facilitator may, by order in writing, prohibit the employment in or about the`
  line `mine or any part thereof of any person whose employment is not in his opinion reasonably`
  line `necessary for securing compliance with the terms of the notice;`
  line
  line `(c) without prejudice to the provisions contained in sub-clause (a), the Chief Inspector-cum-Facilitator or the Inspector-cum-Facilitator may, by order in writing addressed to the`
  line `employer of a mine, prohibit the extraction or reduction of pillars or blocks of minerals in the`
  line `mine or part thereof, if, in his opinion, such operation is likely to cause the crushing of pillars`
  line `or blocks of minerals or the premature collapse of any part of the workings or otherwise`
  line `endanger the mine or the life or safety of persons employed therein or if, in his opinion,`
  line `adequate provision against the outbreak of fire or flooding has not been made by providing`
  line `for the sealing off and isolation of the part of the mine in which such operation is`
  line `contemplated and for restricting the area that might be affected by fire or flooding;`
  line
  line `(d) if the Chief Inspector-cum-Facilitator or an Inspector-cum-Facilitator authorised, by`
  line `general or special order in writing by the Chief Inspector-cum-Facilitator, is of opinion that`
  line `there is urgent and immediate danger to the life or safety of any person employed in any`
  line `mine or part thereof, he may, by order in writing containing a statement of the grounds of his`
  line `opinion, prohibit until he is satisfied that the danger is removed, the employment in or about`
  line `the mine or any part thereof of any person whose employment is not in his opinion`
  line `reasonably necessary for the purpose of removing the danger;`
  line
  line `(e) every person whose employment is prohibited under sub-clause (b) or sub-clause (d)`
  line `shall be entitled to payment of full wages for the period for which he would have been, but`
  line `for the prohibition, in employment and the employer shall be liable for payment of such full`
  line `wages of that person:`
  line
  line `Provided that the employer may instead of paying such full wages provide such person`
  line `with an alternative employment at the same wages which such person was receiving in the`
  line `employment which was prohibited;`
  line
  line `(f) where a notice has been given under sub-clause (a) or an order is made under subclause (b) or sub-clause (c) or sub-clause (d) by an Inspector-cumFacilitator, the employer of`
  line `the mine may, within ten days after the receipt of the notice or order, as the case may be,`
  line `appeal against the same to the Chief Inspector-cum-Facilitator who may confirm, modify or`
  line `cancel the notice or order;`
  line
  line `(g) the Chief Inspector-cum-Facilitator or the Inspector-cum-Facilitator sending a notice`
  line `under sub-clause (a) or making an order under sub-clause (b) or sub-clause (c) or sub-clause`
  line `(d) and the Chief Inspector-cum-Facilitator making an order (other than an order of`
  line `cancellation in appeal) under sub-clause (f) shall forthwith report the same to the Central`
  line Government;
  line
  line `(h) if the employer of the mine objects to a notice sent under sub-clause (a) by the Chief`
  line `Inspector-cum-Facilitator or the Inspector-cumFacilitator or to an order made by the Chief`
  line `Inspector-cum-Facilitator or the Inspector-cum-Facilitator under sub-clause (b) or sub-clause`
  line `(c) or sub-clause (d) or sub-clause (f), as the case may be, he may, within twenty days after`
  line `the receipt of the notice containing the requisition or of the order or after the date of the`
  line `decision on appeal, as the case may be, send his objection in writing stating the grounds`
  line `thereof to the Central Government which shall, ordinarily within a period of one month from`
  line `the date of receipt of the objection, decide the matter;`
  line
  line `(i) every notice under sub-clause (a), or order under sub-clause (b) or sub-clause (c) or`
  line `sub-clause (d) or sub-clause (f), to which objection is made under sub-clause (h), shall be`
  line `complied with, pending the objection with the concerned Chief Inspector-cum-Facilitator or`
  line `Inspector-cum-Facilitator of the mine, for the decision of the Central Government:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Central Government may, on the application of the employer, suspend`
  line `the operation of a notice under sub-clause (a), pending its decision on the objection;`
  line
  line `(j) nothing in this section shall affect the powers of a magistrate under section 144 of the`
  line `Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974.);`
  line
  line `(k) where in respect of any matter relating to safety of mine for which express provision is`
  line `made by or under this Code, the employer of a mine fails to comply with such provisions, the`
  line `Chief Inspector-cum-Facilitator may give notice in writing requiring the same to be complied`
  line `with within such time as he may specify in the notice or within such extended period of time`
  line `as he may, from time to time, specify thereafter;`
  line
  line `(l) where the employer fails to comply with the terms of a notice given under`
  line `sub-clause (k) within the period specified in such notice or within the extended period of`
  line `time specified under that sub-clause, the Chief Inspector-cum-Facilitator may, by order in`
  line `writing, prohibit the employment, in or about the mine or any part thereof, of any person`
  line `whose employment is not, in his opinion, reasonably necessary for securing compliance with`
  line `the terms of the notice;`
  line
  line `(m) every person whose employment is prohibited under sub-clause (l), shall be entitled`
  line `to payment of full wages for the period for which he would have been, but for the`
  line `prohibition, in employment, and the owner, agent or manager referred to in section 67 shall`
  line `be liable for payment of such full wages of that person:`
  line `Provided that the employer may, instead of paying such full wages, provide such person`
  line `with an alternative employment at the same wages which such person was receiving in the`
  line `employment which was prohibited under sub-clause (l);`
  line
  line `(n) the provisions of sub-clauses (g), (h) and (i) shall apply in relation to a notice issued`
  line `under sub-clause (k) or an order made under sub-clause (l) as they apply in relation to a`
  line `notice or an order under sub-clause (b);`
  line
  line `(o) the Chief Inspector-cum-Facilitator may, for reasons to be recorded in writing, reverse`
  line `or modify any order passed by him under this Code or under any regulation, rule or bye-law`
  line `made thereunder in relation to mine;`
  line
  line `(p) no order prejudicial to the owner, agent or manager of a mine shall be made under this`
  line `section unless such owner, agent or manager has been given a reasonable opportunity of`
  line `making representation;`
  line
  line `(q) the Central Government may reverse or modify any order passed by Chief Inspectorcum-Facilitator under this Code or under any regulation, rule or bye-laws thereunder in`
  line `relation to mine;`
  line
  line `(C) shall have the following special powers in respect of dock work namely:---`
  line
  line `(a) if it appears to an Inspector-cum-Facilitator that any place where any dock work is`
  line `being carried on is in such a condition that it is dangerous to life, safety or health, of workers`
  line `employed in dock work, he may, in writing, serve on the employer, an order prohibiting any`
  line `dock work, in such place, until measures have been taken to remove the cause of the danger`
  line `to his satisfaction;`
  line
  line `(b) an Inspector-cum-Facilitator after serving an order under clause (a) shall endorse a`
  line `copy thereof to the Chief Inspector-cum-Facilitator who may modify or cancel the order`
  line `without waiting for an appeal;`
  line
  line `(c) any person aggrieved by an order under clause (a) or clause (b) may, within fifteen`
  line `days from the date on which the order is communicated to him, prefer an appeal to the Chief`
  line `Inspector-cum-Facilitator or where such order is by the Chief Inspector-cum-Facilitator, to`
  line `the Central Government and the Chief Inspector-cum-Facilitator or the Central Government`
  line `shall, after giving the appellant an opportunity of being heard, dispose of the appeal within`
  line `sixty days:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Chief Inspector-cum-Facilitator or the Central Government may`
  line `entertain the appeal after the expiry of the said period of fifteen days, if he or it is satisfied`
  line `that the appellant was prevented by sufficient cause from filing the appeal in time:`
  line
  line `Provided further that an order under clause (a) or an order modified under clause (b) shall`
  line `be complied with, pending the decision of the Chief Inspector-cum-Facilitator or the Central`
  line Government.
  line
  line `(2) Without prejudice to the other powers of an Inspector-cum-Facilitator elsewhere in this Code,---`
  line
  line `(a) if it appears to the Chief Inspector-cum-Facilitator or Inspector-cum-Facilitator that any`
  line `site or place at which any building or other construction work is being carried on, is in such`
  line `condition that it is dangerous to life, safety or health of building workers or the general public,`
  line `he may, in writing serve, on the employer of building workers working at such site or place or`
  line `on the employer of the establishment in which such site or place is situated or on the person in`
  line `charge of such site or place, an order prohibiting any building or other construction work at such`
  line `site or place until measures have been taken to remove the cause of the danger to his`
  line satisfaction;
  line
  line `(b) an Inspector-cum-Facilitator serving an order under clause (a) shall endorse a copy of the`
  line `order to the Chief Inspector-cum-Facilitator;`
  line
  line `(c) such prohibition order made by the Inspector-cum-Facilitator shall be complied with by`
  line `the employer forthwith.`
  line
  line `(3) Any person aggrieved by an order under clause (a) of sub-section (2), may, within fifteen days`
  line `from the date on which the order is communicated to him, prefer an appeal to the Chief Inspectorcum-Facilitator or where such order is by the Chief Inspector-cum-Facilitator, to the appropriate`
  line `Government and the Chief Inspector-cum-Facilitator or the appropriate Government, as the case may`
  line `be, shall, after giving the appellant an opportunity of being heard, dispose of the appeal within sixty`
  line `days:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Chief Inspector-cum-Facilitator or the appropriate Government may, entertain the`
  line `appeal after the expiry of the said period of fifteen days if it is satisfied that the appellant was`
  line `prevented by sufficient cause from filing the appeal in time:`
  line
  line `Provided further that the order under clause (a) of sub-section (2), shall be complied with, subject`
  line `to the decision of the Chief Inspector-cum-Facilitator or the appropriate Government as the case may`
  line be.
obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_39:
  sectionId (101707)
  sectionNo (39)
  orderNo 39
  title `Secrecy of information by Chief Inspector-cum-Facilitator or Inspector-cum-Facilitator, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_39_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013&sectionId=101707&sectionno=39&orderno=39&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013
obj_root_law_sections_39_content:
  string
  line `(1) All copies of, and extracts from, registers or other records pertaining to any establishment and`
  line `all other information relating to any manufacturing or commercial business or any working process`
  line `acquired by the Chief Inspector-cum-Facilitator or an Inspector-cum-Facilitator or by any one assisting`
  line `him, in the course of the inspection or survey of any establishment under this Code or acquired by any`
  line `officer authorised under section 20 in the exercise of his duties thereunder, shall be regarded as`
  line `confidential and shall not, while in service or after leaving the service, be disclosed to any person or`
  line `authority unless the Chief Inspector-cum-Facilitator or the Inspector-cum-Facilitator considers disclosure`
  line `necessary to ensure the health, safety or welfare of any person employed in establishment.`
  line
  line `(2) Nothing in sub-section (1) shall apply to the disclosure of any such information to---`
  line
  line `(a) any court;`
  line
  line `(b) any Committee or Board constituted under this Code;`
  line
  line `(c) an official superior or the employer of the establishment concerned;`
  line
  line `(d) a Commissioner for employees' compensation appointed under the Employees'`
  line `Compensation Act, 1923 (8 of 1923);`
  line
  line `(e) the Controller, Indian Bureau of Mines; and`
  line
  line `(f) any such officer, authority or authorised person as may be specified in this behalf by the`
  line `appropriate Government.`
  line
  line `(3) Notwithstanding anything contained in the Right to Information Act, 2005 (22 of 2005), no`
  line `Chief Inspector-cum-Facilitator or Inspector-cum-Facilitator shall disclose the source of any complaint, made to him regarding the contravention of the provisions of this Code without the consent`
  line `of the complainant and shall also not while making an inspection under this Code in pursuance of such`
  line `complaint, disclose to the employer concerned or any of his representative that the inspection is being`
  line `made in pursuance of such complaint.`
obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_40:
  sectionId (102028)
  sectionNo (40)
  orderNo 40
  title `Facilities to be afforded to Inspector-cum-Facilitator.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_40_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013&sectionId=102028&sectionno=40&orderno=40&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013
obj_root_law_sections_40_content:
  string
  line `Every employer of an establishment`
  line `shall afford the Chief Inspector-cum-Facilitator and every Inspector-cum-Facilitator having jurisdiction or`
  line `every person authorised by the Chief Inspector-cum-Facilitator all reasonable facilities for making any`
  line `entry, inspection, survey, measurement, examination or inquiry under this Code.`
obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_41:
  sectionId (102029)
  sectionNo (41)
  orderNo 41
  title `Powers of special officer to enter, measure, etc., in relation to mine.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_41_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013&sectionId=102029&sectionno=41&orderno=41&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013
obj_root_law_sections_41_content:
  string
  line `Any person in the`
  line `service of the Government duly authorised in this behalf by a special order in writing of the Chief`
  line `Inspector-cum-Facilitator or of an Inspector-cum-Facilitator may, for the purpose of surveying, leveling`
  line `or measuring any mine or any output therefrom, after giving not less than three days' notice to the`
  line `manager of such mine, enter the mine and may survey, level or measure the mine or any part thereof or`
  line `any output therefrom at any time by day or night:`
  line
  line `Provided that, where in the opinion of the Chief Inspector-cum-Facilitator or of an Inspector-cum-Facilitator an emergency exists, he may, by order in writing, authorise any such person to enter the mine`
  line `for any of the aforesaid purposes without giving any such notice.`
obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_42:
  sectionId (101709)
  sectionNo (42)
  orderNo 42
  title `Medical officer.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_42_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_42_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013&sectionId=101709&sectionno=42&orderno=42&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013
obj_root_law_sections_42_content:
  string
  line `(1) The appropriate Government may appoint medical practitioners having`
  line `prescribed qualification to be medical officers for the purposes of this Code in relation to factory, mines,`
  line `plantation, motor transport undertakings and in any other establishment as may be prescribed:`
  line
  line `Provided that the medical officers so appointed shall before entering into their office shall disclose to`
  line `the appropriate Government their interest in the concerned establishment.`
  line
  line `(2) The medical officer shall perform the following duties, namely:---`
  line
  line `(a) the examination and certification of workers in a mine or factory or in such other establishment`
  line `engaged in such dangerous occupations or processes as may be prescribed;`
  line
  line `(b) the exercise of such medical supervision for any factory, mines, plantation, motor transport`
  line `undertaking and for such other establishment as may be prescribed by the appropriate Government`
  line `where cases of illness have occurred which it is reasonable to believe are due to the nature of any`
  line `process carried on or other conditions of work prevailing in such establishments;`
  line
  line `(c) the examination and certification of adolescent for the purpose of ascertaining his fitness for`
  line `employment in factory, plantation, motor transport undertakings and in any other establishment as may`
  line `be prescribed by the appropriate Government in any work which is likely to cause injury to their`
  line health.
obj_root_law_sections_42_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_43:
  sectionId (101710)
  sectionNo (43)
  orderNo 43
  title `Employment of women.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_43_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_43_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013&sectionId=101710&sectionno=43&orderno=43&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013
obj_root_law_sections_43_content:
  string
  line `Women shall be entitled to be employed in all establishments for all`
  line `types of work under this Code and they may also be employed, with their consent before 6 a.m. and`
  line `beyond 7 p.m. subject to such conditions relating to safety, holidays and working hours or any other`
  line `condition to be observed by the employer as may be prescribed by the appropriate Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_43_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_44:
  sectionId (101711)
  sectionNo (44)
  orderNo 44
  title `Adequate safety of employment of women in dangerous operation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_44_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_44_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013&sectionId=101711&sectionno=44&orderno=44&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013
obj_root_law_sections_44_content:
  string
  line `Where the appropriate`
  line `Government considers that the employment of women is dangerous for their health and safety, in an`
  line `establishment or class of establishments or in any particular hazardous or dangerous processes in such`
  line `establishment or class of establishments, due to the operation carried out therein, such Government may`
  line `in the prescribed manner, require the employer to provide adequate safeguards prior to the employment of`
  line `women for such operation.`
obj_root_law_sections_44_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_45:
  sectionId (101712)
  sectionNo (45)
  orderNo 45
  title `Applicability of this Part.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_45_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_45_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013&sectionId=101712&sectionno=45&orderno=45&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013
obj_root_law_sections_45_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Part shall apply to---`
  line
  line `(i) every establishment in which fifty or more contract labour are employed or were employed`
  line `on any day of the preceding twelve months through contract;`
  line
  line `(ii) every manpower supply contractor who has employed, on any day of the preceding twelve`
  line `months, fifty or more contract labour.`
  line
  line `(2) This Part shall not apply to the establishment in which work only of an intermittent or casual`
  line `nature is performed:`
  line
  line `Provided that if a question arises as to whether work performed in an establishment is of an`
  line `intermittent or casual nature, the appropriate Government shall decide that question after consultation`
  line `with the National Board or a State Advisory Board and its decision thereon shall be final.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--- For the purpose of this sub-section, work performed in an establishment shall not be`
  line `deemed to be of an intermittent nature---`
  line
  line `(i) if it was performed for more than one hundred and twenty days in the preceding twelve`
  line `months; or`
  line
  line `(ii) if it is of seasonal character and is performed for more than sixty days in a year.`
obj_root_law_sections_45_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_46:
  sectionId (101713)
  sectionNo (46)
  orderNo 46
  title `Appointment of designated authority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_46_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_46_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013&sectionId=101713&sectionno=46&orderno=46&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013
obj_root_law_sections_46_content:
  string
  line `The appropriate Government may, by an order, appoint`
  line `such persons, being Gazetted officers of the Government, as it thinks fit to be designated as authority`
  line `under sub-section (1) of section 119 and specify the limits of their jurisdiction and vest with such powers`
  line `and duties including dealing with issuance and revocation of licences electronically as may be specified`
  line therein.
obj_root_law_sections_46_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_47:
  sectionId (101714)
  sectionNo (47)
  orderNo 47
  title `Licensing of contractors.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_47_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_47_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013&sectionId=101714&sectionno=47&orderno=47&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013
obj_root_law_sections_47_content:
  string
  line `(1) No contractor to whom this Part applies shall---`
  line
  line `(a) supply or engage contract labour in any establishment; or`
  line
  line `(b) undertake or execute the work through contract labour,`
  line
  line `except under and in accordance with a licence issued to him by the authority referred to in sub-section (1)`
  line `of section 119 in accordance with the provisions of that section after satisfying that the contractor fulfills`
  line `such requisite qualifications or criteria as may be prescribed by the Central Government and such licence`
  line `shall, in addition to the requisite particulars and conditions specified in sub-section (3), specify the`
  line `number of such contract labour who can be supplied or engaged and the amount of security to be`
  line `deposited by the contractor.`
  line
  line `(2) Where the contractor does not fulfil the requisite qualifications or criteria referred to in`
  line `sub-section (1), the authority referred to in sub-section (1) of section 119 may issue him a "work specific`
  line `licence" electronically renewable within such period as may be prescribed by the Central Government to`
  line `supply or engage the contract labour, or execute the work through contract labour, only for the concerned`
  line `work order as may be specified in such licence and subject to such conditions as may be specified in such`
  line licence.
  line
  line `(3) Subject to the provisions of this Part,---`
  line
  line `(a) a licence under sub-section (1) may contain such conditions including, in particular, conditions`
  line `as to hours of work, fixation of wages and other essential amenities in respect of contract labour as`
  line `may be prescribed by the appropriate Government;`
  line
  line `(b) the licence referred to in sub-section (1) or sub-section (2), shall be obtained from, if for such`
  line `establishment the appropriate Government is---`
  line
  line `(i) the Central Government, the authority referred to in sub-section (1) of section 119 designated`
  line `by that Government; and`
  line
  line `(ii) the State Government, the authority referred to in sub-section (1) of section 119 designated`
  line `by that Government:`
  line
  line `Provided that where the contractor is desirous of obtaining licence for supplying or engaging contract`
  line `labour or undertaking or executing the contract works under sub-section (1) or sub-section (2) in more`
  line `than one States or for the whole of India, then, he may obtain the licence from the authority referred to in`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 119 designated by the Central Government for such purpose and the provisions`
  line `of that section shall apply:`
  line
  line `Provided further that before issuing such licence the authority referred to in the first proviso shall`
  line `consult the concerned State or States authorities designated under sub-section (1) of section 119,`
  line `electronically before issuing licence for the establishments for which the appropriate Government is the`
  line `State Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_47_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_48:
  sectionId (101715)
  sectionNo (48)
  orderNo 48
  title `Procedure for issue or renewal of licence.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_48_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_48_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013&sectionId=101715&sectionno=48&orderno=48&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013
obj_root_law_sections_48_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to the provisions of section 119, every`
  line `application for issuing a licence under section 119 for the purposes of sub-section (1) or sub-section (2) of`
  line `section 47 shall be made electronically in such form and manner and shall contain such particulars`
  line `regarding the number of contract labour, nature of work for which contract labour is to be employed and`
  line `such other particulars including the information relating to the employment of inter-State migrant workers`
  line `as may be prescribed by the appropriate Government.`
  line
  line `(2) Subject to the provisions of section 119, the authority referred to in sub-section (1) thereof shall`
  line `follow such procedure as may be prescribed by the appropriate Government.`
  line
  line `(3) Subject to the provisions of section 119, the licence issued for the purposes of sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 47 shall be valid for a period of five years in respect of the number of contract labour specified`
  line `therein and in case the contractor wants to increase the number of the contract labour, he shall apply in the`
  line `prescribed manner for the amendment to the licence for such purpose to the authority referred to in`
  line `sub-section (1) of section119 and if the licence is so amended, the number of contract labour shall be`
  line `increased to such extent by depositing such security deposit as specified in the amended licence for the`
  line `balance period.`
  line
  line `(4) Subject to the provisions of section 119, the licence issued for the purposes of sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 47 shall contain responsibility of the contractor as may be prescribed by the appropriate`
  line Government.
obj_root_law_sections_48_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_49:
  sectionId (101716)
  sectionNo (49)
  orderNo 49
  title `No fees or commission or any cost to workers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_49_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_49_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013&sectionId=101716&sectionno=49&orderno=49&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013
obj_root_law_sections_49_content:
  string
  line `The contractor shall not charge directly or`
  line `indirectly, in whole or in part, any fee or commission from the contract labour.`
obj_root_law_sections_49_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_50:
  sectionId (101717)
  sectionNo (50)
  orderNo 50
  title `Information regarding work order to be given to the appropriate Government.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_50_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_50_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013&sectionId=101717&sectionno=50&orderno=50&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013
obj_root_law_sections_50_content:
  string
  line `(1) When a`
  line `contractor receives work order from an establishment either to supply contract labour in the establishment`
  line `or to execute the contract through contract labour in the establishment he shall, within such time and in`
  line `such manner as may be prescribed, intimate to the authority referred to in section 119.`
  line
  line `(2) Where the contractor fails to give intimation under sub-section (1), the designated authority may,`
  line `after giving the holder of the licence an opportunity of showing cause, suspend or cancel the licence in`
  line `such manner as may be prescribed by the appropriate Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_50_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_51:
  sectionId (101718)
  sectionNo (51)
  orderNo 51
  title `Revocation, suspension and amendment of licence.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_51_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_51_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013&sectionId=101718&sectionno=51&orderno=51&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013
obj_root_law_sections_51_content:
  string
  line `(1) If the authority referred to in`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 119 is satisfied, either on a reference made to him in this behalf or otherwise,`
  line that---
  line
  line `(a) a licence granted for the purposes of this Part has been obtained by misrepresentation or`
  line `suppression of any material fact, or`
  line
  line `(b) the holder of a licence has, failed to comply with the conditions subject to which the licence has`
  line `been granted or has contravened any of the provisions of this Part or the rules made thereunder, then,`
  line
  line `without prejudice to any other penalty to which the contractor may be liable under this Code, the authority`
  line `referred to in sub-section (1) of section 119 may, after giving the contractor an opportunity of showing`
  line `cause, revoke or suspend the licence in accordance with the procedure as may be prescribed by the`
  line `Central Government.`
  line
  line `(2) Subject to any rules that may be made in this behalf, the authority referred to in sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 119 may amend a licence granted for the purposes of this Part.`
obj_root_law_sections_51_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_52:
  sectionId (101719)
  sectionNo (52)
  orderNo 52
  title Appeal.
  content obj_root_law_sections_52_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_52_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013&sectionId=101719&sectionno=52&orderno=52&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013
obj_root_law_sections_52_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any person aggrieved by an order made under section 47, section 48 or section 51`
  line `may, within thirty days from the date on which the order is communicated to him, prefer an appeal to an`
  line `appellate authority prescribed by the appropriate Government under sub-section (6) of section 119:`
  line
  line `Provided that the appellate authority may entertain the appeal after the expiry of the said period of`
  line `thirty days, if he is satisfied that the appellant was prevented by sufficient cause from filing the appeal in`
  line time.
  line
  line `(2) On receipt of an appeal under sub-section (1), the appellate authority shall, after giving the`
  line `appellant an opportunity of being heard, dispose of the appeal within thirty days from the date on which`
  line `the appeal is preferred.`
obj_root_law_sections_52_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_53:
  sectionId (101720)
  sectionNo (53)
  orderNo 53
  title `Liability of principal employer for welfare facilities.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_53_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_53_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013&sectionId=101720&sectionno=53&orderno=53&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013
obj_root_law_sections_53_content:
  string
  line `Welfare facilities specified under`
  line `section 23 and section 24 shall be provided by the principal employer of the establishment to the contract`
  line `labour who are employed in such establishment.`
obj_root_law_sections_53_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_54:
  sectionId (101721)
  sectionNo (54)
  orderNo 54
  title `Effect of employing contract labour from a non-licenced contractor.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_54_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_54_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013&sectionId=101721&sectionno=54&orderno=54&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013
obj_root_law_sections_54_content:
  string
  line `Where any principal`
  line `employer of an establishment is employing contract labour through a contractor who is required to obtain`
  line `a licence under this Part, but he has not obtained such licence, then, such employment shall be deemed to`
  line `be in contravention of the provision of this Code.`
obj_root_law_sections_54_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_55:
  sectionId (101722)
  sectionNo (55)
  orderNo 55
  title `Responsibility for payment of wages.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_55_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_55_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013&sectionId=101722&sectionno=55&orderno=55&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013
obj_root_law_sections_55_content:
  string
  line `(1) A contractor shall be responsible for payment of`
  line `wages to each contract labour employed by him and such wages shall be paid before the expiry of such`
  line `period as may be prescribed by the appropriate Government.`
  line
  line `(2) Every contractor shall, make the disbursement of wages referred to in sub-section (1) through bank`
  line `transfer or electronic mode and inform the principal employer electronically the amount so paid by such`
  line `mode:`
  line
  line `Provided that where it is not practicable to disburse payment in the mode specified in this section,`
  line `then, the payment shall be made in such manner as may be prescribed by the appropriate Government.`
  line
  line `(3) In case the contractor fails to make payment of wages referred to in sub-section (1) within the`
  line `prescribed period or makes short payment, then, the principal employer shall be liable to make payment`
  line `of the wages in full or the unpaid balance due, as the case may be, to the concerned contract labour`
  line `employed by the contractor and recover the amount so paid from the contractor either by deduction from`
  line `any amount payable to the contractor under any contract or as a debt payable by the contractor.`
  line
  line `(4) The appropriate Government, in the event the contractor does not pay the wages to the contract`
  line `labour employed by him, shall pass the orders of making payment of such wages from the amount`
  line `deposited by such contractor as security deposit under the licence issued by the licensing officer to the`
  line `contractor, in such manner as may be prescribed by such Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_55_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_56:
  sectionId (101723)
  sectionNo (56)
  orderNo 56
  title `Experience certificate.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_56_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_56_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013&sectionId=101723&sectionno=56&orderno=56&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013
obj_root_law_sections_56_content:
  string
  line `Every concerned contractor shall issue, on demand, experience`
  line `certificate, in such form as may be prescribed by the appropriate Government, to the contract labour`
  line `giving details of the work performed by such contract labour.`
obj_root_law_sections_56_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_57:
  sectionId (101724)
  sectionNo (57)
  orderNo 57
  title `Prohibition of employment of contract labour.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_57_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_57_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013&sectionId=101724&sectionno=57&orderno=57&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013
obj_root_law_sections_57_content:
  string
  line `(1) Notwithstanding anything contained in this`
  line `Part, employment of contract labour in core activities of any establishment is prohibited:`
  line
  line `Provided that the principal employer may engage contract labour through a contractor to any core`
  line `activity, if---`
  line
  line `(a) the normal functioning of the establishment is such that the activity is ordinarily done through`
  line `contractor; or`
  line
  line `(b) the activities are such that they do not require full time workers for the major portion of the`
  line `working hours in a day or for longer periods, as the case may be;`
  line
  line `(c) any sudden increase of volume of work in the core activity which needs to be accomplished in a`
  line `specified time.`
  line
  line `(2) (a) The appropriate Government may, by notification, appoint a designated authority to advise that`
  line `Government on the question whether any activity of an establishment is a core activity or otherwise;`
  line
  line `(b) if a question arises as to whether any activity of an establishment is a core activity or otherwise,`
  line `the aggrieved party may make an application in such form and manner as may be prescribed, to the`
  line `appropriate Government for decision;`
  line
  line `(c) the appropriate Government may refer any such question suo motu or refer the application to the`
  line `designated authority, which on the basis of relevant material in its possession, or after making such an`
  line `enquiry as it deems fit, shall report to the appropriate Government, within such period and thereafter`
  line `the appropriate Government shall decide the question within such period as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_57_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_58:
  sectionId (101725)
  sectionNo (58)
  orderNo 58
  title `Power to exempt in special cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_58_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_58_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013&sectionId=101725&sectionno=58&orderno=58&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013
obj_root_law_sections_58_content:
  string
  line `The appropriate Government may, in the case of an`
  line `emergency, direct, by notification, that subject to such conditions and restrictions, if any, and for such`
  line `period, as may be specified in the notification, all or any of the provisions of this Code or the rules made`
  line `thereunder shall not apply to any establishment or class of establishments or any class of contractors.`
obj_root_law_sections_58_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_59:
  sectionId (101726)
  sectionNo (59)
  orderNo 59
  title `Applicability of Part II.`
  content `This Part shall apply to every establishment in which ten or more interState migrant workers are employed or were employed on any day of the preceding twelve months.`
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_59_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013&sectionId=101726&sectionno=59&orderno=59&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013
obj_root_law_sections_59_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_60:
  sectionId (101727)
  sectionNo (60)
  orderNo 60
  title `Facilities to inter-State migrant workers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_60_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_60_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013&sectionId=101727&sectionno=60&orderno=60&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013
obj_root_law_sections_60_content:
  string
  line `It shall be the duty of every contractor or the`
  line `employer, of an establishment employing inter-State migrant workers in connection with the work of that`
  line establishment---
  line
  line `(i) to ensure suitable conditions of work to such worker having regard to the fact that he is required`
  line `to work in a State different from his own State;`
  line
  line `(ii) in case of fatal accident or serious bodily injury to any such worker, to report to the specified`
  line `authorities of both the States and also the next of kin of the worker;`
  line
  line `(iii) to extend all benefits to such worker which are available to a worker of that establishment`
  line `including benefits under the Employees' State Insurance Act, 1948 (34 of 1948) or the Employees'`
  line `Provident Funds and Miscellaneous Provisions Act, 1952 (19 of 1952) or any other law for the time`
  line `being in force and the facility of medical check-up as available to a worker under clause (c) of`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 6.`
obj_root_law_sections_60_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_61:
  sectionId (101728)
  sectionNo (61)
  orderNo 61
  title `Journey allowance.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_61_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_61_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013&sectionId=101728&sectionno=61&orderno=61&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013
obj_root_law_sections_61_content:
  string
  line `The employer shall pay, to every inter-State migrant worker employed in`
  line `his establishment, in a year a lump sum amount of fare for to and fro journey to his native place from the`
  line `place of his employment, in the manner taking into account the minimum service for entitlement,`
  line `periodicity and class of travel and such other matters as may be prescribed by the appropriate`
  line Government.
obj_root_law_sections_61_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_62:
  sectionId (101729)
  sectionNo (62)
  orderNo 62
  title `Benefits of public distribution system, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_62_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_62_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013&sectionId=101729&sectionno=62&orderno=62&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013
obj_root_law_sections_62_content:
  string
  line `The appropriate Government shall make schemes to`
  line provide---
  line
  line `(a) option to an inter-State migrant worker for availing benefits of public distribution system either`
  line `in his native State or the destination State where he is employed; and`
  line
  line `(b) for portability of the benefits of the inter-State migrant worker working for building or other`
  line `construction work out of the building and other construction cess fund in the destination State where`
  line `such inter-State migrant worker is employed.`
obj_root_law_sections_62_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_63:
  sectionId (101730)
  sectionNo (63)
  orderNo 63
  title `Toll free helpline.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_63_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_63_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013&sectionId=101730&sectionno=63&orderno=63&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013
obj_root_law_sections_63_content:
  string
  line `The appropriate Government may provide facility of toll free helpline to the`
  line `inter-State migrant workers in such manner as may be prescribed by that Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_63_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_64:
  sectionId (101731)
  sectionNo (64)
  orderNo 64
  title `Study of inter-State migrant workers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_64_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_64_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013&sectionId=101731&sectionno=64&orderno=64&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013
obj_root_law_sections_64_content:
  string
  line `The appropriate Government may provide for study of`
  line `inter-State migrant workers in such manner as may be prescribed by that Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_64_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_65:
  sectionId (101732)
  sectionNo (65)
  orderNo 65
  title `Past liabilities.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_65_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_65_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013&sectionId=101732&sectionno=65&orderno=65&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013
obj_root_law_sections_65_content:
  string
  line `No suit or other proceeding shall lie in any court or before any authority for the`
  line `recovery of debt or any part thereof relating to an inter-State migrant worker after the completion of his`
  line `employment where it remains unsettled obligation to the contractor or the principal employer and such`
  line `debt or part thereof shall, on the completion of the period of employment of such worker, be deemed to`
  line `have been extinguished.`
obj_root_law_sections_65_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_66:
  sectionId (101733)
  sectionNo (66)
  orderNo 66
  title `Prohibition of employment of audio-visual worker without agreement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_66_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_66_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013&sectionId=101733&sectionno=66&orderno=66&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013
obj_root_law_sections_66_content:
  string
  line `(1) No person shall`
  line `be employed as an audio-visual worker in or in connection with production of any audio-visual`
  line `programme unless,---`
  line
  line `(a) an agreement in writing is entered into---`
  line
  line `(i) with such person by the producer of such audio-visual programme; or`
  line
  line `(ii) with such person by the producer of such audio-visual programme with the contractor,`
  line `where such person is employed through such contractor; or`
  line
  line `(iii) with such person by the contractor or other person through whom such person is employed;`
  line and
  line
  line `(b) such agreement is registered with the competent authority, to be notified by the appropriate`
  line `Government, by the producer of such audio-visual programme.`
  line
  line `(2) Every agreement, referred to in sub-section (1) shall,---`
  line
  line `(a) be in the prescribed form;`
  line
  line `(b) specify the name and such other particulars as may be prescribed by the appropriate`
  line `Government with respect to, such person to be employed under the agreement as audio-visual`
  line worker;
  line
  line `(c) include, where such audio-visual worker is employed through a contractor, a specific`
  line `condition to the effect that in the event of the contractor failing to discharge his obligations under`
  line `the agreement to the audio-visual worker with respect to payment of wages or any other matter, the`
  line `producer of the audio-visual programme shall also be liable to discharge such obligations and shall`
  line `be entitled to be reimbursed with respect thereto by the contractor.`
  line
  line `(3) A copy of the agreement referred to in sub-section (1) with respect to the employment of the audiovisual worker shall, if such audio-visual worker is covered under the provision of an enactment for the`
  line `time being in force for providing the benefit of provident fund to him, also be forwarded by the producer`
  line `of the audio-visual programme to such authority as may be prescribed by the appropriate Government.`
  line
  line `(4) Notwithstanding anything contained in Chapters V, VI and VII, the agreement referred to in`
  line `sub-section (1) shall include,---`
  line
  line `(i) nature of assignment;`
  line
  line `(ii) wages and other benefits (including provident fund, if covered under the Employees'`
  line `Provident Fund and Miscellaneous Provisions Act, 1952 (19 of 1952));`
  line
  line `(iii) health and working conditions;`
  line
  line `(iv) safety;`
  line
  line `(v) hours of work;`
  line
  line `(vi) welfare facilities; and`
  line
  line `(vii) dispute resolution process or mechanism, the constitution and other details of which shall`
  line `be prescribed by the appropriate Government:`
  line
  line `Provided that in case of failure of the resolution of the dispute in such dispute resolution process or`
  line `mechanism, either party in the dispute may invoke the jurisdiction of the Industrial Tribunal`
  line `established by the appropriate Government under section 7A of the Industrial Disputes Act, 1947 (14 of 1947) and for such purpose such dispute shall be deemed to be industrial dispute within the`
  line `meaning of that Act and it shall be the responsibility of the producer of the audio-visual programme to`
  line `provide the facilities specified in the agreement to the audio-visual worker and the payment of wages`
  line `shall be through electronic mode.`
obj_root_law_sections_66_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_67:
  sectionId (101734)
  sectionNo (67)
  orderNo 67
  title Managers.
  content obj_root_law_sections_67_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_67_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013&sectionId=101734&sectionno=67&orderno=67&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013
obj_root_law_sections_67_content:
  string
  line `(1) Save as may be otherwise prescribed, every mine shall be under a sole manager`
  line `who shall have such qualifications as may be prescribed by the Central Government and the owner or`
  line `agent of every mine shall appoint a person having such qualifications to be the manager:`
  line
  line `Provided that the owner or agent may appoint himself as manager if he possesses the prescribed`
  line qualifications.
  line
  line `(2) Subject to any instructions given to him by or on behalf of the owner or agent of the mine, the`
  line `manager shall be responsible for the overall management, control, supervision and direction of the mine`
  line `and all such instructions when given by the owner or agent shall be confirmed in writing forthwith.`
  line
  line `(3) Except in case of an emergency, the owner or agent of a mine or anyone on his behalf shall not`
  line `give, otherwise than through the manager, instructions affecting the fulfilment of his statutory duties, to a`
  line `person, employed in a mine, who is responsible to the manager.`
obj_root_law_sections_67_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_68:
  sectionId (101735)
  sectionNo (68)
  orderNo 68
  title `Code not to apply in certain cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_68_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_68_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013&sectionId=101735&sectionno=68&orderno=68&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013
obj_root_law_sections_68_content:
  string
  line `(1) The provisions of this Code, except those contained in`
  line `sections 35, 38, 40, 41 and 44, shall not apply to---`
  line
  line `(a) any mine or part thereof in which excavation is being made for prospecting purposes only and`
  line `not for the purpose of obtaining minerals for use or sale subject to such conditions relating to number`
  line `of employees, depth of excavation and other matters as may be prescribed by the Central Government;`
  line
  line `(b) any mine engaged in the extraction of kankar, murrum, laterite, boulder, gravel, shingle,`
  line `ordinary sand (excluding mouldings and glass sand and other mineral sands), ordinary clay (excluding`
  line `kaolin, china clay, white clay or fire clay), building stone, slate, road metal, earth, fullers earth (marl,`
  line `chalk) and lime stone subject to such conditions relating to workings, open cast workings and`
  line `explosives as may be prescribed by the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), the Central Government may declare that`
  line `the provisions of this Code shall apply to such mine or part thereof as may be prescribed by the Central`
  line Government.
  line
  line `(3) Without prejudice to the provisions contained in sub-section (2), if at any time any of the`
  line `conditions specified in clause (a) or clause (b) of sub-section (1) is not fulfilled in relation to any mine`
  line `referred to in that sub-section, the provisions of this Code not set out in sub-section (1), shall become`
  line `immediately applicable, and it shall be the duty of the employer of the mine to inform about such non-fulfilment to such authority in such manner and within such time as may be prescribed by the Central`
  line Government.
obj_root_law_sections_68_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_69:
  sectionId (101736)
  sectionNo (69)
  orderNo 69
  title `Exemption from provision regarding employment.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_69_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_69_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013&sectionId=101736&sectionno=69&orderno=69&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013
obj_root_law_sections_69_content:
  string
  line `(1) In case of an emergency involving`
  line `serious risk to the safety of the mine or of persons employed therein, or in case of an accident, whether`
  line `actual or apprehended, or in case of any act of God or in case of any urgent work to be done to machinery,`
  line `plant or equipment of the mine as a result of breakdown of such machinery plant or equipment, the`
  line `manager may, subject to the provision of clause (B) of sub-section (1) of section 38 and in accordance`
  line `with the provisions of section 25 relating to exemption from hours of work above ground, hours of work`
  line `below ground and notification regarding hours of work and weekly day of rest relating to mines under`
  line `section 26, permit persons to be employed in contravention of sections 25 and 30 and sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 31 on such work as may be necessary to protect the safety of the mine or of the persons employed`
  line `therein:`
  line
  line `Provided that in case of any urgent work to be done to machinery, plant or equipment under this`
  line `section, the manager may take the action permitted by this section, although the production of mineral`
  line `would thereby be incidentally affected, but any action so taken shall not exceed the limits necessary for`
  line `the purpose of avoiding serious interference with the ordinary working of the mine.`
  line
  line `(2) Every case in which action has been taken by the manager under sub-section (1), shall be recorded`
  line `together with the circumstances relating thereto and a report thereof shall also be made to the Chief`
  line `Inspector-cum-Facilitator or the Inspector-cum-Facilitator.`
obj_root_law_sections_69_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_70:
  sectionId (101737)
  sectionNo (70)
  orderNo 70
  title `Employment of persons below eighteen years of age.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_70_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_70_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013&sectionId=101737&sectionno=70&orderno=70&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013
obj_root_law_sections_70_content:
  string
  line `(1) No person below eighteen years of`
  line `age shall be allowed to work in any mine or part thereof.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), apprentices and other trainees, not below`
  line `sixteen years of age, may be allowed to work, under proper supervision, in a mine or part thereof by the`
  line `manager as referred to in section 67:`
  line
  line `Provided that in the case of trainees, other than apprentices, prior approval of the Chief Inspector-cum-Facilitator or an Inspector-cum-Facilitator shall be obtained before they are allowed to work.`
  line
  line `(3) The Central Government may prescribe the provisions for medical examination of apprentice,`
  line `other trainee and employee in the mine to ensure their fitness to work and to prevent the persons below`
  line `sixteen years of age to work as apprentice or trainee and those who are not adults to work as such`
  line employee.
  line
  line `Explanation.--- In this section, "apprentice" means an apprentice as defined in clause (a) of section 2 of`
  line `the Apprentices Act, 1961(52 of 1961).`
obj_root_law_sections_70_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_71:
  sectionId (101738)
  sectionNo (71)
  orderNo 71
  title `Exemption to certain persons.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_71_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_71_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013&sectionId=101738&sectionno=71&orderno=71&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013
obj_root_law_sections_71_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government may make rules to provide for`
  line `exemption to certain persons or category of persons employed in mines from the provisions of`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 25, sub-section (1) of section 26, section 30 and sub-section (1) of section 31.`
obj_root_law_sections_71_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_72:
  sectionId (101739)
  sectionNo (72)
  orderNo 72
  title `Establishment, maintenance of rescue services and vocational training.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_72_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_72_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013&sectionId=101739&sectionno=72&orderno=72&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013
obj_root_law_sections_72_content:
  string
  line `The Central`
  line `Government may prescribe vocational training and rescue and recovery services for persons employed in`
  line `a mine.`
obj_root_law_sections_72_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_73:
  sectionId (101740)
  sectionNo (73)
  orderNo 73
  title `Decision of question whether a mine is covered under this Code.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_73_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_73_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013&sectionId=101740&sectionno=73&orderno=73&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013
obj_root_law_sections_73_content:
  string
  line `If any question arises as to`
  line `whether any excavation or working or premises in or adjacent to and belonging to a mine, on which any`
  line `process ancillary to the getting, dressing or preparation for sale of minerals or of coke is being carried on`
  line `in a mine within the meaning of this Code, the Central Government may decide the question, and a`
  line `certificate signed by a Secretary to the Government of India in the Ministry of Labour and Employment`
  line `shall be conclusive proof thereof.`
obj_root_law_sections_73_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_74:
  sectionId (101741)
  sectionNo (74)
  orderNo 74
  title `Licence to industrial premises and person.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_74_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_74_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013&sectionId=101741&sectionno=74&orderno=74&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013
obj_root_law_sections_74_content:
  string
  line `(1) Save as otherwise provided in this Part, no`
  line `employer shall use or allow to use any place or premises as an industrial premises unless he holds a valid`
  line `licence issued under section 119 for the purposes of this Part and no such premises shall be used except in`
  line `accordance with the terms and conditions of such licence.`
  line
  line `(2) Subject to the provisions of section 119, any person who intends to use or allows to use any place`
  line `or premises specified in sub-section (1) shall make an application to the authority referred to in`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 119, in such form and on payment of such fees as may be prescribed by the`
  line `State Government, for a licence to use, or allow to use, such premises as an industrial premises.`
  line
  line `(3) Subject to the provisions of section 119, the application shall specify the maximum number of`
  line `employees proposed to be employed at any time of the day in the place or premises and shall be`
  line `accompanied by a plan of the place or premises prepared in such manner as may be prescribed by the`
  line `State Government.`
  line
  line `(4) Subject to the provisions of section 119, the authority referred to in sub-section (1) thereof shall, in`
  line `deciding whether to grant or refuse to grant a licence, have regard to the following matters, namely:---`
  line
  line `(a) the suitability of the place or premises which is proposed to be used for the manufacture of`
  line `beedi or cigar or both;`
  line
  line `(b) previous experience of the applicant or he has employed experienced person or has entered into`
  line `agreement with the experienced person for employment for the period of licence;`
  line
  line `(c) the financial resources of the applicant including his financial capacity to meet the demands`
  line `arising out of the provisions of the laws for the time being in force relating to welfare of labour;`
  line
  line `(d) whether the application is made bona fide on behalf of the applicant himself or in enami of any`
  line `other person;`
  line
  line `(e) welfare of the labour in the locality, the interest of the public generally and such other matters`
  line `as may be prescribed by the State Government.`
  line
  line `(5) Subject to the provisions of section 119, a licence granted under the said section for the purposes of`
  line `this section shall be valid for five years and may be renewed thereafter.`
  line
  line `(6) Subject to the provisions of section 119, an application for the renewal of a licence for the purposes`
  line `of this Part shall be made at least thirty days before the expiry of the period thereof, on payment of such`
  line `fees as may be prescribed by the State Government, and where such an application has been made, the`
  line `licence shall be deemed to continue, notwithstanding the expiry of the period thereof, until the renewal of`
  line `the licence, or, as the case may be, the rejection of the application for the renewal thereof:`
  line
  line `Provided that the authority referred to in sub-section (1) of section 119 shall not grant or renew a`
  line `licence unless it is satisfied that the provisions of this Part and the rules made thereunder have been`
  line `complied with:`
  line
  line `Provided further that the authority referred to in sub-section (1) of section 119 shall renew or refuse to`
  line `renew the licence within such period as may be prescribed by the State Government and in deciding`
  line `whether to renew a licence or to refuse a renewal thereof shall have regard to the matters specified in`
  line `sub-section (4).`
  line
  line `(7) Subject to the provisions of section 119, the authority referred to in sub-section (1) thereof may,`
  line `after giving the holder of a licence an opportunity of being heard, cancel or suspend any licence granted`
  line `or renewed under section 119 for the purposes of this Part, if it appears to it that such licence has been`
  line `obtained by misrepresentation or fraud or that the licence has contravened or failed to comply with any of`
  line `the provisions of this Part or the rules made thereunder or any of the terms or conditions of the licence.`
  line
  line `(8) The State Government may issue in writing to an authority referred to in sub-section (1) of section`
  line `119 such directions of a general character as that Government may consider necessary in respect of any`
  line `matter relating to the grant or renewal of licence under section 119 relating to this section.`
  line
  line `(9) Subject to section 119 and the foregoing provisions of this section, the authority referred to in`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 119 may grant or renew licence relating to this Part on such terms and`
  line `conditions as it may determine and where such authority refuses to grant or renew any licence, it shall do`
  line `so by an order communicated to the applicant, giving the reasons in writing for such refusal.`
obj_root_law_sections_74_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_75:
  sectionId (101742)
  sectionNo (75)
  orderNo 75
  title Appeals.
  content obj_root_law_sections_75_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_75_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013&sectionId=101742&sectionno=75&orderno=75&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013
obj_root_law_sections_75_content:
  string
  line `Any person aggrieved by the decision of the authority referred to in sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 119 refusing to grant or renew a licence, or cancelling or suspending a licence, relating to this Part`
  line `may, within such time and on payment of such fees as may be prescribed, appeal to the appellate authority`
  line `referred to in sub-section (6) of section 119, and such authority may by order confirm, modify or reverse`
  line `any order refusing to grant or renew a licence, or cancelling or suspending a licence, relating to this Part.`
obj_root_law_sections_75_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_76:
  sectionId (101743)
  sectionNo (76)
  orderNo 76
  title `Permission to work by employees outside industrial premises.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_76_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_76_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013&sectionId=101743&sectionno=76&orderno=76&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013
obj_root_law_sections_76_content:
  string
  line `(1) The State Government may`
  line `permit the wetting or cutting of beedi or tobacco leaves by employees outside the industrial premises on`
  line `an application made to it by the employer on behalf of such employees, subject to such conditions as may`
  line `be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) The employer shall maintain the record of the work permitted under sub-section (1), to be carried`
  line `on outside the industrial premises, in such form as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) Save as otherwise provided in this section, no employer shall require or allow any manufacturing`
  line `process connected with the making of beedi or cigar or both to be carried on outside the industrial`
  line `premises:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing in this sub-section shall apply to any worker who is given raw material by an`
  line `employer or a contractor to make beedi or cigar or both at home.`
obj_root_law_sections_76_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_77:
  sectionId (101744)
  sectionNo (77)
  orderNo 77
  title `Part not to apply to self-employed persons in private dwelling houses.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_77_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_77_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013&sectionId=101744&sectionno=77&orderno=77&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013
obj_root_law_sections_77_content:
  string
  line `Nothing contained in`
  line `this Part shall apply to the owner or occupier of a private dwelling house, not being an employee of an`
  line `employer to whom this Part applies, who carries on any manufacturing process in such private dwelling`
  line `house with the assistance of the members of his family living with him in such dwelling house and`
  line `dependent on him.`
  line
  line `Explanation.---For the purposes of this section,---`
  line
  line `(i) "family" does not include child, as defined in the Child and Adolescent (Prohibition and`
  line `Regulation) Act, 1986 (61 of 1986), for this section;`
  line
  line `(ii) "private dwelling house" means a house in which persons engaged in the manufacture of beedi`
  line `or cigar or both reside.`
obj_root_law_sections_77_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_78:
  sectionId (101745)
  sectionNo (78)
  orderNo 78
  title `Prohibition of employment of certain persons in certain building or other construction work.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_78_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_78_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013&sectionId=101745&sectionno=78&orderno=78&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013
obj_root_law_sections_78_content:
  string
  line `No person, about whom the employer knows or has reasons to believe that he is a deaf or he has`
  line `a defective vision or he has a tendency to giddiness, shall be required or allowed to work in any such`
  line `operation of building or other construction work which is likely to involve a risk of any accident either to`
  line `the building worker himself or to any other person.`
obj_root_law_sections_78_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_79:
  sectionId (101746)
  sectionNo (79)
  orderNo 79
  title `Approval and licensing of factories.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_79_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_79_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013&sectionId=101746&sectionno=79&orderno=79&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013
obj_root_law_sections_79_content:
  string
  line `(1) The appropriate Government may make rules in`
  line `respect of factory or class or description of factories for---`
  line
  line `(a) the submission of plans including specifications, nature and certification thereof;`
  line
  line `(b) the previous permission for the site on which the factory is to be situated and for the`
  line `construction or extension thereof; and`
  line
  line `(c) subject to the provision of sub-section 119, licensing and renewal thereof including fees to be`
  line `payable for such, licensing and renewal, if required, as the case may be.`
  line
  line `(2) If on an application for permission referred to in clause (b) of sub-section (1) accompanied by the`
  line `plans and specifications required by the rules made under clause (a) of that sub-section, sent to the State`
  line `Government or Chief Inspector-cum-Facilitator in the electronic mode, no order is communicated to the`
  line `applicant within such period not exceeding thirty days, the permission applied for in the said application`
  line `shall be deemed to have been granted.`
  line
  line `(3) Where a State Government or a Chief Inspector-cum-Facilitator refuses to grant permission to the`
  line `site, construction or extension of a factory and licensing of a factory, the applicant may within thirty days`
  line `of the date of such refusal appeal to the Central Government if the decision appealed from was of the`
  line `State Government and to the State Government in any other case.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--- A factory shall not be deemed to be extended within the meaning of this section by`
  line `reason only of the replacement of any plant or machinery or within such limits as may be prescribed, of`
  line `the addition of any plant or machinery if such replacement or addition does not reduce the minimum clear`
  line `space required for safe working around the plant or machinery or adversely affect the environmental`
  line `conditions from the evolution or emission of steam, heat or dust or fumes injurious to health.`
obj_root_law_sections_79_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_80:
  sectionId (101747)
  sectionNo (80)
  orderNo 80
  title `Liability of owner of premises in certain circumstances.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_80_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_80_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013&sectionId=101747&sectionno=80&orderno=80&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013
obj_root_law_sections_80_content:
  string
  line `Where any premises or separate`
  line `buildings are leased to different occupiers for use as separate factories, the owner of the premises and`
  line `occupiers of the factories utilising such common facilities which include safety and fire prevention and`
  line `protection, access, hygiene, occupational health, ventilation, temperature, emergency preparedness and`
  line `response, canteens, shelter, rest rooms and crèches shall jointly and severally be responsible for provision`
  line `and maintenance of such common facilities and services as may be prescribed by the appropriate`
  line Government.
obj_root_law_sections_80_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_81:
  sectionId (101748)
  sectionNo (81)
  orderNo 81
  title `Power to apply Code to certain premises.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_81_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_81_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013&sectionId=101748&sectionno=81&orderno=81&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013
obj_root_law_sections_81_content:
  string
  line `(1) The appropriate Government may, by`
  line `notification, declare that all or any of the provisions of this Part shall apply to any place wherein a`
  line `manufacturing process is carried on with or without the aid of power or is ordinarily carried on`
  line `irrespective of the number of workers working in the factory.`
  line
  line `(2) After a place is so declared, it shall be deemed to be a factory for the purposes of this Code, and`
  line `the owner shall be deemed to be the occupier, and any person working therein, a worker.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--- For the purposes of this section, "owner" shall include a lessee or mortgagee with`
  line `possession of the premises.`
obj_root_law_sections_81_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_82:
  sectionId (101749)
  sectionNo (82)
  orderNo 82
  title `Dangerous operations.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_82_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_82_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013&sectionId=101749&sectionno=82&orderno=82&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013
obj_root_law_sections_82_content:
  string
  line `The appropriate Government may by rules make the provisions relating`
  line `to any factory or class or description of factories in which manufacturing process or operation is carried`
  line `on which exposes any of the persons employed in it to a serious risk of bodily injury, poisoning or`
  line `disease, for---`
  line
  line `(a) specifying the manufacturing process or operation and declaring it to be dangerous;`
  line
  line `(b) prohibiting or restricting the employment of pregnant women in the manufacturing process or`
  line operation;
  line
  line `(c) the periodical medical examination before, or at any time during the employment to ascertain`
  line `the fitness of a worker or employee for such employment on the cost of the occupier; and`
  line
  line `(d) welfare amenities, sanitary facilities, protective equipment and clothing, and any other`
  line `requirement necessary for dangerous operations.`
obj_root_law_sections_82_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_83:
  sectionId (101750)
  sectionNo (83)
  orderNo 83
  title `Constitution of site appraisal committee.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_83_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_83_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013&sectionId=101750&sectionno=83&orderno=83&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013
obj_root_law_sections_83_content:
  string
  line `(1) The appropriate Government may, constitute one`
  line `or more site appraisal committees consisting of a chairman and other members, for such purpose as may`
  line `be prescribed including to consider and to give recommendations on an application for grant of`
  line `permission for the initial location of a factory involving a hazardous process or for the expansion of such`
  line factory.
  line
  line `(2) The site appraisal committee referred to in sub-section (1) shall make its recommendation within a`
  line `period of thirty days of the receipt of the application for any of the purpose referred to in the said subsection in such form, as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_83_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_84:
  sectionId (101751)
  sectionNo (84)
  orderNo 84
  title `Compulsory disclosure of information by occupier.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_84_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_84_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013&sectionId=101751&sectionno=84&orderno=84&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013
obj_root_law_sections_84_content:
  string
  line `(1) The occupier of every factory`
  line `involving a hazardous process shall disclose in the manner prescribed by the State Government all`
  line `information regarding dangers, including health hazards and the measures to overcome such hazards`
  line `arising from the exposure to or handling of the materials or substances in the manufacture, transportation,`
  line `storage and other processes, to the workers employed in the factory, the Chief Inspector-cum-Facilitator`
  line `or Inspector-cum-Facilitator, the local authority within whose jurisdiction the factory is situate and the`
  line `general public in the vicinity.`
  line
  line `(2) The occupier shall, at the time of registering the factory involving a hazardous process, lay down a`
  line `detailed policy with respect to the health and safety of the workers employed therein and intimate such`
  line `policy to the Chief Inspector-cum-Facilitator or Inspector-cum-Facilitator and the local authority and,`
  line `thereafter, at such intervals as may be prescribed by the State Government, inform the Chief Inspector-cum-Facilitator or Inspector-cum-Facilitator and the local authority of any change made in the said`
  line policy.
  line
  line `(3) The information furnished under sub-section (1) shall include accurate information as to the`
  line `quantity, specifications and other characteristics of wastes and the manner of their disposal./`
  line
  line `(4) Every occupier shall, with the approval of the Chief Inspector-cum-Facilitator, draw up an on-site`
  line `emergency plan and detailed disaster control measures for his factory and make known to the workers`
  line `employed therein and to the general public living in the vicinity of the factory the safety measures`
  line `required to be taken in the event of an accident taking place.`
  line
  line `(5) Every occupier of a factory shall, if such factory proposes to engage in a hazardous process at any`
  line `time after the commencement of this Code, within a period of thirty days before the commencement of`
  line `such process, inform the Chief Inspector-cum-Facilitator about the nature and details of the process in`
  line `such form and in such manner as may be prescribed by the State Government.`
  line
  line `(6) Where any occupier of a factory contravenes the provisions of sub-section (5), the licence issued`
  line `under section 79 to such factory shall, notwithstanding any penalty to which the occupier of factory shall`
  line `be subjected to under the provisions of this Code, be liable for cancellation.`
  line
  line `(7) The occupier of a factory involving a hazardous process shall, with the previous approval of the`
  line `Chief Inspector-cum-Facilitator, lay down measures for the handling, usage, transportation and storage of`
  line `hazardous substances inside the factory premises and the disposal of such substances outside the factory`
  line `premises and publicise them in the manner prescribed by the State Government among the workers and`
  line `the general public living in the vicinity.`
obj_root_law_sections_84_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_85:
  sectionId (101752)
  sectionNo (85)
  orderNo 85
  title `Specific responsibility of the occupier in relation to hazardous processes.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_85_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_85_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013&sectionId=101752&sectionno=85&orderno=85&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013
obj_root_law_sections_85_content:
  string
  line `Every occupier of a`
  line `factory involving any hazardous process shall---`
  line
  line `(a) maintain accurate and up-to-date health records or, as the case may be, medical records, of the`
  line `workers in the factory who are exposed to any chemical, toxic or any other harmful substances which`
  line `are manufactured, stored, handled or transported and such records shall be accessible to the workers`
  line `subject to such conditions as may be prescribed by the State Government;`
  line
  line `(b) appoint persons who possess prescribed qualifications and experience in handling hazardous`
  line `substances and are competent to supervise such handling within the factory and to provide at the`
  line `working place all the necessary facilities for protecting the workers in the manner prescribed by the`
  line `State Government:`
  line
  line `Provided that where any question arises as to the qualifications and experience of a person so`
  line `appointed, the decision of the Chief Inspector-cum-Facilitator shall be final;`
  line
  line `(c) provide for medical examination of every worker---`
  line
  line `(i) before such worker is assigned to a job involving the handling of, or working with, a`
  line `hazardous substance; and`
  line
  line `(ii) while continuing in such job, and after he has ceased to work in such job, at intervals not`
  line `exceeding twelve months, in such manner as may be prescribed by the State Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_85_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_86:
  sectionId (101753)
  sectionNo (86)
  orderNo 86
  title `National Board to inquire into certain situations.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_86_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_86_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013&sectionId=101753&sectionno=86&orderno=86&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013
obj_root_law_sections_86_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, in the`
  line `event of the occurrence of an extraordinary situation involving a factory engaged in a hazardous process,`
  line `direct the National Board to inquire into the standards of health and safety observed in the factory with a`
  line `view to finding out the causes of any failure or neglect in the adoption of any measures or standards`
  line `prescribed by the State Government for the health and safety of the workers employed in the factory or`
  line `the general public affected, or likely to be affected due to such failure or neglect and for the prevention of`
  line `recurrence of such extraordinary situations in future in such factory or elsewhere.`
  line
  line `(2) The recommendations of the National Board shall be advisory in the nature.`
obj_root_law_sections_86_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_87:
  sectionId (101754)
  sectionNo (87)
  orderNo 87
  title `Emergency standards.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_87_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_87_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013&sectionId=101754&sectionno=87&orderno=87&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013
obj_root_law_sections_87_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where the Central Government is satisfied that no standards of`
  line `safety have been prescribed in respect of a hazardous process or class of hazardous processes, or where`
  line `the standards so prescribed are inadequate, it may direct the Directorate General Occupational Safety and`
  line `Health formerly known as the Directorate General of Factory Advice Service and Labour Institutes or any`
  line `Institution authorised in matters relating to standards of safety in hazardous processes, to lay down`
  line `emergency standards for enforcement of suitable standards in respect of such hazardous processes.`
  line
  line `(2) The emergency standards laid down under sub-section (1) shall, until they are incorporated in the`
  line `rules made under this Code, be enforceable and have the same effect as if they had been incorporated in`
  line `the rules made under this Code.`
obj_root_law_sections_87_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_88:
  sectionId (101755)
  sectionNo (88)
  orderNo 88
  title `Permissible limits of exposure of chemicals and toxic substances.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_88_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_88_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013&sectionId=101755&sectionno=88&orderno=88&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013
obj_root_law_sections_88_content:
  string
  line `The maximum permissible`
  line `limits of exposure of chemical and toxic substances in manufacturing process in any factory shall be of`
  line `the value as may be prescribed by the State Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_88_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_89:
  sectionId (101756)
  sectionNo (89)
  orderNo 89
  title `Right of workers to warn about imminent danger.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_89_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_89_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013&sectionId=101756&sectionno=89&orderno=89&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013
obj_root_law_sections_89_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where the workers employed in any`
  line `factory engaged in a hazardous process have reasonable apprehension that there is a likelihood of`
  line `imminent danger to their lives or health due to any accident, they may, bring the same to the notice of the`
  line `occupier, agent, manager or any other person who is in-charge of the factory or the process concerned`
  line `directly or through their representatives in the Safety Committee and simultaneously bring the same to the`
  line `notice of the Inspector-cum-Facilitator.`
  line
  line `(2) It shall be the duty of such occupier, agent, manager or the person in-charge of the factory or`
  line `process to take immediate remedial action if he is satisfied about the existence of such imminent danger`
  line `and send a report forthwith of the action taken to the Inspector-cum-Facilitator.`
  line
  line `(3) If the occupier, agent, manager or the person in-charge referred to in sub-section (2) is not satisfied`
  line `about the existence of any imminent danger as apprehended by the workers, he shall, nevertheless, refer`
  line `the matter forthwith to the Inspector-cum-Facilitator whose decision on the question of the existence of`
  line `such imminent danger shall be final.`
obj_root_law_sections_89_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_90:
  sectionId (101757)
  sectionNo (90)
  orderNo 90
  title `Appeal against the order of Inspector-cum-Facilitator in case of factory.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_90_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_90_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013&sectionId=101757&sectionno=90&orderno=90&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013
obj_root_law_sections_90_content:
  string
  line `The appropriate`
  line `Government may prescribe provisions providing the manner in which and the appropriate authority to`
  line `whom the manager or occupier of the factory may make appeal against the order of the Inspector-cum-Facilitator and the procedure for disposing of such appeals.`
obj_root_law_sections_90_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_91:
  sectionId (101758)
  sectionNo (91)
  orderNo 91
  title `Power to make rules to exempt.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_91_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_91_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013&sectionId=101758&sectionno=91&orderno=91&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013
obj_root_law_sections_91_content:
  string
  line `(1) The appropriate Government may make rules,---`
  line
  line `(a) specifying the persons who hold positions of supervision or management or are employed in a`
  line `confidential position in a factory or empowering the Chief Inspector-cum-Facilitator to declare any`
  line `person, other than a person so specified, as a person holding position of supervision or management or`
  line `employed in a confidential position in a factory if, in the opinion of the Chief Inspector-cum-Facilitator, such person holds such position or is so employed, and the provisions of this Code, shall`
  line `not apply to any person so defined or declared;`
  line
  line `(b) in respect of any worker or class of workers in any establishment or class of establishment, for`
  line `providing the exemption, extent of exemption and conditions subject to which such exemption may be`
  line given.
  line
  line `(2) The appropriate Government or the Chief Inspector-cum-Facilitator may, by order in writing,`
  line `exempt subject to such conditions as it may deem expedient, any or all of the adult workers in any`
  line `establishment or class of establishments.`
obj_root_law_sections_91_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_92:
  sectionId (101759)
  sectionNo (92)
  orderNo 92
  title `Facilities for workers in plantation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_92_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_92_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013&sectionId=101759&sectionno=92&orderno=92&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013
obj_root_law_sections_92_content:
  string
  line `(1) Without prejudice to the generality of sections 23 and`
  line `24, the State Government may prescribe requiring every employer to make provisions in his plantation`
  line for---
  line
  line `(a) necessary housing accommodation including drinking water, kitchen and toilet to every worker`
  line `employed in the plantation (including his family);`
  line
  line `(b) crèches facilities where in the plantation fifty or more workers (including workers employed by`
  line `any contractor) are employed or were employed on any day of the preceding twelve months:`
  line
  line `Provided that,---`
  line
  line `(i) an establishment may avail common crèche facility of the Central Government, State`
  line `Government, municipality or private entity or provided by non-Governmental organisation or by`
  line `any other organisation; or`
  line
  line `(ii) a group of establishments may agree to pool their resources for setting up of common`
  line crèche;
  line
  line `(c) educational facilities for the children of the workers employed in the plantation where the`
  line `children between the ages of six to twelve of the workers exceed twenty-five in number;`
  line
  line `(d) health facilities to every worker employed in the plantation (including his family) or provide`
  line `coverage under the Employees State Insurance Act, 1948 (34 of 1948); and`
  line
  line `(e) recreational facilities for the workers employed in the plantation.`
  line
  line `(2) An employer of a plantation shall be responsible to provide and maintain welfare facilities for`
  line `which the workers in the plantation are entitled under this Code either from his own resources or through`
  line `the schemes of the Central Government or State Government, Municipality or Panchayat for the locality`
  line `in which the plantation is situated.`
  line
  line `Explanation.---For the purposes of this sub-section---`
  line
  line `(i) the expression "Municipality" has the same meaning as assigned to it in clause (e) of article 243`
  line `of the Constitution; and`
  line
  line `(ii) the expression "Panchayat" has the same meaning as assigned to it in clause (d) of article 243`
  line `of the Constitution.`
obj_root_law_sections_92_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_93:
  sectionId (101760)
  sectionNo (93)
  orderNo 93
  title Safety.
  content obj_root_law_sections_93_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_93_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013&sectionId=101760&sectionno=93&orderno=93&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013
obj_root_law_sections_93_content:
  string
  line `(1) In every plantation, arrangement shall be made by the employer to provide for the`
  line `safety of a worker in connection with the use, handling, storage and transport of insecticides, pesticides`
  line `and chemicals and toxic substances.`
  line
  line `(2) The State Government may prescribe for special safeguards for employment of women or`
  line `adolescents in using or handling hazardous chemicals.`
  line
  line `(3) The employer of a plantation shall appoint persons possessing the prescribed qualifications to`
  line `supervise the use, handling, storage and transportation of insecticides, chemicals and toxic substances in`
  line `his plantation.`
  line
  line `(4) Every employer of a plantation shall ensure that every worker in plantation employed for handling,`
  line `mixing, blending and applying insecticides, chemicals and toxic substances, is trained about the hazards`
  line `involved in different operations in which he is engaged, the various safety measures and safe work`
  line `practices to be adopted in emergencies arising from spillage of such insecticides, chemicals and toxic`
  line `substances and such other matters as may be prescribed by the State Government.`
  line
  line `(5) Every worker in a plantation who is exposed to insecticides, pesticides, chemicals and toxic`
  line `substances shall be medically examined periodically, in such manner as may be prescribed by the State`
  line Government.
  line
  line `(6) Every employer of a plantation shall maintain health record of every worker in plantation who is`
  line `exposed to insecticides, pesticides, chemicals and toxic substances which are used, handled, stored or`
  line `transported in a plantation, and every such worker shall have access to such record.`
  line
  line `(7) Every employer of a plantation shall provide---`
  line
  line `(a) washing, bathing and clock room facilities; and`
  line
  line `(b) protective clothing and equipment,`
  line
  line `to every worker engaged in the handling insecticides, pesticides, chemicals and toxic substances in such`
  line `manner as may be prescribed by the State Government.`
  line
  line `(8) Every employer of a plantation shall display in the plantation, a list of permissible concentrations`
  line `of insecticides, pesticides, chemicals and toxic substances in the breathing zone of the workers engaged in`
  line `the handling and application of insecticides, pesticides, chemicals and toxic substances in the plantation.`
  line
  line `(9) Every employer of a plantation shall exhibit such precautionary notices in the plantation as may be`
  line `prescribed by the State Government indicating the hazards of insecticides, pesticides, chemicals and toxic`
  line substances.
obj_root_law_sections_93_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_94:
  sectionId (101761)
  sectionNo (94)
  orderNo 94
  title `General penalty for offences.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_94_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_94_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013&sectionId=101761&sectionno=94&orderno=94&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013
obj_root_law_sections_94_content:
  string
  line `Save as otherwise expressly provided in this Code, if in, or in`
  line `respect of, any establishment, there is any contravention of the provisions of this Code or regulations or`
  line `rules, or bye-laws or any of standards, made thereunder or of any order in writing given under this Code`
  line `or such regulations or rules or bye-laws or standards, the employer or the principal employer of the`
  line `establishment, as the case may be, shall be liable to penalty which shall not be less than two lakhs rupees`
  line 55
  line `but which may extend up to three lakh rupees, and if the contravention is continued after the conviction,`
  line `then, with further penalty which may extend to two thousand rupees for each day till such contravention`
  line continues.
obj_root_law_sections_94_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_95:
  sectionId (102030)
  sectionNo (95)
  orderNo 95
  title `Punishment for causing obstruction to Chief Inspector-cum-Facilitator or Inspector-cumFacilitator, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_95_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_95_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013&sectionId=102030&sectionno=95&orderno=95&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013
obj_root_law_sections_95_content:
  string
  line `(1) Whoever wilfully---`
  line
  line `(i) prevents or causes obstruction to a Chief Inspector-cum-Facilitator or Inspector-cum-Facilitator`
  line `or an officer of the appropriate Government or a person authorised to discharge any duty or to exercise`
  line `any powers under this Code or the rules or the regulations or the bye-laws made thereunder, from`
  line `discharging such duty or exercising such power; or`
  line
  line `(ii) refuses entry to the Chief Inspector-cum-Facilitator or the Inspector-cum-Facilitator or person`
  line `or public authority referred to in clause (i) of sub-section (1) of section 35 or expert referred to in`
  line `section 37, to any place where such Chief Inspector-cum-Facilitator or Inspector-cum-Facilitator or`
  line `such person or authority or expert is entitled to enter; or`
  line
  line `(iii) fails or refuses to produce any document which he is required to produce; or`
  line
  line `(iv) fails to comply with any requisition or order issued to him,`
  line `under this Code or the rules, regulations or bye-laws made thereunder he shall be punishable with`
  line `imprisonment for a term which may extend to three months, or with fine which may extend to one lakh`
  line `rupees, or with both.`
  line
  line `(2) Where any person convicted of an offence punishable under sub-section (1) is again convicted of`
  line `an offence under the same provision, then, he shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term which`
  line `may extend to six months, or with fine which shall not be less than one lakh rupees but which may extend`
  line `to two lakh rupees, or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_95_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_96:
  sectionId (101763)
  sectionNo (96)
  orderNo 96
  title `Penalty for non-maintenance of register, records and non-filing of returns, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_96_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_96_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013&sectionId=101763&sectionno=96&orderno=96&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013
obj_root_law_sections_96_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any`
  line `person, who is required under this Code or the rules or regulations or bye-laws or order made thereunder,`
  line to---
  line
  line `(i) maintain any register or other document or to file returns, omits or fails to maintain such register`
  line `or document or to file such returns; or`
  line
  line `(ii) produce any register or plan or record or report or any other document, omits or fails to produce`
  line `such register or plan or record or report or such other document,`
  line
  line `he shall be liable to penalty which shall not be less than fifty thousand rupees but which may extend to`
  line `one lakh rupees.`
  line
  line `(2) Where any person convicted of an offence punishable under sub-section (1) is again convicted of`
  line `an offence under the same provision, then, he shall be liable to penalty which shall not be less than fifty`
  line `thousand rupees but which may extend to two lakh rupees.`
obj_root_law_sections_96_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_97:
  sectionId (101764)
  sectionNo (97)
  orderNo 97
  title `Punishment for contravention of certain provisions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_97_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_97_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013&sectionId=101764&sectionno=97&orderno=97&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013
obj_root_law_sections_97_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any person, who, save as permitted`
  line `by or under this Code, contravenes, any---`
  line
  line `(i) provision of this Code or of any rule, regulation or bye-laws; or`
  line
  line `(ii) order made under this Code prohibiting, restricting or regulating the employment of workers`
  line `including women, audio-visual worker and contract labour and employee below eighteen years of age`
  line `in case of mines,`
  line
  line `he shall be liable to penalty which shall not be less than fifty thousand rupees but which may extend to`
  line `one lakh rupees.`
  line
  line `(2) Where any person convicted of an offence punishable under sub-section (1) is again convicted of`
  line `an offence under the same provision, then, he shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term which`
  line `may extend to three months, or with fine which may extend to two lakh rupees, or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_97_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_98:
  sectionId (101765)
  sectionNo (98)
  orderNo 98
  title `Punishment for falsification of records, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_98_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_98_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013&sectionId=101765&sectionno=98&orderno=98&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013
obj_root_law_sections_98_content:
  string
  line `(1) Whoever---`
  line
  line `(a) produces false records or counterfeits or knowingly makes or produces or uses a false`
  line `statement, declaration or evidence regarding any document in connection with compliance of any of`
  line `the provisions of this Code or any rules, regulations or bye-laws or any order made thereunder; or`
  line
  line `(b) falsifies any plan or section, the maintenance of which is required by or under this Code or`
  line `produces before any authority such plan or section, knowing the same to be false; or`
  line
  line `(c) makes, gives or delivers knowingly a false plan, section, return, notice, record or report`
  line `containing a statement, entry or detail,`
  line
  line `he shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term which may extend to three months, or with fine`
  line `which may extend to one lakh rupees, or with both.`
  line
  line `(2) Where any person convicted of an offence punishable under sub-section (1) is again convicted of`
  line `an offence under the same provision, then, he shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term which`
  line `may extend to six months, or with fine which shall not be less than one lakh rupees but which may extend`
  line `to two lakh rupees, or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_98_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_99:
  sectionId (101766)
  sectionNo (99)
  orderNo 99
  title `Penalty for omission to furnish plans, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_99_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_99_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013&sectionId=101766&sectionno=99&orderno=99&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013
obj_root_law_sections_99_content:
  string
  line `Any person who, without reasonable excuse the`
  line `burden of proving which shall lies upon him, omits to make or furnish in the prescribed form or manner`
  line `or at, or within, the prescribed time any plan, section, return, notice, register, record or report required by`
  line `or under any provision of this Code to be made or furnished, he shall be liable to penalty which shall not`
  line `be less than one lakh rupees but which may extend to two lakh rupees.`
obj_root_law_sections_99_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_100:
  sectionId (101767)
  sectionNo (100)
  orderNo 100
  title `Punishment for disclosure of information.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_100_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_100_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013&sectionId=101767&sectionno=100&orderno=100&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013
obj_root_law_sections_100_content:
  string
  line `(1) Whoever being the Chief Inspector-cumFacilitator or Inspector-cum-Facilitator or any other person referred to in section 39 or section 121`
  line `discloses, contrary to the provisions of that section, any such information as is referred to in that section`
  line `without the consent of the appropriate Government, he shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term`
  line `which may extend to three months, or with fine which may extend to one lakh rupees, or with both.`
  line
  line `(2) No court shall proceed with the trial of any offence under this section except with the previous`
  line `sanction of the appropriate Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_100_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_101:
  sectionId (101768)
  sectionNo (101)
  orderNo 101
  title `Punishment for wrongfully disclosing results of analysis.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_101_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_101_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013&sectionId=101768&sectionno=101&orderno=101&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013
obj_root_law_sections_101_content:
  string
  line `Whoever, except in so far as it may`
  line `be necessary for the purposes of a prosecution for any offence punishable under this Code, publishes or`
  line `discloses to any person the results of an analysis, of a sample of substance used or intended to be used in`
  line `any process under this Code, shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term, which may extend to six`
  line `months, or with fine, which may extend to fifty thousand rupees, or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_101_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_102:
  sectionId (101769)
  sectionNo (102)
  orderNo 102
  title `Punishment for contravention of provisions of duties relating to hazardous processes.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_102_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_102_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013&sectionId=101769&sectionno=102&orderno=102&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013
obj_root_law_sections_102_content:
  string
  line `(1)`
  line `Whoever fails to comply with or contravenes any of his duties specified under---`
  line
  line `(i) clauses (a) to (h) of sub-section (1) or sub-section (2) of section 6 or clause (d) of section 13 in`
  line `so far as such duty relates to hazardous processes; or`
  line
  line `(ii) section 80,`
  line
  line `shall, in respect of such failure or contravention, be punishable with an imprisonment for a term which`
  line `may extend to two years and with fine which may extend to five lakh rupees, and in case the failure or`
  line `contravention continues, with additional fine which may extend to twenty-five thousand rupees for every`
  line `day during which such failure or contravention continues, after the conviction for the first such failure or`
  line contravention.
  line
  line `(2) If the failure or contravention referred to in sub-section (1) continues beyond a period of one year`
  line `after the date of conviction, the offender shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term which may`
  line `extend to three years or with a fine of twenty lakh rupees, or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_102_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_103:
  sectionId (102031)
  sectionNo (103)
  orderNo 103
  title `Punishment for contravention of provisions of duties relating to safety provisions resulting in an accident.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_103_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_103_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013&sectionId=102031&sectionno=103&orderno=103&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013
obj_root_law_sections_103_content:
  string
  line `(1) If a person fails to comply with or contravenes any duties under this Code or the`
  line `regulations, rules, bye-laws or orders made there under and such non-compliance or contravention has`
  line `resulted in an accident or dangerous occurrences causing---`
  line
  line `(a) death, he shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term which may extend to two years, or`
  line `with a fine which shall not be less than five lakh rupees, or with both; or`
  line
  line `(b) serious bodily injury to any person within the establishment, he shall be punishable with`
  line `imprisonment for a term which may extend to one year, or with a fine which shall not be less than two`
  line `lakh rupees but not exceeding four lakh rupees, or with both:`
  line
  line `Provided that while imposing the fine under this section, the court may direct that a portion of the fine,`
  line `which shall not be less than fifty per cent. thereof, shall be given as compensation to the victim or to the`
  line `legal heirs of the victim, in the case of his death.`
  line
  line `(2) Where a person having been convicted under sub-section (1) is again convicted there under, shall`
  line `be punishable with double the punishment provided under that sub-section for first conviction.`
obj_root_law_sections_103_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_104:
  sectionId (101771)
  sectionNo (104)
  orderNo 104
  title `Special provision for contravention of order under section 38.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_104_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_104_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013&sectionId=101771&sectionno=104&orderno=104&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013
obj_root_law_sections_104_content:
  string
  line `Whoever continues to work`
  line `in contravention of any general or special order issued under the provisions of section 38, shall be`
  line `punishable with imprisonment for a term which may extend to two years and shall also be liable to fine`
  line `which may extend to five lakh rupees:`
  line
  line `Provided that the court shall not impose a fine under this section which shall be less than two lakh`
  line `rupees without recording in the judgment the reasons for imposing such fine.`
obj_root_law_sections_104_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_105:
  sectionId (101772)
  sectionNo (105)
  orderNo 105
  title `Failure to appoint manager in mine.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_105_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_105_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013&sectionId=101772&sectionno=105&orderno=105&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013
obj_root_law_sections_105_content:
  string
  line `Whoever in compliance of the provisions of section 67,`
  line `fails to appoint a manager shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term which may extend to three`
  line `months, or with fine which may extend to one lakh rupees, or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_105_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_106:
  sectionId (101773)
  sectionNo (106)
  orderNo 106
  title `Offences by employees.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_106_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_106_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013&sectionId=101773&sectionno=106&orderno=106&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013
obj_root_law_sections_106_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to the provisions of section 13, except clause (d) thereof, if`
  line `any employee employed in a workplace contravenes any provision of this Code or any rules or orders`
  line `made there under, imposing any duty or liability on employee, he shall be punishable with penalty which`
  line `may extend to ten thousand rupees.`
  line
  line `(2) Where an employee is convicted of an offence punishable under sub-section (1), the employer of`
  line `the establishment shall not be deemed to be guilty of an offence in respect of that contravention, unless it`
  line `is proved that he failed to take all reasonable measures for its prevention.`
obj_root_law_sections_106_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_107:
  sectionId (101774)
  sectionNo (107)
  orderNo 107
  title `Prosecution of owner, agent or manager of mine.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_107_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_107_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013&sectionId=101774&sectionno=107&orderno=107&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013
obj_root_law_sections_107_content:
  string
  line `No prosecution shall be instituted against`
  line `any owner, agent or manager of a mine for any offence under this Code except at the instance of the Chief`
  line `Inspector-cum-Facilitator or of the District Magistrate or of Inspector-cum-Facilitator authorised in this`
  line `behalf by general or special order in writing by the Chief Inspector-cum-Facilitator:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Chief Inspector-cum-Facilitator or the District Magistrate or the Inspector-cum-Facilitator as so authorised shall before instituting such prosecution satisfy himself that the owner, agent`
  line `or manager of a mine had failed to exercise due diligence to prevent the commission of such offence:`
  line
  line `Provided further that in respect of an offence committed in the course of the technical direction and`
  line `management of a mine, the District Magistrate shall not institute any prosecution against an owner, agent`
  line `or manager of a mine without the previous approval of the Chief Inspector-cum-Facilitator.`
obj_root_law_sections_107_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_108:
  sectionId (102032)
  sectionNo (108)
  orderNo 108
  title `Exemption of owner, agent or manager of mine or occupier of factory from liability in certain cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_108_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_108_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013&sectionId=102032&sectionno=108&orderno=108&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013
obj_root_law_sections_108_content:
  string
  line `Where the owner, agent or manager of the mine or employer or occupier of the factory is`
  line `charged with an offence punishable under this Code he shall be entitled, upon complaint duly made by`
  line `him and on giving to the prosecutor not less than three clear days' notice in writing of his intention so to`
  line `do, to have any other person whom he charges as the actual offender brought before the Court at the time`
  line `appointed for hearing the charge; and if, after the commission of the offence has been proved, the owner,`
  line `agent or manager of the mine or occupier or manager of the factory, as the case may be, proves to the`
  line `satisfaction of the Court---`
  line
  line `(a) that he has exercised due diligence to enforce the execution of this Code, or`
  line
  line `(b) that the said other person committed the offence in question without his knowledge, consent or`
  line connivance,
  line
  line `that other person shall be convicted of the offence and shall be liable to the like punishment as if he was`
  line `the owner, agent or manager of the mine or occupier or manager of the factory, as the case may be, and`
  line `the owner, agent or manager of a mine or the occupier or the manager of the factory shall be, discharged`
  line `from any liability under this Code in respect of such offence:`
  line
  line `Provided that in seeking to prove as aforesaid the owner, agent or manager of a mine or the occupier`
  line `or manager of the factory, as the case may be, may be examined on oath, and his evidence and that of any`
  line `witness whom he calls in his support, shall be subject to cross-examination on behalf of the person he`
  line `charges as the actual offender and by the prosecutor:`
  line
  line `Provided further that, if the person charged as the actual offender by the owner, agent or manager of`
  line `the mine or occupier or manager of the factory, as the case may be, cannot be brought before the court at`
  line `the time appointed for hearing the charge, the court shall adjourn the hearing from time to time for a`
  line `period not exceeding three months and if by the end of the said period the person charged as the actual`
  line `offender cannot still be brought before the court, the court shall proceed to hear the charge against the`
  line `owner, agent or manager of the mine or occupier or manager of the factory, as the case may be, and shall,`
  line `if the offence be proved, convict him.`
obj_root_law_sections_108_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_109:
  sectionId (101776)
  sectionNo (109)
  orderNo 109
  title `Offences by companies, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_109_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_109_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013&sectionId=101776&sectionno=109&orderno=109&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013
obj_root_law_sections_109_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where an offence under this Code has been committed by a`
  line `company, every person who, at the time the offence was committed, was in charge of, and was`
  line `responsible to, the company for the conduct of the business of the company, as well as the company, shall`
  line `be deemed to be guilty of the offence and shall be liable to be proceeded against and punished`
  line `accordingly:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing contained in this sub-section shall render any such person liable to any`
  line `punishment, if he proves that the offence was committed without his knowledge or that he had exercised`
  line `all due diligence to prevent the commission of such offence.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1) where any offence under this Code has been`
  line `committed by a company and it is proved that the offence has been committed with the consent or`
  line `connivance of, or is attributable to any neglect on the part of any director, manager, company secretary or`
  line `other officer of the company, such director, manager, company secretary or other officer shall be deemed`
  line `to be guilty of that offence and shall be liable to be proceeded against and punished accordingly.`
  line
  line `Explanation. --- For the purposes of this section,---`
  line
  line `(a) "company" means any body corporate and includes a firm or other association of individuals;`
  line and
  line
  line `(b) "director" means,---`
  line
  line `(i) in relation to a firm a partner thereof; or`
  line
  line `(ii) the owner of a mine being a firm or other association of individuals or a company; or`
  line
  line `(iii) in case of association of individuals other than specified in sub-clause (ii), any of its`
  line members.
obj_root_law_sections_109_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_110:
  sectionId (101777)
  sectionNo (110)
  orderNo 110
  title `Limitation of prosecution and cognizance of offences.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_110_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_110_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013&sectionId=101777&sectionno=110&orderno=110&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013
obj_root_law_sections_110_content:
  string
  line `(1) Notwithstanding anything`
  line `contained in this Chapter, the Inspector-cum-Facilitator shall, not initiate prosecution proceeding against`
  line `an employer for any offence under this Chapter, give an opportunity to comply with relevant provisions`
  line `of this Act within a period of thirty days from the date of notice giving opportunity, and, if the employer`
  line `complies with such provisions within such period, then, no such proceeding shall be initiated against such`
  line `employer:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such opportunity shall be accorded to an employer in case of an accident and if the`
  line `violation of the same nature of the provisions under this Code is repeated within a period of three years`
  line `from the date on which such first violation was committed and in such case the prosecution shall be`
  line `initiated in accordance with provisions of sub-section (2).`
  line
  line `(2) No court shall take cognizance of any offence punishable under this Code, unless a complaint in`
  line `respect thereof is made within six months of the date on which the alleged commission of the offence`
  line `came to the knowledge of the Inspector-cum-Facilitator and a complaint is filed in that regard by him.`
  line
  line `(3) No court inferior to that of a Metropolitan Magistrate or a Judicial Magistrate of the First Class`
  line `shall try any offence punishable under this Code.`
  line
  line `Explanation.---For the purposes of this section,---`
  line
  line `(a) in the case of a continuing offence, the period of limitation shall be computed with reference to`
  line `every point of time during which the offence continues;`
  line
  line `(b) where for the performance of any act, time is granted or extended on an application made by the`
  line `employer of an establishment, the period of limitation shall be computed from the date on which the`
  line `time so granted or extended expired.`
obj_root_law_sections_110_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_111:
  sectionId (101778)
  sectionNo (111)
  orderNo 111
  title `Power of officers of appropriate Government to impose penalty in certain cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_111_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_111_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013&sectionId=101778&sectionno=111&orderno=111&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013
obj_root_law_sections_111_content:
  string
  line `(1)`
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained in section 110, for the purpose of imposing penalty under`
  line `sub-section (3) of section 12 or sections 94, 96, 97, 99, 106 and sub-section (3) of section 114, the`
  line `appropriate Government may appoint any officer not below the rank of Under Secretary to the`
  line `Government of India or an officer of equivalent rank in the State Government, as the case may be, for`
  line `holding enquiry in such manner, as may be prescribed by the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(2) While holding the enquiry, the officer referred to in sub-section (1) shall have the power to`
  line `summon and enforce attendance of any person acquainted with the facts and circumstances of the case to`
  line `give evidence or to produce any document, which in the opinion of such officer, may be useful for or`
  line `relevant to the subject-matter of the enquiry and if, on such enquiry, he is satisfied that the person has`
  line `committed any offence under the provisions referred to in sub-section (1), he may impose such penalty as`
  line `he thinks fit in accordance with the provisions of that sub-section.`
  line
  line `(3) Any person aggrieved by an order made by the officer under sub-section (2) may prefer an appeal,`
  line `in such form and manner and accompanied by such fee as may be prescribed, to the appellate authority to`
  line `be appointed by the appropriate Government from amongst officers not below the rank of Deputy`
  line `Secretary to the Government of India or an officer of equivalent rank in the State Government, as the case`
  line `may be, within sixty days from the date on which the copy of the order made by the officer referred in`
  line `sub-section (1) is received by the aggrieved person.`
  line
  line `(4) The appellate authority may, after giving the parties to the appeal an opportunity of being heard,`
  line `pass such order as he thinks fit, confirming, modifying or setting aside the order appealed against, within`
  line `a period of sixty days from the date of receipt of appeal.`
  line
  line `(5) Where a person fails to pay the penalty so imposed within a period of ninety days from the date of`
  line `receipt of the copy of the order, he shall be punishable with fine which shall not be less than twenty-five`
  line `thousand rupees but which may extend up to two lakh rupees.`
  line
  line `(6) The amount of penalty imposed and received under this section shall be credited to the fund`
  line `established under sub-section (1) of section 115.`
obj_root_law_sections_111_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_112:
  sectionId (101779)
  sectionNo (112)
  orderNo 112
  title `Jurisdiction of court for entertaining proceedings, etc., for offence.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_112_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_112_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013&sectionId=101779&sectionno=112&orderno=112&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013
obj_root_law_sections_112_content:
  string
  line `For the purposes of`
  line `conferring jurisdiction on any court in relation to an offence under this Code or the rules, regulation or`
  line `bye-laws made there under in connection with an establishment, the place where the establishment is for`
  line `the time being situated, shall be deemed to be the place where such offence has been committed.`
obj_root_law_sections_112_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_113:
  sectionId (101780)
  sectionNo (113)
  orderNo 113
  title `Power of court to make orders.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_113_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_113_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013&sectionId=101780&sectionno=113&orderno=113&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013
obj_root_law_sections_113_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where the employer of a mine or a factory or a dock is`
  line `convicted of an offence punishable under this Code, the court may, in addition to awarding him any`
  line `punishment, by order in writing, require him within the period specified in the order (which may be`
  line `extended by the court from time to time on application made in this behalf) to take such measures as may`
  line `be specified in the order for remedying the matters in respect of which the offence was committed.`
  line
  line `(2) Where an order is made under sub-section (1), the employer of the mine or the factory shall not be`
  line `liable under this Code in respect of the continuance of the offence during the period or extended period, if`
  line `any, but if on the expiry of such period or extended period the order of the court has not been fully`
  line `complied with, employer shall be deemed to have committed a further offence and shall be punishable`
  line `with imprisonment for a term which may extend to six months, or with fine which may extend to one`
  line `hundred rupees for every day after such expiry on which the order has not been complied with, or with`
  line both.
obj_root_law_sections_113_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_114:
  sectionId (101781)
  sectionNo (114)
  orderNo 114
  title `Composition of certain offences.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_114_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_114_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013&sectionId=101781&sectionno=114&orderno=114&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013
obj_root_law_sections_114_content:
  string
  line `(1) Notwithstanding anything contained in the Code of`
  line `Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974), any penalty under sub-section (3) of section 12 or section`
  line `94 or section 96 or sub-section (1) of section 97 or section 99 or section 106 or sub-section (3) or any`
  line `offence under sub-section (2) of section 97 or sub-section (1) of section 100 or section 101 or clause (b)`
  line `of sub-section (1) of section 103 or section 105 or sub-section (2) of section 113 may either before or`
  line `after the holding the enquiry or, as the case may be, of institution of prosecution may be compounded by`
  line `such officer of the appropriate Government as may be notified by that Government in the manner as may`
  line `be prescribed by it---`
  line
  line `(a) in a case of penalty for a sum of fifty per cent. of the maximum penalty provided for such`
  line `penalty; and`
  line
  line `(b) in a case of offence for a sum of seventy-five per cent. of the maximum fine provided for such`
  line offence.
  line
  line `(2) Where a penalty or an offence has been compounded under sub-section (1), the person liable for`
  line `penalty or the offender, as the case may be, shall be discharged of the penalty or offence and there shall`
  line `be no further proceedings against him in respect of such penalty or offence.`
  line
  line `(3) Any person who fails to comply with an order made by the officer referred to in sub-section (1),`
  line `shall be liable to pay a penalty equivalent to twenty per cent. of the maximum penalty or fine provided for`
  line `the penalty or the offence, as the case may be, in addition to the penalty or fine.`
  line
  line `(4) The amount of composition received under sub-section (1) shall be credited to the fund established`
  line `under sub-section (1) of section 115 for the unorganised workers.`
  line
  line `(5) Nothing contained in sub-section (1) shall apply to a penalty or an offence committed by a person`
  line `for a second or subsequent time within a period of three years from the date of penalty or offence, as the`
  line `case may be,---`
  line
  line `(a) which was earlier compounded; or`
  line
  line `(b) for which such person was earlier convicted.`
obj_root_law_sections_114_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_115:
  sectionId (101782)
  sectionNo (115)
  orderNo 115
  title `Social security fund.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_115_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_115_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013&sectionId=101782&sectionno=115&orderno=115&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013
obj_root_law_sections_115_content:
  string
  line `(1) There shall be established by the appropriate Government a social`
  line `security fund for the welfare of the unorganised workers to which there shall be credited the amount`
  line `received from composition of the offence as specified in sub-section (4) of section 114 and the amount of`
  line `the penalty as specified in sub-section (6) of section 111.`
  line
  line `(2) The fund may also be funded by such other sources as may be prescribed by the appropriate`
  line Government.
  line
  line `(3) The fund shall be administered and expended for welfare of the unorganised workers in such`
  line `manner as may be prescribed by the appropriate Government including the transfer of the amount in the`
  line `fund to any fund established under any other law for the time being in force for the welfare of the`
  line `unorganised workers.`
  line
  line `Explanation.---For the purpose of this section the expression "unorganised worker" shall have the`
  line `same meaning as is assigned to it under clause (m) of section 2 of the Unorganised Workers Social`
  line `Security Act, 2008 (33 of 2008).`
obj_root_law_sections_115_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_116:
  sectionId (101783)
  sectionNo (116)
  orderNo 116
  title `Delegation of powers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_116_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_116_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013&sectionId=101783&sectionno=116&orderno=116&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013
obj_root_law_sections_116_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government may, by notification, direct that any power`
  line `exercisable by it under this Code or rules made there under shall, in relation to such matters and subject to`
  line `such conditions, if any, as may be specified in the notification, be exercisable also by the State`
  line `Government or by such officer or authority subordinate to the State Government as may be specified in`
  line `the said notification.`
obj_root_law_sections_116_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_117:
  sectionId (101784)
  sectionNo (117)
  orderNo 117
  title `Onus as to age.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_117_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_117_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013&sectionId=101784&sectionno=117&orderno=117&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013
obj_root_law_sections_117_content:
  string
  line `(1) When any offence is committed under this Code involving an issue of a`
  line `certain age of a person and such person is in the opinion of the court prima facie under such age, the`
  line `burden shall be on the accused to prove that such person is not under such age.`
  line
  line `(2) The medical authority prescribed by the Central Government shall, while examining a worker for`
  line `issuing the certificate of age for the purposes of this Code, take into account the Aadhaar card of the`
  line `worker, and in the absence thereof, the date of birth certificate from school or the matriculation or`
  line `equivalent certificate from the concerned examination Board of the worker, if available, and in the`
  line `absence thereof, the birth certificate of the worker given by a corporation or a municipal authority or a`
  line `Panchayat, and only in the absence of any of the methods specified in this sub-section, the age shall be`
  line `determined by such medical authority through an ossification test or any other latest medical age`
  line `determination test.`
obj_root_law_sections_117_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_118:
  sectionId (101785)
  sectionNo (118)
  orderNo 118
  title `Onus of proving limits of what is practicable, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_118_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_118_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013&sectionId=101785&sectionno=118&orderno=118&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013
obj_root_law_sections_118_content:
  string
  line `In any proceeding for an offence for the`
  line `contravention of any provision of this Code or regulations or bye-laws or rules made there under`
  line `consisting of a failure to comply with a duty or requirement to do something, it shall be for the person`
  line `who is alleged to have failed to comply with such duty or requirement, to prove that it was not reasonably`
  line `practicable or all practicable measures were taken to satisfy the duty or requirement.`
obj_root_law_sections_118_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_119:
  sectionId (101786)
  sectionNo (119)
  orderNo 119
  title `Common licence for contractor, factories and to industrial premises, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_119_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_119_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013&sectionId=101786&sectionno=119&orderno=119&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013
obj_root_law_sections_119_content:
  string
  line `(1)`
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained in this Code, any person desirous of obtaining common licence in`
  line `respect of a factory, industrial premises for beedi and cigar work and for engaging contract workers or`
  line `any combination thereof or single licence for any one of them under this Code shall make an application`
  line `electronically or otherwise to such authority as may be designated, by notification, by the appropriate`
  line Government.
  line
  line `(2) The application under sub-section (1),---`
  line
  line `(a) shall be in such form and filed in such manner and accompanied by such fee and contain such`
  line `information as may be prescribed by the appropriate Government;`
  line
  line `(b) shall, in so far as it relates to the licence for engaging contract labours, contain the number of`
  line `inter-State migrant workers employed.`
  line
  line `(3) On receipt of an application under sub-section (1), the authority referred to in that sub-section shall`
  line `take such actions in such manner and make such inquiry as may be prescribed by the appropriate`
  line Government.
  line
  line `(4) Where the authority referred to in sub-section (1) is satisfied that the common licence may be`
  line `issued in respect of a factory, industrial premises for beedi and cigar work and for engaging contract`
  line `workers or any combination thereof or single licence for any one of them under this Code, such authority`
  line `shall issue a licence electronically within forty-five days of the receipt of application failing which the`
  line `licence shall be deemed to be issued and shall be auto generated and the responsibility of such failure`
  line `shall be on such authority:`
  line
  line `Provided that where the licence is deemed to be issued, no further inquiry shall be made:`
  line
  line `Provided further that the form of licence shall, as far as practicable, be similar throughout India:`
  line
  line `Provided also that where such authority rejects the application he shall assign the reason for such`
  line rejection.
  line
  line `(5) Notwithstanding anything contained in this Code, any licence in respect of a factory, industrial`
  line `premises for beedi and cigar work and for engaging contract labour has been obtained under any Central`
  line `labour law before the commencement of this Code, in respect of any establishment shall be deemed to`
  line `have been obtained under the provisions of this Code and shall be valid for the period for which it was`
  line `issued and shall have to be obtained afresh after its expiration.`
  line
  line `(6) Any person aggrieved by an order passed under this section by the authority referred to in`
  line `sub-section (1) may file, within thirty days from the date of the order, an appeal in such form,`
  line `accompanied with such fee to such appellate authority as may be prescribed by the appropriate`
  line `Government and the appeal shall be disposed of electronically within thirty days of the filing of the`
  line appeal.
obj_root_law_sections_119_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_120:
  sectionId (101787)
  sectionNo (120)
  orderNo 120
  title `Effect of law and agreements inconsistent with Code.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_120_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_120_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013&sectionId=101787&sectionno=120&orderno=120&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013
obj_root_law_sections_120_content:
  string
  line `(1) The provisions of this Code shall`
  line `have effect notwithstanding anything inconsistent therewith contained in any other law for the time being`
  line `in force or in the terms of any award, agreement or contract of service whether made before or after the`
  line `commencement of this Code:`
  line
  line `Provided that where under any such award, agreement, contract of service or otherwise an employee is`
  line `entitled to benefits in respect of any matters which are more favourable to him than those to which he will`
  line `be entitled to under this Code, the employee shall continue to get the former notwithstanding that he`
  line `receives benefits in respect of other matters under this Code.`
  line
  line `(2) Nothing contained in this Code shall be construed as precluding any employee from entering into`
  line `an agreement with an employer for granting him rights or privileges in respect of any matter which are`
  line `more favourable to him than those to which he would be entitled under this Code.`
obj_root_law_sections_120_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_121:
  sectionId (101788)
  sectionNo (121)
  orderNo 121
  title `Power of appropriate Government to direct inquiry in certain cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_121_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_121_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013&sectionId=101788&sectionno=121&orderno=121&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013
obj_root_law_sections_121_content:
  string
  line `(1) The appropriate`
  line `Government may, in the event of the occurrence of an accident in an establishment which has caused or`
  line `had the potentiality to cause serious danger to employees and other persons within, and in the vicinity of`
  line `the workplace or whether immediate or delayed, or any occupational disease as specified in the Third`
  line `Schedule, which has been or is suspected to have been contracted, in epidemic proportions, appoint one or`
  line `more persons possessing legal or special knowledge to act as assessors or competent persons in such`
  line `inquiry in order to inquire into the causes of the accident and disease, fix responsibilities and suggest a`
  line `plan of action for the future to prevent such accidents or diseases and submit the report to the appropriate`
  line Government.
  line
  line `(2) The appropriate Government may direct a Chief Inspector-cum-Facilitator or any other officer`
  line `under the control of the Government concerned or appoint a committee to undertake a survey in such`
  line `manner as may be prescribed by the appropriate Government on the situation relating to safety or health`
  line `at work at any workplace or class of workplaces or into the effect of work activity on the health of the`
  line `employees and other persons within and in the vicinity of the workplace.`
  line
  line `(3) The officer directed or committee appointed, under sub-section (1) or sub-section (2), to hold an`
  line `inquiry, shall have the powers of a civil court under the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908), for the`
  line `purposes of enforcing the attendance of witnesses and compelling the production of documents and`
  line `material objects, and may also so far as may be necessary for the purposes of the inquiry, exercise such`
  line `powers of an Inspector-cum-Facilitator under this Code as may be necessary.`
  line
  line `(4) The Central Government may make rules for regulating the procedure of inquiry and survey and`
  line `other related matters under this section.`
obj_root_law_sections_121_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_122:
  sectionId (101789)
  sectionNo (122)
  orderNo 122
  title `Publication of reports.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_122_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_122_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013&sectionId=101789&sectionno=122&orderno=122&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013
obj_root_law_sections_122_content:
  string
  line `The appropriate Government may, if it thinks fit, cause to be published`
  line `any report submitted to it by the National Board or State Advisory Board or any extracts from any report`
  line `submitted to it under this Code.`
obj_root_law_sections_122_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_123:
  sectionId (101790)
  sectionNo (123)
  orderNo 123
  title `Powers of Central Government to give directions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_123_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_123_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013&sectionId=101790&sectionno=123&orderno=123&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013
obj_root_law_sections_123_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government may give`
  line `directions to a State Government for the implementation of the provisions of this Code.`
obj_root_law_sections_123_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_124:
  sectionId (101791)
  sectionNo (124)
  orderNo 124
  title `General restriction on disclosure of information.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_124_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_124_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013&sectionId=101791&sectionno=124&orderno=124&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013
obj_root_law_sections_124_content:
  string
  line `(1) No person shall in respect of the`
  line `establishment, disclose any information relating to any manufacturing or commercial business or any`
  line `working process which may come to his knowledge in the course of his official duties.`
  line
  line `(2) Nothing in sub-section (1) shall apply to any disclosure of information made with the previous`
  line `consent in writing of the owner of the business or process or for the purposes of any legal proceeding`
  line `(including adjudication or arbitration), pursuant to any of the relevant statutory provisions or of any`
  line `criminal proceeding under this Code which may be taken, whether pursuant to any of the relevant`
  line `statutory provisions or otherwise, or for the purposes of any report of any such proceedings.`
obj_root_law_sections_124_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_125:
  sectionId (101792)
  sectionNo (125)
  orderNo 125
  title `Jurisdiction of civil courts barred.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_125_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_125_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013&sectionId=101792&sectionno=125&orderno=125&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013
obj_root_law_sections_125_content:
  string
  line `No civil court shall have jurisdiction in respect of any`
  line `matter to which any provision of this Code applies and no injunction shall be granted by any civil court in`
  line `respect of anything which is done or intended to be done by or under this Code.`
obj_root_law_sections_125_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_126:
  sectionId (101793)
  sectionNo (126)
  orderNo 126
  title `Protection of action taken in good faith.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_126_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_126_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013&sectionId=101793&sectionno=126&orderno=126&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013
obj_root_law_sections_126_content:
  string
  line `(1) No suit, prosecution or other legal proceeding`
  line `shall lie against any person for anything which is in good faith done or intended to be done in pursuance`
  line `of this Code or any rule or regulation or bye-laws or order made there under.`
  line
  line `(2) No prosecution or other legal proceeding shall lie against the Government, any Board or`
  line `committees constituted under this Code or any member of such Board or any officer or employee of the`
  line `Government or the Board or any other person authorised by the Government or any Board or committee,`
  line `for any damage caused or likely to be caused by anything which is in good faith done or intended to be`
  line `done in pursuance of this Code or any rule or regulation or bye-laws or order made or issued there under.`
obj_root_law_sections_126_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_127:
  sectionId (101794)
  sectionNo (127)
  orderNo 127
  title `Power to exempt in special cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_127_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_127_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013&sectionId=101794&sectionno=127&orderno=127&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013
obj_root_law_sections_127_content:
  string
  line `(1) The appropriate Government may, by notification and`
  line `subject to such conditions and restrictions, if any, and for such period or periods as may be specified in`
  line `the notification, direct that all or any of the provisions of this Code or the rules or the regulations made`
  line `there under shall not apply to or in relation to any establishment or class of establishments.`
  line
  line `(2) Without prejudice to the generality of sub-section (1), where the State Government is satisfied in`
  line `the public interest that it is necessary to create more economic activities and employment opportunities, it`
  line `may, by notification, exempt, subject to such conditions as it may think fit, any new factory or class or`
  line `description of new factories from all or any of the provisions of this Code for such period from the date`
  line `on which such commercial production starts, as may be specified in the notification:`
  line
  line `Provided that any notification issued by a State Government under the Factories Act, 1948 (63 of`
  line `1948) for the time being in force in the State prior to the commencement of this Code to achieve the same`
  line `purpose as is specified in this sub-section, shall remain in force after such commencement for its`
  line `remaining period as if the provisions of this Code, to the extent they defeat any purpose to be achieved by`
  line `such notification issued by the State Government, were not in force.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--- For the purpose of this sub-section, the expression "new factory or class or description`
  line `of new Factories" means such factory or class or description of Factories which are established and whose`
  line `commercial production start within such period as may be specified in the notification.`
obj_root_law_sections_127_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_128:
  sectionId (101795)
  sectionNo (128)
  orderNo 128
  title `Power to exempt during public emergency.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_128_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_128_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013&sectionId=101795&sectionno=128&orderno=128&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013
obj_root_law_sections_128_content:
  string
  line `In case of a public emergency or disaster or`
  line `pandemic in whole of India or part thereof, the appropriate Government may, by notification, exempt any`
  line `workplace or work activity or class thereof from all or any of the provisions of this Code for such period`
  line `and subject to such conditions as it may think fit:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such notification shall be made for a period exceeding one year at a time.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--- For the purposes of this section "public emergency" means a grave emergency whereby`
  line `the security of India or any part of the territory thereof is threatened, whether by war or external`
  line `aggression or internal disturbance.`
obj_root_law_sections_128_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_129:
  sectionId (101796)
  sectionNo (129)
  orderNo 129
  title `Power to exempt public institution.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_129_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_129_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013&sectionId=101796&sectionno=129&orderno=129&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013
obj_root_law_sections_129_content:
  string
  line `The appropriate Government may exempt, subject to such`
  line `conditions as it may consider necessary, any workshop or workplace where a manufacturing process is`
  line `carried on and which is attached to a public institution maintained for the purposes of education, training,`
  line `research or information, from all or any of the provisions of this Code:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such exemption shall be granted from the provisions relating to hours of work and`
  line `holidays unless the persons having the control of the institution submit, for the approval of the appropriate`
  line `Government, a scheme of the regulation of the hours of employment, intervals for meals, and holidays of`
  line `the persons employed in or attending the institution or who are inmates for the institution, and the`
  line `appropriate Government is satisfied that the provisions of the scheme are not less favourable than the`
  line `corresponding provisions of this Code.`
obj_root_law_sections_129_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_130:
  sectionId (101797)
  sectionNo (130)
  orderNo 130
  title `Persons required to give notice, etc., legally bound to do so.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_130_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_130_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013&sectionId=101797&sectionno=130&orderno=130&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013
obj_root_law_sections_130_content:
  string
  line `Every person required to give`
  line `any notice or to furnish any information to any authority in relation to the provisions of this Code shall be`
  line `legally bound to do so within the meaning of section 176 of the Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860).`
obj_root_law_sections_130_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_131:
  sectionId (101798)
  sectionNo (131)
  orderNo 131
  title `Power of Central Government to amend Schedule.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_131_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_131_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013&sectionId=101798&sectionno=131&orderno=131&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013
obj_root_law_sections_131_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government may, by`
  line `notification, amend any Schedule by way of addition, alteration or omission therein and on any such`
  line `notification being issued, the Schedule shall be deemed to be amended accordingly.`
obj_root_law_sections_131_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_132:
  sectionId (101799)
  sectionNo (132)
  orderNo 132
  title `Power to remove difficulties.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_132_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_132_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013&sectionId=101799&sectionno=132&orderno=132&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013
obj_root_law_sections_132_content:
  string
  line `(1) If any difficulty arises in giving effect to the provisions of`
  line `this Code, the Central Government may, by order published in the Official Gazette, make such provisions`
  line `not inconsistent with the provisions of this Code, as appears to it to be necessary or expedient for`
  line `removing the difficulty:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such order shall be made after the expiry of two years from the date on which this`
  line `Code comes into force.`
  line
  line `(2) Every order made under this section shall, as soon as may be after it is made, be laid before each`
  line `House of Parliament.`
obj_root_law_sections_132_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_133:
  sectionId (101800)
  sectionNo (133)
  orderNo 133
  title `Power of appropriate Government to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_133_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_133_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013&sectionId=101800&sectionno=133&orderno=133&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013
obj_root_law_sections_133_content:
  string
  line `(1) The appropriate Government may,`
  line `subject to the condition of previous publication and by notification, make rules for carrying out the`
  line `purposes of this Code.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:---`
  line
  line `(a) income from the sources under Explanation to clause (x) of sub-section (1) of section 2;`
  line
  line `(b) substance or quantity of substance under clause (zb) of sub-section (1) of section 2;`
  line
  line `(c) the late fee under the proviso to sub-section (1) of section 3;`
  line
  line `(d) the manner of submitting application under sub-section (2) of section 3 and the form of such`
  line `application and the particulars to be contained therein and the fees to be accompanied therewith;`
  line
  line `(e) the form and manner of sending the notice and the authority to whom the notice shall be sent`
  line `and the manner of intimating the authority under sub-section (1) of section 5;`
  line
  line `(f) annual health examination or test free of costs, age of employees or class of employees or`
  line `establishment or class of establishments under clause (c) of sub-section (1) of section 6;`
  line
  line `(g) the information to be included in the letter of appointment and the form of such letter under`
  line `clause (f) of sub-section (1) of section 6;`
  line
  line `(h) the nature of bodily injury and the manner of notice and the time within which the notice shall`
  line `be sent and the authority to which notice shall be sent under sub-section (1) of section 10;`
  line
  line `(i) nature of dangerous occurrence and the form of notice, the time within which and the authority`
  line `to which notice shall be sent under section 11;`
  line
  line `(j) the form of notice related to certain diseases and the time within which the notice shall be sent`
  line `and the authority to which the notice shall be sent under sub-section (1) of section 12;`
  line
  line `(k) the form and manner of the report and the time within which such report shall be sent to the`
  line `office of the Chief Inspector-cum-Facilitator under sub-section (2) of section 12;`
  line
  line `(l) manner of making report by employee under clause (d) and other duties of employees under`
  line `clause (g) of section 13;`
  line
  line `(m) manner of sending report of action taken under sub-section (3) of section 14;`
  line
  line `(n) the manner of constituting a safety committee and the manner and the purpose for choosing the`
  line `representative of the workers in the Safety Committee under sub-section (1) of section 22;`
  line
  line `(o) the qualifications, duties and number of safety officers under sub-section (2) of section 22;`
  line
  line `(p) conditions for exemption of workers from weekly and compensatory holidays under subsection (2) of section 26;`
  line
  line `(q) the total number of overtime under second proviso to section 27;`
  line
  line `(r) circumstances for exemption from restriction on double employment in factory and mine under`
  line `section 30;`
  line
  line `(s) the form of notice and manner of display of such notice and the manner in which such notice`
  line `shall be sent to the Inspector-cum-Facilitator under sub-section (2) of section 31;`
  line
  line `(t) the form of register and particulars of workers under clause (a) of section 33;`
  line
  line `(u) the manner and form of displaying notices under clause (b) of section 33;`
  line
  line `(v) return, manner of filing the return and periods of filing return to the Inspector-cum-Facilitator`
  line `under clause (d) of section 33;`
  line
  line `(w) the qualification and experience of Chief Inspector-cum-Facilitator under sub-section (5) of`
  line `section 34;`
  line
  line `(x) the manner of taking samples of any article or substance found in any premises and air of`
  line `atmosphere under clause (x) of sub-section (1) of section 35;`
  line
  line `(y) the other powers and duties under clause (xiv) of sub-section (1) of section 35;`
  line
  line `(z) the specialised qualification and experience, duties and responsibilities of experts to be`
  line `empanelled under section 37;`
  line
  line `(za) the manner of providing alternative employment under sub-clause (d) of clause (A) of subsection (1) of section 38;`
  line
  line `(zb) the qualification for the appointment of medical practitioner and other establishment under`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 42;`
  line
  line `(zc) other establishment engaged in the dangerous occupation or processes under clause (a) of`
  line `sub-section (2) of section 42;`
  line
  line `(zd) medical supervision and other establishment under clause (b) of sub-section (2) of section 42;`
  line
  line `(ze) other establishment under clause (c) of sub-section (2) of section 42;`
  line
  line `(zf) conditions relating to safety, holidays and working hours or any other condition to be observed`
  line `by the employer under section 43;`
  line
  line `(zg) the manner of requiring the employer to provide the adequate safeguards under section 44;`
  line
  line `(zh) conditions including, in particular, conditions as to hours of work, fixation of wages and other`
  line `essential amenities in respect of contract labour under clause (a) of sub-section (3) of section 47;`
  line
  line `(zi) the form and manner of application and the particulars which such application shall contain`
  line `regarding the number of contract labour, nature of work for which contract labour is to be employed`
  line `and other particulars including the information relating to the employment of inter-State migrant`
  line `workers under sub-section (1) of section 48;`
  line
  line `(zj) the procedure under sub-section (2) of section 48;`
  line
  line `(zk) manner of applying for the renewal of licence and the manner of renewal of licence under subsection (3) of section 48;`
  line
  line `(zl) responsibility of the contractor under sub-section (4) of section 48;`
  line
  line `(zm) the manner of intimation of work order and time-limit for such intimation under subsection (1) of section 50;`
  line
  line `(zn) the manner of suspending or cancelling the licence under sub-section (2) of section 50;`
  line
  line `(zo) the period before which the wages shall be paid under sub-section (1) of section 55;`
  line
  line `(zp) the mode of payment of wages under proviso to sub-section (2) of section 55;`
  line
  line `(zq) the manner of payment of wages from security deposit under sub-section (4) of section 55;`
  line
  line `(zr) the form of issuing experience certificate under section 56;`
  line
  line `(zs) the form and manner of making application under clause (b) of sub-section (2) of section 57;`
  line
  line `(zt) period of making report and the period of deciding the question under clause (c) of subsection (2) of section 57;`
  line
  line `(zu) minimum service for entitlement, class of travel and other matters under section 61;`
  line
  line `(zv) manner of providing facility of toll free helpline under section 63;`
  line
  line `(zw) manner of providing for study on inter-State migrant workers under section 64;`
  line
  line `(zx) authority to whom a copy of the agreement shall be forwarded by the producer under subsection (3) of section 66;`
  line
  line `(zy) details under clause (vii) of sub-section (4) of section 66;`
  line
  line `(zz) rules in respect of factory or class or description of factories under sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 79;`
  line
  line `(zza) mode of submission of application under sub-section (2) of section 79;`
  line
  line `(zzb) common facilities and services for joint liability of owner of premises and occupiers of the`
  line `factories under section 80;`
  line
  line `(zzc) rules under section 82;`
  line
  line `(zzd) purposes under sub-section (1) of section 83;`
  line
  line `(zze) form of application under sub-section (2) of section 83;`
  line
  line `(zzf) the appellate authority for appeal against the order of Inspector-cum-Facilitator of factory and`
  line `the manner of appeal under section 90;`
  line
  line `(zzg) rules under section 91;`
  line
  line `(zzh) manner of holding enquiry under sub-section (1) of section 111;`
  line
  line `(zzi) form and manner of preferring appeal and the fee to accompany such appeal under subsection (3) of section 111;`
  line
  line `(zzj) manner of compounding under sub-section (1) of section 114;`
  line
  line `(zzk) other sources of fund under sub-section (2) of section 115;`
  line
  line `(zzl) the manner of administering and expending the Fund under sub-section (3) of section 115;`
  line
  line `(zzm) the form of application, manner of filing the application and the fee to be accompanied`
  line `therewith including the information relating to the employment of inter-State migrant workers under`
  line `sub-section (2) of section 119;`
  line
  line `(zzn) actions, manner of taking actions and inquiry under sub-section (3) of section 119;`
  line
  line `(zzo) the form of appeal, the fee to be accompanied therewith and the appellate authority under subsection (6) of section 119;`
  line
  line `(zzp) the manner of survey under sub-section (2) of section 121;`
  line
  line `(zzq) any other matter which is required to be, or may be, prescribed under this Code.`
obj_root_law_sections_133_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_134:
  sectionId (101801)
  sectionNo (134)
  orderNo 134
  title `Power of Central Government to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_134_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_134_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013&sectionId=101801&sectionno=134&orderno=134&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013
obj_root_law_sections_134_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, subject to`
  line `the condition of previous publication and by notification, make rules for carrying out the purposes of this`
  line Code.
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:---`
  line
  line `(a) the other authority under sub-clause (iii) of clause (zs) of sub-section (1) of section 2;`
  line
  line `(b) the matters which are directly related to the condition of ship under the proviso to subclause (iii) of clause (zs) of sub-section (1) of section 2;`
  line
  line `(c) other period under clause (a) of sub-section (1) of section 3;`
  line
  line `(d) the form of certificate of registration, the time within which and the conditions subject to which`
  line `such certificate shall be issued under sub-section (3) of section 3;`
  line
  line `(e) the form of intimation by the employer electronically and the manner of amendment in the`
  line `certificate electronically under sub-section (4) of section 3;`
  line
  line `(f) the manner of informing closing of establishment and certifying payment to the registering`
  line `officer under sub-section (5) of section 3;`
  line
  line `(g) procedure for nomination and discharge of functions of Members of National Board under`
  line `sub-section (3) of section 16;`
  line
  line `(h) the terms and conditions of service of officers and employees of the National Board under`
  line `sub-section (4) of section 16;`
  line
  line `(i) the number of members of technical committees or advisory committees and their qualifications`
  line `under sub-section (5) of section 16;`
  line
  line `(j) the form and manner of collecting, compiling and analyzing occupational safety and health`
  line `statistics under sub-section (1) of section 21;`
  line
  line `(k) the form and manner of maintaining database electronically or otherwise and the documents to`
  line `be produced under sub-section (2) of section 21;`
  line
  line `(l) health and working conditions under sub-section (1) of section 23;`
  line
  line `(m) regarding matters specified in sub-section (2) of section 23;`
  line
  line `(n) welfare facilities for the employees under sub-section (1) of section 24;`
  line
  line `(o) regarding matters specified in sub-section (2) of section 24;`
  line
  line `(p) facility of creche under sub-section (3) of section 24;`
  line
  line `(q) definition of "running time" in relation to a working day under clause (a) of the Explanation to`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 25;`
  line
  line `(r) the hours of work for working journalist under sub-section (2) of section 25;`
  line
  line `(s) other kinds of leave under clause (i) of sub-section (3) of section 25;`
  line
  line `(t) the maximum period of accumulating leave under clause (ii) of sub-section (3) of section 25;`
  line
  line `(u) the limit up to which the earned leave may be availed of at a time and the reasons for which`
  line `such leave may be exceeding under clause (iii) of sub-section (3) of section 25;`
  line
  line `(v) conditions and restrictions for entitlement of cash compensation under clause (iv) of subsection (3) of section 25;`
  line
  line `(w) powers and duties of District Magistrate under section 36;`
  line
  line `(x) requisite qualifications or criteria under sub-section (1) of section 47;`
  line
  line `(y) period of renewal of licence under sub-section (2) of section 47;`
  line
  line `(z) procedure under clause (b) of sub-section (1) of section 51;`
  line
  line `(za) form of agreement under clause (a), and the name and other particulars under clause (b) of`
  line `sub-section (2) of section 66;`
  line
  line `(zb) the matter which may be saved and the qualifications of sole manager under sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 67;`
  line
  line `(zc) the conditions relating to number of employees, depth of excavation and other matters under`
  line `clause (a) of sub-section (1) of section 68;`
  line
  line `(zd) conditions relating to workings, opencast workings and explosives under clause (b) of subsection (1) of section 68;`
  line
  line `(ze) to declare the mines and part thereof for the purpose of applicability of the provisions of this`
  line `Code under sub-section (2) of section 68;`
  line
  line `(zf) the authority, the manner of informing such authority and the time limit for making such`
  line `information under sub-section (3) of section 68;`
  line
  line `(zg) to provide for medical examination of apprentice, other trainee or employee under subsection (3) of section 70;`
  line
  line `(zh) to exempt certain persons or category of persons holding positions of supervision or`
  line `management and the persons employed in mine and the persons employed therein under section 71;`
  line
  line `(zi) to provide for vocational training and rescue and recovery services to the persons employed in`
  line `a mine under section 72;`
  line
  line `(zj) medical authority under sub-section (2) of section 117;`
  line
  line `(zk) rules under sub-section (4) of section 121;`
  line
  line `(zl) the language of the bye-laws under sub-section (7) of section 139;`
  line
  line `(zm) any other matter which is required to be, or may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_134_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_135:
  sectionId (101802)
  sectionNo (135)
  orderNo 135
  title `Power of State Government to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_135_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_135_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013&sectionId=101802&sectionno=135&orderno=135&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013
obj_root_law_sections_135_content:
  string
  line `(1) The State Government may, subject to the`
  line `condition of previous publication and by notification, make rules for the carrying out the provisions of`
  line `this Code`
  line
  line `(2) In particular and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:---`
  line
  line `(a) the constitution, procedure and other matters relating to State Advisory Board under subsection (2) of section 17`
  line
  line `(b) the number of members and their qualifications under sub-section (3) of section 17`
  line
  line `(c) the form of application and the payment of fees under sub-section (2) of section 74`
  line
  line `(d) the manner of preparing the plan of the place or premises under sub-section (3) of section 74`
  line
  line `(e) other matters under clause (e) of sub-section (4) of section 74`
  line
  line `(f) fees under sub-section (6) of section 74`
  line
  line `(g) period under the second proviso to sub-section (6) of section 74`
  line
  line `(h) the time of filing appeal and fees under section 75`
  line
  line `(i) the form of application by the employee and conditions under sub-section (1) of section 76`
  line
  line `(j) form of maintaining the record of the work under sub-section (2) of section 76`
  line
  line `(k) the manner of disclosing information by occupier of a factory under sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 84`
  line
  line `(l) the interval of informing Chief Inspector-cum-Facilitator and the local authority about the policy`
  line `with respect to the health and safety of the workers under sub-section (2) of section 84`
  line
  line `(m) the form and manner of informing Chief Inspector-cum-Facilitator under sub-section (5) of`
  line `section 84`
  line
  line `(n) the manner of publicising among the workers and the general public living in the vicinity of the`
  line `factory the measures and disposal laid down under sub-section (7) of section 84`
  line
  line `(o) the conditions for accessibility to the record by the workers under clause (a) of section 85`
  line
  line `(p) the qualification and experience of persons handling hazardous substance and manner of`
  line `providing necessary facilities for protecting the workers under clause (b) of section 85`
  line
  line `(q) the manner of providing for medical examination of a worker under sub-clause (ii) of clause (c)`
  line `of section 85`
  line
  line `(r) the measures or standards under sub-section (1) of section 86`
  line
  line `(s) the value of the maximum permissible limit of exposure of chemical and toxic substances in`
  line `manufacturing process in any factory under section 88`
  line
  line `(t) requiring every employer to make in his plantation provisions in respect of as specified in`
  line `clauses (a) to (d) of sub-section (1) of section 92`
  line
  line `(u) for prohibiting or, restricting employment of women or adolescents under sub-section (2) of`
  line `section 93`
  line
  line `(v) qualifications under sub-section (3) of section 93`
  line
  line `(w) other matters under sub-section (4) of section 93`
  line
  line `(x) manner of periodical medical examination of worker under sub-section (5) of section 93`
  line
  line `(y) the manner of providing facilities, clothing and equipment under sub-section (7) of section 93`
  line
  line `(z) precautionary notices under sub-section (9) of section 93`
  line
  line `(za) any other matter which is required to be, or may be, prescribed`
  line
  line `(3) The Central Government may, by notification and in consultation with the State Government,`
  line `make rules for the purposes of bringing uniformity, throughout the country, in occupational safety, health`
  line `or such other matters as it considers necessary in respect of factories`
obj_root_law_sections_135_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_136:
  sectionId (101803)
  sectionNo (136)
  orderNo 136
  title `Power of Central Government to make regulations in relation to mines and dock work.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_136_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_136_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013&sectionId=101803&sectionno=136&orderno=136&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013
obj_root_law_sections_136_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government may, by notification, make regulations consistent with this Code for all or any of`
  line `the following purposes, namely:---`
  line
  line `(a) for specifying the qualifications required for appointment as Inspector-cum-Facilitator;`
  line
  line `(b) for specifying and regulating the duties and powers of the Chief Inspector-cum-Facilitator and`
  line `of Inspector-cum-Facilitators in regard to the inspection of mines under this Code;`
  line
  line `(c) for specifying the duties of owners, agents and managers of mines and of persons acting under`
  line `them, and for specifying the qualifications (including age) of agents and managers of mines and of`
  line `persons acting under them;`
  line
  line `(d) for requiring facilities to be provided for enabling managers of mines and other persons acting`
  line `under them to efficiently discharge their duties;`
  line
  line `(e) for regulating the manner of ascertaining, by examination or otherwise, the qualifications of`
  line `managers of mines and persons acting under them, and the granting and renewal of certificates of`
  line competency;
  line
  line `(f) for fixing the fees, if any, to be paid in respect of such examinations and of the grant and`
  line `renewal of such certificates;`
  line
  line `(g) for determining the circumstances in which and the conditions subject to which it shall be`
  line `lawful for more mines than one to be under a single manager, or for any mines to be under a manager`
  line `not having the specified qualifications;`
  line
  line `(h) for providing for inquiries to be made under this Code, including any inquiry relating to`
  line `misconduct or incompetence on the part of any person holding a certificate under this Code and for the`
  line `suspension or cancellation of any such certificate and for providing, wherever necessary, that the`
  line `person appointed to hold an inquiry shall have all the powers of a civil court under the Code of Civil`
  line `Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908) , for the purpose of enforcing the attendance of witnesses and compelling`
  line `the production of documents and material objects;`
  line
  line `(i) for regulating, subject to the provisions of the Indian Explosives Act, 1884 (4 of 1884) , and of`
  line `any rules made there under, the storage, conveyance and use of explosives;`
  line
  line `(j) for prohibiting, restricting or regulating the employment of women in mines or in any class of`
  line `mines or on particular kinds of labour which are attended by danger to the life, safety or health of such`
  line `persons and for limiting the weight of any single load that may be carried by any such person;`
  line
  line `(k) for providing for the safety of the persons employed in a mine, their means of entrance there`
  line `into and exit therefrom, the number of shafts or outlets to be furnished, and the fencing of shafts, pits,`
  line `outlets, pathways and subsidences;`
  line
  line `(l) for prohibiting the employment in a mine either as manager or in any other specified capacity of`
  line `any person except persons paid by the owner of the mine and directly answerable to the owner or`
  line `manager of the mine;`
  line
  line `(m) for providing for the safety of the roads and working places in mines, including the siting,`
  line `maintenance and extraction or reduction of pillars or blocks of minerals and the maintenance of`
  line `sufficient barriers between mine and mine;`
  line
  line `(n) for the inspection of workings and sealed off fire-areas in a mine, and for the restriction of`
  line `workings in the vicinity of the sea or any lake or river or any other body of surface water, whether`
  line `natural or artificial, or of any public road or building, and for requiring due precaution to be taken`
  line `against the irruption or inrush of water or other liquid matter into, outbreak of fire in or premature`
  line `collapse of, any workings;`
  line
  line `(o) for providing for the ventilation of mines and the action to be taken in respect of dust, fire, and`
  line `inflammable and noxious gases, including precautions against spontaneous combustion, underground`
  line `fire and coal dust;`
  line
  line `(p) for regulating, subject to the provisions of the Electricity Act, 2003 (36 of 2003) , and of any`
  line `rules made there under, the generation, storage, transformation, transmission and use of electricity in`
  line `mines and for providing for the care and the regulation of the use of all electrical apparatus and`
  line `electrical cables in mines and of all other machinery and plant therein;`
  line
  line `(q) "for regulating the use of machinery in mines, for providing for the safety of persons employed`
  line `on or near such machinery and on haulage roads and for restricting the use of certain classes of`
  line `locomotives underground;`
  line
  line `(r) for providing for proper lighting of mines and regulating the use of safety lamps therein and for`
  line `the search of persons entering a mine in which safety lamps are in use;`
  line
  line `(s) for providing against explosions or ignitions of inflammable gas or dust or irruptions of or`
  line `accumulations of water in mines and against danger arising therefrom and for prohibiting, restricting`
  line `or regulating the extraction of minerals in circumstances likely to result in the premature collapse of`
  line `workings or to result in or to aggravate the collapse of workings or irruptions of water or ignitions in`
  line mines;
  line
  line `(t) for specifying type of accidents for the purposes of notice under section 10 and for specifying`
  line `the notices of accidents and dangerous occurrences, and the notices, reports and returns of mineral`
  line `output, persons employed and other matters provided for by regulations, to be furnished by owners,`
  line `agents and managers of mines, and for specifying the forms of such notices, returns and reports, the`
  line `persons and authorities to whom they are to be furnished, the particulars to be contained in them, and`
  line `the time within which they are to be submitted;`
  line
  line `(u) for requiring owners, agents and managers of mines to have fixed boundaries for the mines, for`
  line `specifying the plans and sections and field notes connected therewith to be kept by them and the`
  line `manner and places in which such plans, sections and field notes are to be kept for purposes of record`
  line `and for the submission of copies thereof to the Chief Inspector-cum-Facilitator, and for requiring the`
  line `making of fresh surveys and plans by them, and in the event of non-compliance, for having the survey`
  line `made and plans prepared through any other agency and for the recovery of expenses thereof in the`
  line `same manner as an arrear of land revenue;`
  line
  line `(v) for regulating the procedure on the occurrence of accidents or accidental explosions or ignitions`
  line `in or about, mines; for dealing effectively with the situation;`
  line
  line `(w) for specifying the form of, and the particulars to be contained in, the notice to be given by the`
  line `owner, agent or manager of a mine under section 5;`
  line
  line `(x) for specifying the notice to be given by the owner, agent or manager of a mine before mining`
  line `operations are commenced at or extended to any point within forty-five meters of any railway subject`
  line `to the provisions of the Indian Railways Act, 1989 (24 of 1989) or of any public roads or other works`
  line `as the case may be, which are maintained by the Government or any local authority;`
  line
  line `(y) for the protection from injury, in respect of any mine when the workings are discontinued, of`
  line `property vested in the Government or any local authority or railway company as defined in the Indian`
  line `Railways Act, 1989 (24 of 1989);`
  line
  line `(z) for requiring protective works to be constructed by the owner, agent or manager of a mine`
  line `before the mine is closed, and in the event of non-compliance, for getting such works executed by any`
  line `other agency and for recovering the expenses thereof from such owner in the same manner as an arrear`
  line `of land revenue;`
  line
  line `(za) for requiring the fencing of any mine or part of a mine or any quarry, incline, shaft, pit or`
  line `outlet, whether the same is being worked or not, or any dangerous or prohibited area, subsidence,`
  line `haulage, tramline or pathway, where such fencing is necessary for the protection of the public;`
  line
  line `(zb) for specifying the number of officials to be appointed;`
  line
  line `(zc) for specifying the qualifications of the officials to be appointed;`
  line
  line `(zd) for specifying the qualifications and experience of the agents;`
  line
  line `(ze) for specifying the period during which the agent shall be resident in India;`
  line
  line `(zf) for specifying duties and responsibilities of suppliers, designers, importer and contractors for`
  line `safety in mines;`
  line
  line `(zg) for requiring the owners, agents and managers of mines to formulate, maintain and enforce`
  line `safety management plan in their mines;`
  line
  line `(zh) for requiring the managers of mines to formulate and implement codes of practice or standard`
  line `operating procedure in respect of any machinery or operation used in the mines;`
  line
  line `(zi) for providing for the safety in opencast mines and associated operations and machineries used`
  line therein;
  line
  line `(zj) for regulating the extraction of methane from working or abandoned coal mines or from virgin`
  line `coal seam;`
  line
  line `(zk) for specifying the forms of returns which shall be filed by the establishments or the class of`
  line `establishments under this Code;`
  line
  line `(zl) for the general requirement relating to the construction, equipping and maintenance for the`
  line `safety of working places on shore, ship, dock, structure and other places at which any dock work is`
  line `carried on;`
  line
  line `(zm) for the safety of any regular approaches over a dock, wharf, quay or other places which dock`
  line `workers have to use for going for work and for fencing of such places and projects;`
  line
  line `(zn) for the efficient lighting of all areas of dock, ship, any other vessel, dock structure or working`
  line `places where any dock work is carried on and of all approaches to such places to which dock workers`
  line `are required to go in the course of their employment;`
  line
  line `(zo) providing and maintaining adequate ventilation and suitable temperature in every building or`
  line `an enclosure on ship where dock workers are employed;`
  line
  line `(zp) providing for the fire and explosion prevention and protection;`
  line
  line `(zq) providing for safe means of access to ships, holds, stagings, equipment, lifting appliances and`
  line `other working places;`
  line
  line `(zr) providing for the safety of workers engaged in the opening and closing of hatches, protection`
  line `of ways and other openings in the docks which may be dangerous to them;`
  line
  line `(zs) providing for the safety of workers on docks from the risk of falling overboard being struck by`
  line `cargo during loading or unloading operations;`
  line
  line `(zt) providing for the construction, maintenance and use of lifting and other cargo handling`
  line `appliances and services, such as, pallets containing or supporting loads and provision of safety`
  line `appliances on them, if necessary;`
  line
  line `(zu) providing for the safety of workers employed in freight container terminals or other terminals`
  line `for handling unitised cargo;`
  line
  line `(zv) providing for the fencing of machinery, live electrical conductors, steam pipes and hazardous`
  line openings;
  line
  line `(zw) providing for the construction, maintenance and use of staging;`
  line
  line `(zx) providing for the rigging and use of ship's derricks;`
  line
  line `(zy) providing for the testing, examination, inspection and certification as appropriate of loose gears`
  line `including chains and ropes and of slings and other lifting devices used in the dock work;`
  line
  line `(zz) providing for the precautions to be taken to facilitate escape of workers when employed in a`
  line `hold, bin, hopper or the like or between decks of a hold while handling coal or other bulk cargo;`
  line
  line `(zza) providing for the measures to be taken in order to prevent dangerous methods of working in`
  line `the stacking, unstacking, stowing and unstowing of cargo or handling in connection therewith;`
  line
  line `(zzb) providing for the handling of dangerous substances and working in dangerous or harmful`
  line `environments and the precautions to be taken in connection with such handling;`
  line
  line `(zzc) providing for the work in connection with cleaning, chipping, painting, operations and`
  line `precautions to be taken in connection with such work;`
  line
  line `(zzd) providing for the employment of persons for handling cargo, handling appliances, power`
  line `operated hatch covers or other power operated ship's equipment, such as, door in the hull of a ship,`
  line `ramp, retraceable car deck or similar equipment or to give signals to the drivers of such machinery;`
  line
  line `(zze) providing for the transport of dock workers;`
  line
  line `(zzf) providing for the precautions to be taken to protect dock workers against harmful effects of`
  line `excessive noise, vibrations and air pollution at the workplace;`
  line
  line `(zzg) providing for protective equipment or protective clothing;`
  line
  line `(zzh) providing for the sanitary, washing and welfare facilities;`
  line
  line `(zzi) providing for---`
  line
  line `(i) the medical supervision;`
  line
  line `(ii) the ambulance rooms, first aid and rescue facilities and arrangements for the removal of`
  line `dock workers to the nearest place of treatment;`
  line `(iii) the safety and health organisation; and`
  line
  line `(iv) the training of dock workers and for the obligations and rights of the dock workers for their`
  line `safety and health at the workplace;`
  line
  line `(zzj) providing for the investigation of occupational accidents, dangerous occurrences and diseases,`
  line `specifying such diseases and the forms of notices, the persons and authorities to whom, they are to be`
  line `furnished, the particulars to be contained in them and the time within which they are to be submitted;`
  line
  line `(zzk) providing for the submission of statement of accidents, man-days lost, volume of cargo`
  line `handled and particulars of dock workers; and`
  line
  line `(zzl) any other matter which is required to be or may be specified by regulation.`
obj_root_law_sections_136_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_137:
  sectionId (101804)
  sectionNo (137)
  orderNo 137
  title `Prior publication of rules, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_137_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_137_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013&sectionId=101804&sectionno=137&orderno=137&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013
obj_root_law_sections_137_content:
  string
  line `The power to make rules, regulations, and bye-laws under this`
  line `Code shall be subject to the condition of the previous publication of the same being made, in the`
  line `following manner, namely:---`
  line
  line `(a) the date to be specified after a draft of rule, regulation, and bye-laws proposed to be made will`
  line `be taken under consideration, shall not be less than forty-five days from the date on which the draft of`
  line `the proposed rule, regulation and bye-laws is published for general information;`
  line
  line `(b) rule, regulation and bye-laws shall be published in the Official Gazette and on such publication,`
  line `shall have effect as if enacted in this Code.`
obj_root_law_sections_137_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_138:
  sectionId (101805)
  sectionNo (138)
  orderNo 138
  title `Power to make regulation without previous publication.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_138_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_138_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013&sectionId=101805&sectionno=138&orderno=138&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013
obj_root_law_sections_138_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything`
  line `contained in section 137, regulations under section 136 may be made without previous publication and`
  line
  line `without reference to the National Occupational Safety Health Advisory Board constituted under`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 16, if the Central Government is satisfied that for the prevention of apprehended`
  line `danger or the speedy remedy of conditions likely to cause danger and to avoid delay it is necessary to`
  line `dispense with from such publication and reference.`
obj_root_law_sections_138_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_139:
  sectionId (101806)
  sectionNo (139)
  orderNo 139
  title Bye-laws.
  content obj_root_law_sections_139_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_139_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013&sectionId=101806&sectionno=139&orderno=139&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013
obj_root_law_sections_139_content:
  string
  line `(1) The employer of a mine may, and shall, if called upon to do so by the Chief`
  line `Inspector-cum-Facilitator or Inspector-cum-Facilitator, frame and submit to the Chief Inspector-cum-Facilitator or Inspector-cum-Facilitator a draft of such bye-laws, not being inconsistent with this Code or`
  line `any rules or regulations or standards for the time being in force, governing the use of any particular`
  line `machinery or the adoption of a particular method of working in the mine, as the employer may deem`
  line `necessary to prevent accidents and provide for the safety, convenience and discipline of the persons`
  line `employed in the mine.`
  line
  line `(2) If any such employer---`
  line
  line `(a) fails to submit within two months a draft of bye-laws after being called upon to do so by the`
  line `Chief Inspector-cum-Facilitator or Inspector-cum-Facilitator; or`
  line
  line `(b) submits a draft of bye-laws which is not in the opinion of the Chief Inspector-cum-Facilitator or`
  line `Inspector-cum-Facilitator sufficient, the Chief Inspector-cum-Facilitator or Inspector-cum-Facilitator`
  line may---
  line
  line `(i) propose a draft of such bye-laws as appear to him to be sufficient; or`
  line
  line `(ii) propose such amendments in any draft submitted to him by the employer as will, in his`
  line `opinion, render it sufficient, and shall send such draft bye-laws or draft amendments to the`
  line `employer for consideration.`
  line
  line `(3) If within a period of two months from the date on which any draft bye-laws or draft amendments`
  line `are sent by the Chief Inspector-cum-Facilitator or Inspector-cum-Facilitator to the employer under the`
  line `provisions of sub-section (2), the Chief Inspector-cum-Facilitator or Inspector-cum-Facilitator and the`
  line `employer are unable to agree as to the terms of the bye-laws to be made under sub-section (1), the Chief`
  line `Inspector-cum-Facilitator or Inspector-cum-Facilitator shall refer the draft bye-laws for settlement to the`
  line `technical committee constituted under sub-section (5) of section 16 in respect of mines.`
  line
  line `(4) When such draft bye-laws have been agreed to by the employer and the Chief Inspector-cum-Facilitator or Inspector-cum-Facilitator, or, when they are unable to agree, have been settled by the`
  line `technical Committee constituted under sub-section (5) of section 16 in respect of mines, a copy of the`
  line `draft bye-laws shall be sent by the Chief Inspector-cum-Facilitator or Inspector-cum-Facilitator to the`
  line `Central Government for approval:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Central Government may make such modification of the draft bye-laws as it thinks`
  line `fit:`
  line
  line `Provided further that before the Central Government approves the draft bye-laws, whether with or`
  line `without modifications, there shall be published, in such manner as the Central Government may think best`
  line `adapted for informing the persons affected, a notice of the proposal to make the bye-laws and of the place`
  line `where copies of the draft bye-laws may be obtained, and of the time (which shall not be less than thirty`
  line `days) within which any objections with reference to the draft bye-laws, made by or on behalf of persons`
  line `affected should be sent to the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(5) Every objection under second proviso to sub-section (4) shall be in writing and shall state---`
  line
  line `(i) the specific grounds of objections, and`
  line
  line `(ii) the omissions, additions or modifications asked for.`
  line
  line `(6) The Central Government shall consider any objection made within the required time by or on`
  line `behalf of persons appearing to it to be affected, and may approve the bye-laws either in the form in which`
  line `they were published or after making such amendments thereto as it thinks fit.`
  line
  line `(7) The employer shall cause a copy of the bye-laws, in English and in such other language or`
  line `languages as may be prescribed by the Central Government, to be pasted up in some conspicuous place at`
  line
  line `or near the mine, where the bye-laws may be conveniently read or seen by the persons employed; and, as`
  line `and when the same become defaced, obliterated or destroyed, shall cause them to be pasted again.`
  line
  line `(8) The Central Government may, by order in writing rescind, in whole or in part, any bye-law so`
  line `made, and thereupon such bye-law shall cease to have effect accordingly.`
obj_root_law_sections_139_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_140:
  sectionId (101807)
  sectionNo (140)
  orderNo 140
  title `Powers to regulate general safety and health.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_140_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_140_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013&sectionId=101807&sectionno=140&orderno=140&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013
obj_root_law_sections_140_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding any law for the time being in`
  line `force, the Central Government may make rules to regulate general safety and health of the persons`
  line `residing in whole or part of India, in the event of declaration of an epidemic, pandemic or disaster, for`
  line `such period as may be notified by the Central Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_140_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_141:
  sectionId (101808)
  sectionNo (141)
  orderNo 141
  title `Laying of regulations, rules, byelaws, etc., before Parliament.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_141_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_141_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013&sectionId=101808&sectionno=141&orderno=141&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013
obj_root_law_sections_141_content:
  string
  line `Every rule, regulation,`
  line `standard and bye-laws notified or made by the Central Government under this Code shall be laid, as soon`
  line `as may be after it is notified or made, before each House of Parliament, while it is in session, for a total`
  line `period of thirty days which may be comprised in one session or in two or more successive sessions, and`
  line `if, before the expiry of the session immediately following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid,`
  line `both Houses agree in making any modification in the rule, regulation, standard or bye-law or both Houses`
  line `agree that the rule, regulation, standard or bye-law should not be made, the rule, regulation, standard or`
  line `bye-law shall thereafter have effect only in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so,`
  line `however, that any such modification or annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything`
  line `previously done under that rule, regulation, standard or bye-law, as the case may be.`
obj_root_law_sections_141_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_142:
  sectionId (101809)
  sectionNo (142)
  orderNo 142
  title `Laying of rules made by State Government.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_142_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_142_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013&sectionId=101809&sectionno=142&orderno=142&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013
obj_root_law_sections_142_content:
  string
  line `Every rule made by the State Government under`
  line `this Code shall be laid, as soon as may be, after it is made, before the State Legislature.`
obj_root_law_sections_142_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_143:
  sectionId (101810)
  sectionNo (143)
  orderNo 143
  title `Repeal and Savings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_143_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_143_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013&sectionId=101810&sectionno=143&orderno=143&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00037_2020-37_1764583355013
obj_root_law_sections_143_content:
  string
  line `(1) The following enactments shall stand repealed on and from the dates`
  line `the notification referred to in sub-section (2) of section 1 is issued, namely:---`
  line
  line `(a) The Factories Act, 1948 (63 of 1948);`
  line
  line `(b) The Plantations Labour Act, 1951 (69 of 1951);`
  line
  line `(c) The Mines Act, 1952 (35 of 1952);`
  line
  line `(d) The Working Journalists and other Newspaper Employees (Conditions of Service) and`
  line `Miscellaneous Provisions Act, 1955 (45 of 1955);`
  line
  line `(e) The Working Journalists (Fixation of Rates of Wages) Act, 1958 (29 of 1958);`
  line
  line `(f) The Motor Transport Workers Act, 1961 (27 of 1961);`
  line
  line `(g) The Beedi and Cigar Workers (Conditions of Employment) Act, 1966 (32 of 1966);`
  line
  line `(h) The Contract Labour (Regulation and Abolition) Act, 1970 (37 of 1970);`
  line
  line `(i) The Sales Promotion Employees (Conditions of Service) Act, 1976 (11 of 1976);`
  line
  line `(j) The Inter-State Migrant Workmen (Regulation of Employment and Conditions of Service) Act,`
  line `1979 (30 of 1979);`
  line
  line `(k) The Cine-Workers and Cinema Theatre Workers (Regulation of Employment) Act, 1981 (50 of`
  line `1981);`
  line
  line `(l) The Dock Workers (Safety, Health and Welfare) Act, 1986 (54 of 1986);`
  line
  line `(m) The Building and Other Construction Workers (Regulation of Employment and Conditions of`
  line `Service) Act, 1996 (27 of 1996).`
  line
  line `(2) Every Chief Inspector, Additional Chief Inspector, Joint Chief Inspector, Deputy Chief Inspector,`
  line `Inspector and every other officer appointed for the purposes under any of the provisions of the enactments`
  line `repealed by this Code, shall be deemed to have been appointed under this Code for such purposes under`
  line `this Code.`
  line
  line `(3) Notwithstanding repeal under sub-section (1), anything done or any action taken under the`
  line `enactments so repealed (including any rule, regulation, bye-laws, notification, nomination, appointment,`
  line `order or direction made there under) shall be deemed to have been done or taken under the corresponding`
  line
  line `provisions of this Code and shall remain in force to the extent they are not contrary to the provisions of`
  line `this Code till they are repealed by the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(4) Without prejudice to the provisions of sub-section (2), provisions of section 6 of the General`
  line `Clauses Act, 1897 (10 of 1897) shall apply to the repeal of such enactments.`
obj_root_law_sections_143_footnotes:
  string
  line
